1016 
1017 static void stripUnusedQualifiers(Qualifiers &Q) {
1018  // Ignore these qualifiers for now.
1019  Q.removeObjCGCAttr();
1020  Q.removeAddressSpace();
1021  Q.removeObjCLifetime();
1022  Q.removeUnaligned();
1023 }
1024 
1025 static llvm::dwarf::Tag getNextQualifier(Qualifiers &Q) {
1026  if (Q.hasConst()) {
1027  Q.removeConst();
1028  return llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_const_type;
1029  }
1030  if (Q.hasVolatile()) {
1031  Q.removeVolatile();
1032  return llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_volatile_type;
1033  }
1034  if (Q.hasRestrict()) {
1035  Q.removeRestrict();
1036  return llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_restrict_type;
1037  }
1038  return (llvm::dwarf::Tag)0;
1039 }
1040 
1041 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateQualifiedType(QualType Ty,
1042  llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
1043  QualifierCollector Qc;
1044  const Type *T = Qc.strip(Ty);
1045 
1046  stripUnusedQualifiers(Qc);
1047 
1048  // We will create one Derived type for one qualifier and recurse to handle any
1049  // additional ones.
1050  llvm::dwarf::Tag Tag = getNextQualifier(Qc);
1051  if (!Tag) {
1052  assert(Qc.empty() && "Unknown type qualifier for debug info");
1053  return getOrCreateType(QualType(T, 0), Unit);
1054  }
1055 
1056  auto *FromTy = getOrCreateType(Qc.apply(CGM.getContext(), T), Unit);
1057 
1058  // No need to fill in the Name, Line, Size, Alignment, Offset in case of
1059  // CVR derived types.
1060  return DBuilder.createQualifiedType(Tag, FromTy);
1061 }
1062 
1063 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateQualifiedType(const FunctionProtoType *F,
1064  llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
1065  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI = F->getExtProtoInfo();
1066  Qualifiers &Q = EPI.TypeQuals;
1067  stripUnusedQualifiers(Q);
1068 
1069  // We will create one Derived type for one qualifier and recurse to handle any
1070  // additional ones.
1071  llvm::dwarf::Tag Tag = getNextQualifier(Q);
1072  if (!Tag) {
1073  assert(Q.empty() && "Unknown type qualifier for debug info");
1074  return nullptr;
1075  }
1076 
1077  auto *FromTy =
1078  getOrCreateType(CGM.getContext().getFunctionType(F->getReturnType(),
1079  F->getParamTypes(), EPI),
1080  Unit);
1081 
1082  // No need to fill in the Name, Line, Size, Alignment, Offset in case of
1083  // CVR derived types.
1084  return DBuilder.createQualifiedType(Tag, FromTy);
1085 }
1086 
1087 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const ObjCObjectPointerType *Ty,
1088  llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
1089 
1090  // The frontend treats 'id' as a typedef to an ObjCObjectType,
1091  // whereas 'id<protocol>' is treated as an ObjCPointerType. For the
1092  // debug info, we want to emit 'id' in both cases.
1093  if (Ty->isObjCQualifiedIdType())
1094  return getOrCreateType(CGM.getContext().getObjCIdType(), Unit);
1095 
1096  return CreatePointerLikeType(llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_pointer_type, Ty,
1097  Ty->getPointeeType(), Unit);
1098 }
1099 
1100 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const PointerType *Ty,
1101  llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
1102  return CreatePointerLikeType(llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_pointer_type, Ty,
1103  Ty->getPointeeType(), Unit);
1104 }
1105 
1106 /// \return whether a C++ mangling exists for the type defined by TD.
1107 static bool hasCXXMangling(const TagDecl *TD, llvm::DICompileUnit *TheCU) {
1108  switch (TheCU->getSourceLanguage()) {
1109  case llvm::dwarf::DW_LANG_C_plus_plus:
1110  case llvm::dwarf::DW_LANG_C_plus_plus_11:
1111  case llvm::dwarf::DW_LANG_C_plus_plus_14:
1112  return true;
1113  case llvm::dwarf::DW_LANG_ObjC_plus_plus:
1114  return isa<CXXRecordDecl>(TD) || isa<EnumDecl>(TD);
1115  default:
1116  return false;
1117  }
1118 }
1119 
1120 // Determines if the debug info for this tag declaration needs a type
1121 // identifier. The purpose of the unique identifier is to deduplicate type
1122 // information for identical types across TUs. Because of the C++ one definition
1123 // rule (ODR), it is valid to assume that the type is defined the same way in
1124 // every TU and its debug info is equivalent.
1125 //
1126 // C does not have the ODR, and it is common for codebases to contain multiple
1127 // different definitions of a struct with the same name in different TUs.
1128 // Therefore, if the type doesn't have a C++ mangling, don't give it an
1129 // identifer. Type information in C is smaller and simpler than C++ type
1130 // information, so the increase in debug info size is negligible.
1131 //
1132 // If the type is not externally visible, it should be unique to the current TU,
1133 // and should not need an identifier to participate in type deduplication.
1134 // However, when emitting CodeView, the format internally uses these
1135 // unique type name identifers for references between debug info. For example,
1136 // the method of a class in an anonymous namespace uses the identifer to refer
1137 // to its parent class. The Microsoft C++ ABI attempts to provide unique names
1138 // for such types, so when emitting CodeView, always use identifiers for C++
1139 // types. This may create problems when attempting to emit CodeView when the MS
1140 // C++ ABI is not in use.
1141 static bool needsTypeIdentifier(const TagDecl *TD, CodeGenModule &CGM,
1142  llvm::DICompileUnit *TheCU) {
1143  // We only add a type identifier for types with C++ name mangling.
1144  if (!hasCXXMangling(TD, TheCU))
1145  return false;
1146 
1147  // Externally visible types with C++ mangling need a type identifier.
1148  if (TD->isExternallyVisible())
1149  return true;
1150 
1151  // CodeView types with C++ mangling need a type identifier.
1152  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCodeView)
1153  return true;
1154 
1155  return false;
1156 }
1157 
1158 // Returns a unique type identifier string if one exists, or an empty string.
1159 static SmallString<256> getTypeIdentifier(const TagType *Ty, CodeGenModule &CGM,
1160  llvm::DICompileUnit *TheCU) {
1161  SmallString<256> Identifier;
1162  const TagDecl *TD = Ty->getDecl();
1163 
1164  if (!needsTypeIdentifier(TD, CGM, TheCU))
1165  return Identifier;
1166  if (const auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(TD))
1167  if (RD->getDefinition())
1168  if (RD->isDynamicClass() &&
1169  CGM.getVTableLinkage(RD) == llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage)
1170  return Identifier;
1171 
1172  // TODO: This is using the RTTI name. Is there a better way to get
1173  // a unique string for a type?
1174  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Identifier);
1175  CGM.getCXXABI().getMangleContext().mangleCXXRTTIName(QualType(Ty, 0), Out);
1176  return Identifier;
1177 }
1178 
1179 /// \return the appropriate DWARF tag for a composite type.
1180 static llvm::dwarf::Tag getTagForRecord(const RecordDecl *RD) {
1181  llvm::dwarf::Tag Tag;
1182  if (RD->isStruct() || RD->isInterface())
1183  Tag = llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_structure_type;
1184  else if (RD->isUnion())
1185  Tag = llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_union_type;
1186  else {
1187  // FIXME: This could be a struct type giving a default visibility different
1188  // than C++ class type, but needs llvm metadata changes first.
1189  assert(RD->isClass());
1190  Tag = llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_class_type;
1191  }
1192  return Tag;
1193 }
1194 
1195 llvm::DICompositeType *
1196 CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateRecordFwdDecl(const RecordType *Ty,
1197  llvm::DIScope *Ctx) {
1198  const RecordDecl *RD = Ty->getDecl();
1199  if (llvm::DIType *T = getTypeOrNull(CGM.getContext().getRecordType(RD)))
1200  return cast<llvm::DICompositeType>(T);
1201  llvm::DIFile *DefUnit = getOrCreateFile(RD->getLocation());
1202  const unsigned Line =
1203  getLineNumber(RD->getLocation().isValid() ? RD->getLocation() : CurLoc);
1204  StringRef RDName = getClassName(RD);
1205 
1206  uint64_t Size = 0;
1207  uint32_t Align = 0;
1208 
1209  const RecordDecl *D = RD->getDefinition();
1210  if (D && D->isCompleteDefinition())
1211  Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
1212 
1213  llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagFwdDecl;
1214 
1215  // Add flag to nontrivial forward declarations. To be consistent with MSVC,
1216  // add the flag if a record has no definition because we don't know whether
1217  // it will be trivial or not.
1218  if (const CXXRecordDecl *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD))
1219  if (!CXXRD->hasDefinition() ||
1220  (CXXRD->hasDefinition() && !CXXRD->isTrivial()))
1221  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagNonTrivial;
1222 
1223  // Create the type.
1224  SmallString<256> Identifier;
1225  // Don't include a linkage name in line tables only.
1226  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo())
1227  Identifier = getTypeIdentifier(Ty, CGM, TheCU);
1228  llvm::DICompositeType *RetTy = DBuilder.createReplaceableCompositeType(
1229  getTagForRecord(RD), RDName, Ctx, DefUnit, Line, 0, Size, Align, Flags,
1230  Identifier);
1231  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DebugFwdTemplateParams)
1232  if (auto *TSpecial = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RD))
1233  DBuilder.replaceArrays(RetTy, llvm::DINodeArray(),
1234  CollectCXXTemplateParams(TSpecial, DefUnit));
1235  ReplaceMap.emplace_back(
1236  std::piecewise_construct, std::make_tuple(Ty),
1237  std::make_tuple(static_cast<llvm::Metadata *>(RetTy)));
1238  return RetTy;
1239 }
1240 
1241 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreatePointerLikeType(llvm::dwarf::Tag Tag,
1242  const Type *Ty,
1243  QualType PointeeTy,
1244  llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
1245  // Bit size, align and offset of the type.
1246  // Size is always the size of a pointer.
1247  uint64_t Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
1248  auto Align = getTypeAlignIfRequired(Ty, CGM.getContext());
1249  std::optional<unsigned> DWARFAddressSpace =
1250  CGM.getTarget().getDWARFAddressSpace(
1251  CGM.getTypes().getTargetAddressSpace(PointeeTy));
1252 
1253  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 4> Annots;
1254  auto *BTFAttrTy = dyn_cast<BTFTagAttributedType>(PointeeTy);
1255  while (BTFAttrTy) {
1256  StringRef Tag = BTFAttrTy->getAttr()->getBTFTypeTag();
1257  if (!Tag.empty()) {
1258  llvm::Metadata *Ops[2] = {
1259  llvm::MDString::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), StringRef("btf_type_tag")),
1260  llvm::MDString::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), Tag)};
1261  Annots.insert(Annots.begin(),
1262  llvm::MDNode::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), Ops));
1263  }
1264  BTFAttrTy = dyn_cast<BTFTagAttributedType>(BTFAttrTy->getWrappedType());
1265  }
1266 
1267  llvm::DINodeArray Annotations = nullptr;
1268  if (Annots.size() > 0)
1269  Annotations = DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(Annots);
1270 
1271  if (Tag == llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_reference_type ||
1272  Tag == llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_rvalue_reference_type)
1273  return DBuilder.createReferenceType(Tag, getOrCreateType(PointeeTy, Unit),
1274  Size, Align, DWARFAddressSpace);
1275  else
1276  return DBuilder.createPointerType(getOrCreateType(PointeeTy, Unit), Size,
1277  Align, DWARFAddressSpace, StringRef(),
1278  Annotations);
1279 }
1280 
1281 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateStructPtrType(StringRef Name,
1282  llvm::DIType *&Cache) {
1283  if (Cache)
1284  return Cache;
1285  Cache = DBuilder.createForwardDecl(llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_structure_type, Name,
1286  TheCU, TheCU->getFile(), 0);
1287  unsigned Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(CGM.getContext().VoidPtrTy);
1288  Cache = DBuilder.createPointerType(Cache, Size);
1289  return Cache;
1290 }
1291 
1292 uint64_t CGDebugInfo::collectDefaultElementTypesForBlockPointer(
1293  const BlockPointerType *Ty, llvm::DIFile *Unit, llvm::DIDerivedType *DescTy,
1294  unsigned LineNo, SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Metadata *> &EltTys) {
1295  QualType FType;
1296 
1297  // Advanced by calls to CreateMemberType in increments of FType, then
1298  // returned as the overall size of the default elements.
1299  uint64_t FieldOffset = 0;
1300 
1301  // Blocks in OpenCL have unique constraints which make the standard fields
1302  // redundant while requiring size and align fields for enqueue_kernel. See
1303  // initializeForBlockHeader in CGBlocks.cpp
1304  if (CGM.getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
1305  FType = CGM.getContext().IntTy;
1306  EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__size", &FieldOffset));
1307  EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__align", &FieldOffset));
1308  } else {
1309  FType = CGM.getContext().getPointerType(CGM.getContext().VoidTy);
1310  EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__isa", &FieldOffset));
1311  FType = CGM.getContext().IntTy;
1312  EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__flags", &FieldOffset));
1313  EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__reserved", &FieldOffset));
1314  FType = CGM.getContext().getPointerType(Ty->getPointeeType());
1315  EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__FuncPtr", &FieldOffset));
1316  FType = CGM.getContext().getPointerType(CGM.getContext().VoidTy);
1317  uint64_t FieldSize = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
1318  uint32_t FieldAlign = CGM.getContext().getTypeAlign(Ty);
1319  EltTys.push_back(DBuilder.createMemberType(
1320  Unit, "__descriptor", nullptr, LineNo, FieldSize, FieldAlign,
1321  FieldOffset, llvm::DINode::FlagZero, DescTy));
1322  FieldOffset += FieldSize;
1323  }
1324 
1325  return FieldOffset;
1326 }
1327 
1328 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const BlockPointerType *Ty,
1329  llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
1330  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> EltTys;
1331  QualType FType;
1332  uint64_t FieldOffset;
1333  llvm::DINodeArray Elements;
1334 
1335  FieldOffset = 0;
1336  FType = CGM.getContext().UnsignedLongTy;
1337  EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "reserved", &FieldOffset));
1338  EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "Size", &FieldOffset));
1339 
1340  Elements = DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(EltTys);
1341  EltTys.clear();
1342 
1343  llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagAppleBlock;
1344 
1345  auto *EltTy =
1346  DBuilder.createStructType(Unit, "__block_descriptor", nullptr, 0,
1347  FieldOffset, 0, Flags, nullptr, Elements);
1348 
1349  // Bit size, align and offset of the type.
1350  uint64_t Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
1351 
1352  auto *DescTy = DBuilder.createPointerType(EltTy, Size);
1353 
1354  FieldOffset = collectDefaultElementTypesForBlockPointer(Ty, Unit, DescTy,
1355  0, EltTys);
1356 
1357  Elements = DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(EltTys);
1358 
1359  // The __block_literal_generic structs are marked with a special
1360  // DW_AT_APPLE_BLOCK attribute and are an implementation detail only
1361  // the debugger needs to know about. To allow type uniquing, emit
1362  // them without a name or a location.
1363  EltTy = DBuilder.createStructType(Unit, "", nullptr, 0, FieldOffset, 0,
1364  Flags, nullptr, Elements);
1365 
1366  return DBuilder.createPointerType(EltTy, Size);
1367 }
1368 
1369 static llvm::SmallVector<TemplateArgument>
1370 GetTemplateArgs(const TemplateDecl *TD, const TemplateSpecializationType *Ty) {
1371  assert(Ty->isTypeAlias());
1372  // TemplateSpecializationType doesn't know if its template args are
1373  // being substituted into a parameter pack. We can find out if that's
1374  // the case now by inspecting the TypeAliasTemplateDecl template
1375  // parameters. Insert Ty's template args into SpecArgs, bundling args
1376  // passed to a parameter pack into a TemplateArgument::Pack. It also
1377  // doesn't know the value of any defaulted args, so collect those now
1378  // too.
1379  SmallVector<TemplateArgument> SpecArgs;
1380  ArrayRef SubstArgs = Ty->template_arguments();
1381  for (const NamedDecl *Param : TD->getTemplateParameters()->asArray()) {
1382  // If Param is a parameter pack, pack the remaining arguments.
1383  if (Param->isParameterPack()) {
1384  SpecArgs.push_back(TemplateArgument(SubstArgs));
1385  break;
1386  }
1387 
1388  // Skip defaulted args.
1389  // FIXME: Ideally, we wouldn't do this. We can read the default values
1390  // for each parameter. However, defaulted arguments which are dependent
1391  // values or dependent types can't (easily?) be resolved here.
1392  if (SubstArgs.empty()) {
1393  // If SubstArgs is now empty (we're taking from it each iteration) and
1394  // this template parameter isn't a pack, then that should mean we're
1395  // using default values for the remaining template parameters (after
1396  // which there may be an empty pack too which we will ignore).
1397  break;
1398  }
1399 
1400  // Take the next argument.
1401  SpecArgs.push_back(SubstArgs.front());
1402  SubstArgs = SubstArgs.drop_front();
1403  }
1404  return SpecArgs;
1405 }
1406 
1407 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const TemplateSpecializationType *Ty,
1408  llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
1409  assert(Ty->isTypeAlias());
1410  llvm::DIType *Src = getOrCreateType(Ty->getAliasedType(), Unit);
1411 
1412  const TemplateDecl *TD = Ty->getTemplateName().getAsTemplateDecl();
1413  if (isa<BuiltinTemplateDecl>(TD))
1414  return Src;
1415 
1416  const auto *AliasDecl = cast<TypeAliasTemplateDecl>(TD)->getTemplatedDecl();
1417  if (AliasDecl->hasAttr<NoDebugAttr>() || noSystemDebugInfo(AliasDecl, CGM))
1418  return Src;
1419 
1420  SmallString<128> NS;
1421  llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(NS);
1422 
1423  auto PP = getPrintingPolicy();
1424  Ty->getTemplateName().print(OS, PP, TemplateName::Qualified::None);
1425 
1426  SourceLocation Loc = AliasDecl->getLocation();
1427 
1428  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DebugTemplateAlias) {
1429  auto ArgVector = ::GetTemplateArgs(TD, Ty);
1430  TemplateArgs Args = {TD->getTemplateParameters(), ArgVector};
1431 
1432  // FIXME: Respect DebugTemplateNameKind::Mangled, e.g. by using GetName.
1433  // Note we can't use GetName without additional work: TypeAliasTemplateDecl
1434  // doesn't have instantiation information, so
1435  // TypeAliasTemplateDecl::getNameForDiagnostic wouldn't have access to the
1436  // template args.
1437  std::string Name;
1438  llvm::raw_string_ostream OS(Name);
1439  TD->getNameForDiagnostic(OS, PP, /*Qualified=*/false);
1440  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().getDebugSimpleTemplateNames() !=
1441  llvm::codegenoptions::DebugTemplateNamesKind::Simple ||
1442  !HasReconstitutableArgs(Args.Args))
1443  printTemplateArgumentList(OS, Args.Args, PP);
1444 
1445  llvm::DIDerivedType *AliasTy = DBuilder.createTemplateAlias(
1446  Src, Name, getOrCreateFile(Loc), getLineNumber(Loc),
1447  getDeclContextDescriptor(AliasDecl), CollectTemplateParams(Args, Unit));
1448  return AliasTy;
1449  }
1450 
1451  // Disable PrintCanonicalTypes here because we want
1452  // the DW_AT_name to benefit from the TypePrinter's ability
1453  // to skip defaulted template arguments.
1454  //
1455  // FIXME: Once -gsimple-template-names is enabled by default
1456  // and we attach template parameters to alias template DIEs
1457  // we don't need to worry about customizing the PrintingPolicy
1458  // here anymore.
1459  PP.PrintCanonicalTypes = false;
1460  printTemplateArgumentList(OS, Ty->template_arguments(), PP,
1461  TD->getTemplateParameters());
1462  return DBuilder.createTypedef(Src, OS.str(), getOrCreateFile(Loc),
1463  getLineNumber(Loc),
1464  getDeclContextDescriptor(AliasDecl));
1465 }
1466 
1467 /// Convert an AccessSpecifier into the corresponding DINode flag.
1468 /// As an optimization, return 0 if the access specifier equals the
1469 /// default for the containing type.
1470 static llvm::DINode::DIFlags getAccessFlag(AccessSpecifier Access,
1471  const RecordDecl *RD) {
1472  AccessSpecifier Default = clang::AS_none;
1473  if (RD && RD->isClass())
1474  Default = clang::AS_private;
1475  else if (RD && (RD->isStruct() || RD->isUnion()))
1476  Default = clang::AS_public;
1477 
1478  if (Access == Default)
1479  return llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
1480 
1481  switch (Access) {
1482  case clang::AS_private:
1483  return llvm::DINode::FlagPrivate;
1484  case clang::AS_protected:
1485  return llvm::DINode::FlagProtected;
1486  case clang::AS_public:
1487  return llvm::DINode::FlagPublic;
1488  case clang::AS_none:
1489  return llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
1490  }
1491  llvm_unreachable("unexpected access enumerator");
1492 }
1493 
1494 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const TypedefType *Ty,
1495  llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
1496  llvm::DIType *Underlying =
1497  getOrCreateType(Ty->getDecl()->getUnderlyingType(), Unit);
1498 
1499  if (Ty->getDecl()->hasAttr<NoDebugAttr>() ||
1500  noSystemDebugInfo(Ty->getDecl(), CGM))
1501  return Underlying;
1502 
1503  // We don't set size information, but do specify where the typedef was
1504  // declared.
1505  SourceLocation Loc = Ty->getDecl()->getLocation();
1506 
1507  uint32_t Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(Ty->getDecl(), CGM.getContext());
1508  // Typedefs are derived from some other type.
1509  llvm::DINodeArray Annotations = CollectBTFDeclTagAnnotations(Ty->getDecl());
1510 
1511  llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
1512  const DeclContext *DC = Ty->getDecl()->getDeclContext();
1513  if (isa<RecordDecl>(DC))
1514  Flags = getAccessFlag(Ty->getDecl()->getAccess(), cast<RecordDecl>(DC));
1515 
1516  return DBuilder.createTypedef(Underlying, Ty->getDecl()->getName(),
1517  getOrCreateFile(Loc), getLineNumber(Loc),
1518  getDeclContextDescriptor(Ty->getDecl()), Align,
1519  Flags, Annotations);
1520 }
1521 
1522 static unsigned getDwarfCC(CallingConv CC) {
1523  switch (CC) {
1524  case CC_C:
1525  // Avoid emitting DW_AT_calling_convention if the C convention was used.
1526  return 0;
1527 
1528  case CC_X86StdCall:
1529  return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_BORLAND_stdcall;
1530  case CC_X86FastCall:
1531  return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_BORLAND_msfastcall;
1532  case CC_X86ThisCall:
1533  return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_BORLAND_thiscall;
1534  case CC_X86VectorCall:
1535  return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_vectorcall;
1536  case CC_X86Pascal:
1537  return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_BORLAND_pascal;
1538  case CC_Win64:
1539  return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_Win64;
1540  case CC_X86_64SysV:
1541  return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_X86_64SysV;
1542  case CC_AAPCS:
1543  case CC_AArch64VectorCall:
1544  case CC_AArch64SVEPCS:
1545  return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_AAPCS;
1546  case CC_AAPCS_VFP:
1547  return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_AAPCS_VFP;
1548  case CC_IntelOclBicc:
1549  return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_IntelOclBicc;
1550  case CC_SpirFunction:
1551  return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_SpirFunction;
1552  case CC_OpenCLKernel:
1553  case CC_AMDGPUKernelCall:
1554  return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_OpenCLKernel;
1555  case CC_Swift:
1556  return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_Swift;
1557  case CC_SwiftAsync:
1558  return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_SwiftTail;
1559  case CC_PreserveMost:
1560  return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_PreserveMost;
1561  case CC_PreserveAll:
1562  return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_PreserveAll;
1563  case CC_X86RegCall:
1564  return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_X86RegCall;
1565  case CC_M68kRTD:
1566  return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_M68kRTD;
1567  case CC_PreserveNone:
1568  return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_PreserveNone;
1569  case CC_RISCVVectorCall:
1570  return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_RISCVVectorCall;
1571  }
1572  return 0;
1573 }
1574 
1575 static llvm::DINode::DIFlags getRefFlags(const FunctionProtoType *Func) {
1576  llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
1577  if (Func->getExtProtoInfo().RefQualifier == RQ_LValue)
1578  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagLValueReference;
1579  if (Func->getExtProtoInfo().RefQualifier == RQ_RValue)
1580  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagRValueReference;
1581  return Flags;
1582 }
1583 
1584 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const FunctionType *Ty,
1585  llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
1586  const auto *FPT = dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(Ty);
1587  if (FPT) {
1588  if (llvm::DIType *QTy = CreateQualifiedType(FPT, Unit))
1589  return QTy;
1590  }
1591 
1592  // Create the type without any qualifiers
1593 
1594  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 16> EltTys;
1595 
1596  // Add the result type at least.
1597  EltTys.push_back(getOrCreateType(Ty->getReturnType(), Unit));
1598 
1599  llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
1600  // Set up remainder of arguments if there is a prototype.
1601  // otherwise emit it as a variadic function.
1602  if (!FPT) {
1603  EltTys.push_back(DBuilder.createUnspecifiedParameter());
1604  } else {
1605  Flags = getRefFlags(FPT);
1606  for (const QualType &ParamType : FPT->param_types())
1607  EltTys.push_back(getOrCreateType(ParamType, Unit));
1608  if (FPT->isVariadic())
1609  EltTys.push_back(DBuilder.createUnspecifiedParameter());
1610  }
1611 
1612  llvm::DITypeRefArray EltTypeArray = DBuilder.getOrCreateTypeArray(EltTys);
1613  llvm::DIType *F = DBuilder.createSubroutineType(
1614  EltTypeArray, Flags, getDwarfCC(Ty->getCallConv()));
1615  return F;
1616 }
1617 
1618 llvm::DIDerivedType *
1619 CGDebugInfo::createBitFieldType(const FieldDecl *BitFieldDecl,
1620  llvm::DIScope *RecordTy, const RecordDecl *RD) {
1621  StringRef Name = BitFieldDecl->getName();
1622  QualType Ty = BitFieldDecl->getType();
1623  if (BitFieldDecl->hasAttr<PreferredTypeAttr>())
1624  Ty = BitFieldDecl->getAttr<PreferredTypeAttr>()->getType();
1625  SourceLocation Loc = BitFieldDecl->getLocation();
1626  llvm::DIFile *VUnit = getOrCreateFile(Loc);
1627  llvm::DIType *DebugType = getOrCreateType(Ty, VUnit);
1628 
1629  // Get the location for the field.
1630  llvm::DIFile *File = getOrCreateFile(Loc);
1631  unsigned Line = getLineNumber(Loc);
1632 
1633  const CGBitFieldInfo &BitFieldInfo =
1634  CGM.getTypes().getCGRecordLayout(RD).getBitFieldInfo(BitFieldDecl);
1635  uint64_t SizeInBits = BitFieldInfo.Size;
1636  assert(SizeInBits > 0 && "found named 0-width bitfield");
1637  uint64_t StorageOffsetInBits =
1638  CGM.getContext().toBits(BitFieldInfo.StorageOffset);
1639  uint64_t Offset = BitFieldInfo.Offset;
1640  // The bit offsets for big endian machines are reversed for big
1641  // endian target, compensate for that as the DIDerivedType requires
1642  // un-reversed offsets.
1643  if (CGM.getDataLayout().isBigEndian())
1644  Offset = BitFieldInfo.StorageSize - BitFieldInfo.Size - Offset;
1645  uint64_t OffsetInBits = StorageOffsetInBits + Offset;
1646  llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = getAccessFlag(BitFieldDecl->getAccess(), RD);
1647  llvm::DINodeArray Annotations = CollectBTFDeclTagAnnotations(BitFieldDecl);
1648  return DBuilder.createBitFieldMemberType(
1649  RecordTy, Name, File, Line, SizeInBits, OffsetInBits, StorageOffsetInBits,
1650  Flags, DebugType, Annotations);
1651 }
1652 
1653 llvm::DIDerivedType *CGDebugInfo::createBitFieldSeparatorIfNeeded(
1654  const FieldDecl *BitFieldDecl, const llvm::DIDerivedType *BitFieldDI,
1655  llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Metadata *> PreviousFieldsDI, const RecordDecl *RD) {
1656 
1657  if (!CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().shouldEmitDWARFBitFieldSeparators())
1658  return nullptr;
1659 
1660  /*
1661  Add a *single* zero-bitfield separator between two non-zero bitfields
1662  separated by one or more zero-bitfields. This is used to distinguish between
1663  structures such the ones below, where the memory layout is the same, but how
1664  the ABI assigns fields to registers differs.
1665 
1666  struct foo {
1667  int space[4];
1668  char a : 8; // on amdgpu, passed on v4
1669  char b : 8;
1670  char x : 8;
1671  char y : 8;
1672  };
1673  struct bar {
1674  int space[4];
1675  char a : 8; // on amdgpu, passed on v4
1676  char b : 8;
1677  char : 0;
1678  char x : 8; // passed on v5
1679  char y : 8;
1680  };
1681  */
1682  if (PreviousFieldsDI.empty())
1683  return nullptr;
1684 
1685  // If we already emitted metadata for a 0-length bitfield, nothing to do here.
1686  auto *PreviousMDEntry =
1687  PreviousFieldsDI.empty() ? nullptr : PreviousFieldsDI.back();
1688  auto *PreviousMDField =
1689  dyn_cast_or_null<llvm::DIDerivedType>(PreviousMDEntry);
1690  if (!PreviousMDField || !PreviousMDField->isBitField() ||
1691  PreviousMDField->getSizeInBits() == 0)
1692  return nullptr;
1693 
1694  auto PreviousBitfield = RD->field_begin();
1695  std::advance(PreviousBitfield, BitFieldDecl->getFieldIndex() - 1);
1696 
1697  assert(PreviousBitfield->isBitField());
1698 
1699  ASTContext &Context = CGM.getContext();
1700  if (!PreviousBitfield->isZeroLengthBitField(Context))
1701  return nullptr;
1702 
1703  QualType Ty = PreviousBitfield->getType();
1704  SourceLocation Loc = PreviousBitfield->getLocation();
1705  llvm::DIFile *VUnit = getOrCreateFile(Loc);
1706  llvm::DIType *DebugType = getOrCreateType(Ty, VUnit);
1707  llvm::DIScope *RecordTy = BitFieldDI->getScope();
1708 
1709  llvm::DIFile *File = getOrCreateFile(Loc);
1710  unsigned Line = getLineNumber(Loc);
1711 
1712  uint64_t StorageOffsetInBits =
1713  cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(BitFieldDI->getStorageOffsetInBits())
1714  ->getZExtValue();
1715 
1716  llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags =
1717  getAccessFlag(PreviousBitfield->getAccess(), RD);
1718  llvm::DINodeArray Annotations =
1719  CollectBTFDeclTagAnnotations(*PreviousBitfield);
1720  return DBuilder.createBitFieldMemberType(
1721  RecordTy, "", File, Line, 0, StorageOffsetInBits, StorageOffsetInBits,
1722  Flags, DebugType, Annotations);
1723 }
1724 
1725 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::createFieldType(
1726  StringRef name, QualType type, SourceLocation loc, AccessSpecifier AS,
1727  uint64_t offsetInBits, uint32_t AlignInBits, llvm::DIFile *tunit,
1728  llvm::DIScope *scope, const RecordDecl *RD, llvm::DINodeArray Annotations) {
1729  llvm::DIType *debugType = getOrCreateType(type, tunit);
1730 
1731  // Get the location for the field.
1732  llvm::DIFile *file = getOrCreateFile(loc);
1733  const unsigned line = getLineNumber(loc.isValid() ? loc : CurLoc);
1734 
1735  uint64_t SizeInBits = 0;
1736  auto Align = AlignInBits;
1737  if (!type->isIncompleteArrayType()) {
1738  TypeInfo TI = CGM.getContext().getTypeInfo(type);
1739  SizeInBits = TI.Width;
1740  if (!Align)
1741  Align = getTypeAlignIfRequired(type, CGM.getContext());
1742  }
1743 
1744  llvm::DINode::DIFlags flags = getAccessFlag(AS, RD);
1745  return DBuilder.createMemberType(scope, name, file, line, SizeInBits, Align,
1746  offsetInBits, flags, debugType, Annotations);
1747 }
1748 
1749 void CGDebugInfo::CollectRecordLambdaFields(
1750  const CXXRecordDecl *CXXDecl, SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Metadata *> &elements,
1751  llvm::DIType *RecordTy) {
1752  // For C++11 Lambdas a Field will be the same as a Capture, but the Capture
1753  // has the name and the location of the variable so we should iterate over
1754  // both concurrently.
1755  const ASTRecordLayout &layout = CGM.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(CXXDecl);
1756  RecordDecl::field_iterator Field = CXXDecl->field_begin();
1757  unsigned fieldno = 0;
1758  for (CXXRecordDecl::capture_const_iterator I = CXXDecl->captures_begin(),
1759  E = CXXDecl->captures_end();
1760  I != E; ++I, ++Field, ++fieldno) {
1761  const LambdaCapture &C = *I;
1762  if (C.capturesVariable()) {
1763  SourceLocation Loc = C.getLocation();
1764  assert(!Field->isBitField() && "lambdas don't have bitfield members!");
1765  ValueDecl *V = C.getCapturedVar();
1766  StringRef VName = V->getName();
1767  llvm::DIFile *VUnit = getOrCreateFile(Loc);
1768  auto Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(V, CGM.getContext());
1769  llvm::DIType *FieldType = createFieldType(
1770  VName, Field->getType(), Loc, Field->getAccess(),
1771  layout.getFieldOffset(fieldno), Align, VUnit, RecordTy, CXXDecl);
1772  elements.push_back(FieldType);
1773  } else if (C.capturesThis()) {
1774  // TODO: Need to handle 'this' in some way by probably renaming the
1775  // this of the lambda class and having a field member of 'this' or
1776  // by using AT_object_pointer for the function and having that be
1777  // used as 'this' for semantic references.
1778  FieldDecl *f = *Field;
1779  llvm::DIFile *VUnit = getOrCreateFile(f->getLocation());
1780  QualType type = f->getType();
1781  StringRef ThisName =
1782  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCodeView ? "__this" : "this";
1783  llvm::DIType *fieldType = createFieldType(
1784  ThisName, type, f->getLocation(), f->getAccess(),
1785  layout.getFieldOffset(fieldno), VUnit, RecordTy, CXXDecl);
1786 
1787  elements.push_back(fieldType);
1788  }
1789  }
1790 }
1791 
1792 llvm::DIDerivedType *
1793 CGDebugInfo::CreateRecordStaticField(const VarDecl *Var, llvm::DIType *RecordTy,
1794  const RecordDecl *RD) {
1795  // Create the descriptor for the static variable, with or without
1796  // constant initializers.
1797  Var = Var->getCanonicalDecl();
1798  llvm::DIFile *VUnit = getOrCreateFile(Var->getLocation());
1799  llvm::DIType *VTy = getOrCreateType(Var->getType(), VUnit);
1800 
1801  unsigned LineNumber = getLineNumber(Var->getLocation());
1802  StringRef VName = Var->getName();
1803 
1804  // FIXME: to avoid complications with type merging we should
1805  // emit the constant on the definition instead of the declaration.
1806  llvm::Constant *C = nullptr;
1807  if (Var->getInit()) {
1808  const APValue *Value = Var->evaluateValue();
1809  if (Value) {
1810  if (Value->isInt())
1811  C = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), Value->getInt());
1812  if (Value->isFloat())
1813  C = llvm::ConstantFP::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), Value->getFloat());
1814  }
1815  }
1816 
1817  llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = getAccessFlag(Var->getAccess(), RD);
1818  auto Tag = CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DwarfVersion >= 5
1819  ? llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_variable
1820  : llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_member;
1821  auto Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(Var, CGM.getContext());
1822  llvm::DIDerivedType *GV = DBuilder.createStaticMemberType(
1823  RecordTy, VName, VUnit, LineNumber, VTy, Flags, C, Tag, Align);
1824  StaticDataMemberCache[Var->getCanonicalDecl()].reset(GV);
1825  return GV;
1826 }
1827 
1828 void CGDebugInfo::CollectRecordNormalField(
1829  const FieldDecl *field, uint64_t OffsetInBits, llvm::DIFile *tunit,
1830  SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Metadata *> &elements, llvm::DIType *RecordTy,
1831  const RecordDecl *RD) {
1832  StringRef name = field->getName();
1833  QualType type = field->getType();
1834 
1835  // Ignore unnamed fields unless they're anonymous structs/unions.
1836  if (name.empty() && !type->isRecordType())
1837  return;
1838 
1839  llvm::DIType *FieldType;
1840  if (field->isBitField()) {
1841  llvm::DIDerivedType *BitFieldType;
1842  FieldType = BitFieldType = createBitFieldType(field, RecordTy, RD);
1843  if (llvm::DIType *Separator =
1844  createBitFieldSeparatorIfNeeded(field, BitFieldType, elements, RD))
1845  elements.push_back(Separator);
1846  } else {
1847  auto Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(field, CGM.getContext());
1848  llvm::DINodeArray Annotations = CollectBTFDeclTagAnnotations(field);
1849  FieldType =
1850  createFieldType(name, type, field->getLocation(), field->getAccess(),
1851  OffsetInBits, Align, tunit, RecordTy, RD, Annotations);
1852  }
1853 
1854  elements.push_back(FieldType);
1855 }
1856 
1857 void CGDebugInfo::CollectRecordNestedType(
1858  const TypeDecl *TD, SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Metadata *> &elements) {
1859  QualType Ty = CGM.getContext().getTypeDeclType(TD);
1860  // Injected class names are not considered nested records.
1861  if (isa<InjectedClassNameType>(Ty))
1862  return;
1863  SourceLocation Loc = TD->getLocation();
1864  llvm::DIType *nestedType = getOrCreateType(Ty, getOrCreateFile(Loc));
1865  elements.push_back(nestedType);
1866 }
1867 
1868 void CGDebugInfo::CollectRecordFields(
1869  const RecordDecl *record, llvm::DIFile *tunit,
1870  SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Metadata *> &elements,
1871  llvm::DICompositeType *RecordTy) {
1872  const auto *CXXDecl = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(record);
1873 
1874  if (CXXDecl && CXXDecl->isLambda())
1875  CollectRecordLambdaFields(CXXDecl, elements, RecordTy);
1876  else {
1877  const ASTRecordLayout &layout = CGM.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(record);
1878 
1879  // Field number for non-static fields.
1880  unsigned fieldNo = 0;
1881 
1882  // Static and non-static members should appear in the same order as
1883  // the corresponding declarations in the source program.
1884  for (const auto *I : record->decls())
1885  if (const auto *V = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(I)) {
1886  if (V->hasAttr<NoDebugAttr>() || noSystemDebugInfo(V, CGM))
1887  continue;
1888 
1889  // Skip variable template specializations when emitting CodeView. MSVC
1890  // doesn't emit them.
1891  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCodeView &&
1892  isa<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(V))
1893  continue;
1894 
1895  if (isa<VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(V))
1896  continue;
1897 
1898  // Reuse the existing static member declaration if one exists
1899  auto MI = StaticDataMemberCache.find(V->getCanonicalDecl());
1900  if (MI != StaticDataMemberCache.end()) {
1901  assert(MI->second &&
1902  "Static data member declaration should still exist");
1903  elements.push_back(MI->second);
1904  } else {
1905  auto Field = CreateRecordStaticField(V, RecordTy, record);
1906  elements.push_back(Field);
1907  }
1908  } else if (const auto *field = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(I)) {
1909  CollectRecordNormalField(field, layout.getFieldOffset(fieldNo), tunit,
1910  elements, RecordTy, record);
1911 
1912  // Bump field number for next field.
1913  ++fieldNo;
1914  } else if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCodeView) {
1915  // Debug info for nested types is included in the member list only for
1916  // CodeView.
1917  if (const auto *nestedType = dyn_cast<TypeDecl>(I)) {
1918  // MSVC doesn't generate nested type for anonymous struct/union.
1919  if (isa<RecordDecl>(I) &&
1920  cast<RecordDecl>(I)->isAnonymousStructOrUnion())
1921  continue;
1922  if (!nestedType->isImplicit() &&
1923  nestedType->getDeclContext() == record)
1924  CollectRecordNestedType(nestedType, elements);
1925  }
1926  }
1927  }
1928 }
1929 
1930 llvm::DISubroutineType *
1931 CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateMethodType(const CXXMethodDecl *Method,
1932  llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
1933  const FunctionProtoType *Func = Method->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
1934  if (Method->isStatic())
1935  return cast_or_null<llvm::DISubroutineType>(
1936  getOrCreateType(QualType(Func, 0), Unit));
1937  return getOrCreateInstanceMethodType(Method->getThisType(), Func, Unit);
1938 }
1939 
1940 llvm::DISubroutineType *CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateInstanceMethodType(
1941  QualType ThisPtr, const FunctionProtoType *Func, llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
1942  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI = Func->getExtProtoInfo();
1943  Qualifiers &Qc = EPI.TypeQuals;
1944  Qc.removeConst();
1945  Qc.removeVolatile();
1946  Qc.removeRestrict();
1947  Qc.removeUnaligned();
1948  // Keep the removed qualifiers in sync with
1949  // CreateQualifiedType(const FunctionPrototype*, DIFile *Unit)
1950  // On a 'real' member function type, these qualifiers are carried on the type
1951  // of the first parameter, not as separate DW_TAG_const_type (etc) decorator
1952  // tags around them. (But, in the raw function types with qualifiers, they have
1953  // to use wrapper types.)
1954 
1955  // Add "this" pointer.
1956  const auto *OriginalFunc = cast<llvm::DISubroutineType>(
1957  getOrCreateType(CGM.getContext().getFunctionType(
1958  Func->getReturnType(), Func->getParamTypes(), EPI),
1959  Unit));
1960  llvm::DITypeRefArray Args = OriginalFunc->getTypeArray();
1961  assert(Args.size() && "Invalid number of arguments!");
1962 
1963  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 16> Elts;
1964 
1965  // First element is always return type. For 'void' functions it is NULL.
1966  Elts.push_back(Args[0]);
1967 
1968  // "this" pointer is always first argument.
1969  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = ThisPtr->getPointeeCXXRecordDecl();
1970  if (isa<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RD)) {
1971  // Create pointer type directly in this case.
1972  const PointerType *ThisPtrTy = cast<PointerType>(ThisPtr);
1973  uint64_t Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(ThisPtrTy);
1974  auto Align = getTypeAlignIfRequired(ThisPtrTy, CGM.getContext());
1975  llvm::DIType *PointeeType =
1976  getOrCreateType(ThisPtrTy->getPointeeType(), Unit);
1977  llvm::DIType *ThisPtrType =
1978  DBuilder.createPointerType(PointeeType, Size, Align);
1979  TypeCache[ThisPtr.getAsOpaquePtr()].reset(ThisPtrType);
1980  // TODO: This and the artificial type below are misleading, the
1981  // types aren't artificial the argument is, but the current
1982  // metadata doesn't represent that.
1983  ThisPtrType = DBuilder.createObjectPointerType(ThisPtrType);
1984  Elts.push_back(ThisPtrType);
1985  } else {
1986  llvm::DIType *ThisPtrType = getOrCreateType(ThisPtr, Unit);
1987  TypeCache[ThisPtr.getAsOpaquePtr()].reset(ThisPtrType);
1988  ThisPtrType = DBuilder.createObjectPointerType(ThisPtrType);
1989  Elts.push_back(ThisPtrType);
1990  }
1991 
1992  // Copy rest of the arguments.
1993  for (unsigned i = 1, e = Args.size(); i != e; ++i)
1994  Elts.push_back(Args[i]);
1995 
1996  llvm::DITypeRefArray EltTypeArray = DBuilder.getOrCreateTypeArray(Elts);
1997 
1998  return DBuilder.createSubroutineType(EltTypeArray, OriginalFunc->getFlags(),
1999  getDwarfCC(Func->getCallConv()));
2000 }
2001 
2002 /// isFunctionLocalClass - Return true if CXXRecordDecl is defined
2003 /// inside a function.
2004 static bool isFunctionLocalClass(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
2005  if (const auto *NRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD->getDeclContext()))
2006  return isFunctionLocalClass(NRD);
2007  if (isa<FunctionDecl>(RD->getDeclContext()))
2008  return true;
2009  return false;
2010 }
2011 
2012 llvm::DISubprogram *CGDebugInfo::CreateCXXMemberFunction(
2013  const CXXMethodDecl *Method, llvm::DIFile *Unit, llvm::DIType *RecordTy) {
2014  bool IsCtorOrDtor =
2015  isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(Method) || isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(Method);
2016 
2017  StringRef MethodName = getFunctionName(Method);
2018  llvm::DISubroutineType *MethodTy = getOrCreateMethodType(Method, Unit);
2019 
2020  // Since a single ctor/dtor corresponds to multiple functions, it doesn't
2021  // make sense to give a single ctor/dtor a linkage name.
2022  StringRef MethodLinkageName;
2023  // FIXME: 'isFunctionLocalClass' seems like an arbitrary/unintentional
2024  // property to use here. It may've been intended to model "is non-external
2025  // type" but misses cases of non-function-local but non-external classes such
2026  // as those in anonymous namespaces as well as the reverse - external types
2027  // that are function local, such as those in (non-local) inline functions.
2028  if (!IsCtorOrDtor && !isFunctionLocalClass(Method->getParent()))
2029  MethodLinkageName = CGM.getMangledName(Method);
2030 
2031  // Get the location for the method.
2032  llvm::DIFile *MethodDefUnit = nullptr;
2033  unsigned MethodLine = 0;
2034  if (!Method->isImplicit()) {
2035  MethodDefUnit = getOrCreateFile(Method->getLocation());
2036  MethodLine = getLineNumber(Method->getLocation());
2037  }
2038 
2039  // Collect virtual method info.
2040  llvm::DIType *ContainingType = nullptr;
2041  unsigned VIndex = 0;
2042  llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
2043  llvm::DISubprogram::DISPFlags SPFlags = llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagZero;
2044  int ThisAdjustment = 0;
2045 
2046  if (VTableContextBase::hasVtableSlot(Method)) {
2047  if (Method->isPureVirtual())
2048  SPFlags |= llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagPureVirtual;
2049  else
2050  SPFlags |= llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagVirtual;
2051 
2052  if (CGM.getTarget().getCXXABI().isItaniumFamily()) {
2053  // It doesn't make sense to give a virtual destructor a vtable index,
2054  // since a single destructor has two entries in the vtable.
2055  if (!isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(Method))
2056  VIndex = CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().getMethodVTableIndex(Method);
2057  } else {
2058  // Emit MS ABI vftable information. There is only one entry for the
2059  // deleting dtor.
2060  const auto *DD = dyn_cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(Method);
2061  GlobalDecl GD = DD ? GlobalDecl(DD, Dtor_Deleting) : GlobalDecl(Method);
2062  MethodVFTableLocation ML =
2063  CGM.getMicrosoftVTableContext().getMethodVFTableLocation(GD);
2064  VIndex = ML.Index;
2065 
2066  // CodeView only records the vftable offset in the class that introduces
2067  // the virtual method. This is possible because, unlike Itanium, the MS
2068  // C++ ABI does not include all virtual methods from non-primary bases in
2069  // the vtable for the most derived class. For example, if C inherits from
2070  // A and B, C's primary vftable will not include B's virtual methods.
2071  if (Method->size_overridden_methods() == 0)
2072  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagIntroducedVirtual;
2073 
2074  // The 'this' adjustment accounts for both the virtual and non-virtual
2075  // portions of the adjustment. Presumably the debugger only uses it when
2076  // it knows the dynamic type of an object.
2077  ThisAdjustment = CGM.getCXXABI()
2078  .getVirtualFunctionPrologueThisAdjustment(GD)
2079  .getQuantity();
2080  }
2081  ContainingType = RecordTy;
2082  }
2083 
2084  if (Method->getCanonicalDecl()->isDeleted())
2085  SPFlags |= llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagDeleted;
2086 
2087  if (Method->isNoReturn())
2088  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagNoReturn;
2089 
2090  if (Method->isStatic())
2091  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagStaticMember;
2092  if (Method->isImplicit())
2093  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagArtificial;
2094  Flags |= getAccessFlag(Method->getAccess(), Method->getParent());
2095  if (const auto *CXXC = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(Method)) {
2096  if (CXXC->isExplicit())
2097  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagExplicit;
2098  } else if (const auto *CXXC = dyn_cast<CXXConversionDecl>(Method)) {
2099  if (CXXC->isExplicit())
2100  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagExplicit;
2101  }
2102  if (Method->hasPrototype())
2103  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagPrototyped;
2104  if (Method->getRefQualifier() == RQ_LValue)
2105  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagLValueReference;
2106  if (Method->getRefQualifier() == RQ_RValue)
2107  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagRValueReference;
2108  if (!Method->isExternallyVisible())
2109  SPFlags |= llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagLocalToUnit;
2110  if (CGM.getLangOpts().Optimize)
2111  SPFlags |= llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagOptimized;
2112 
2113  // In this debug mode, emit type info for a class when its constructor type
2114  // info is emitted.
2115  if (DebugKind == llvm::codegenoptions::DebugInfoConstructor)
2116  if (const CXXConstructorDecl *CD = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(Method))
2117  completeUnusedClass(*CD->getParent());
2118 
2119  llvm::DINodeArray TParamsArray = CollectFunctionTemplateParams(Method, Unit);
2120  llvm::DISubprogram *SP = DBuilder.createMethod(
2121  RecordTy, MethodName, MethodLinkageName, MethodDefUnit, MethodLine,
2122  MethodTy, VIndex, ThisAdjustment, ContainingType, Flags, SPFlags,
2123  TParamsArray.get());
2124 
2125  SPCache[Method->getCanonicalDecl()].reset(SP);
2126 
2127  return SP;
2128 }
2129 
2130 void CGDebugInfo::CollectCXXMemberFunctions(
2131  const CXXRecordDecl *RD, llvm::DIFile *Unit,
2132  SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Metadata *> &EltTys, llvm::DIType *RecordTy) {
2133 
2134  // Since we want more than just the individual member decls if we
2135  // have templated functions iterate over every declaration to gather
2136  // the functions.
2137  for (const auto *I : RD->decls()) {
2138  const auto *Method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(I);
2139  // If the member is implicit, don't add it to the member list. This avoids
2140  // the member being added to type units by LLVM, while still allowing it
2141  // to be emitted into the type declaration/reference inside the compile
2142  // unit.
2143  // Ditto 'nodebug' methods, for consistency with CodeGenFunction.cpp.
2144  // FIXME: Handle Using(Shadow?)Decls here to create
2145  // DW_TAG_imported_declarations inside the class for base decls brought into
2146  // derived classes. GDB doesn't seem to notice/leverage these when I tried
2147  // it, so I'm not rushing to fix this. (GCC seems to produce them, if
2148  // referenced)
2149  if (!Method || Method->isImplicit() || Method->hasAttr<NoDebugAttr>() ||
2150  noSystemDebugInfo(Method, CGM))
2151  continue;
2152 
2153  if (Method->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>()->getContainedAutoType())
2154  continue;
2155 
2156  // Reuse the existing member function declaration if it exists.
2157  // It may be associated with the declaration of the type & should be
2158  // reused as we're building the definition.
2159  //
2160  // This situation can arise in the vtable-based debug info reduction where
2161  // implicit members are emitted in a non-vtable TU.
2162  auto MI = SPCache.find(Method->getCanonicalDecl());
2163  EltTys.push_back(MI == SPCache.end()
2164  ? CreateCXXMemberFunction(Method, Unit, RecordTy)
2165  : static_cast<llvm::Metadata *>(MI->second));
2166  }
2167 }
2168 
2169 void CGDebugInfo::CollectCXXBases(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, llvm::DIFile *Unit,
2170  SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Metadata *> &EltTys,
2171  llvm::DIType *RecordTy) {
2172  llvm::DenseSet<CanonicalDeclPtr<const CXXRecordDecl>> SeenTypes;
2173  CollectCXXBasesAux(RD, Unit, EltTys, RecordTy, RD->bases(), SeenTypes,
2174  llvm::DINode::FlagZero);
2175 
2176  // If we are generating CodeView debug info, we also need to emit records for
2177  // indirect virtual base classes.
2178  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCodeView) {
2179  CollectCXXBasesAux(RD, Unit, EltTys, RecordTy, RD->vbases(), SeenTypes,
2180  llvm::DINode::FlagIndirectVirtualBase);
2181  }
2182 }
2183 
2184 void CGDebugInfo::CollectCXXBasesAux(
2185  const CXXRecordDecl *RD, llvm::DIFile *Unit,
2186  SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Metadata *> &EltTys, llvm::DIType *RecordTy,
2187  const CXXRecordDecl::base_class_const_range &Bases,
2188  llvm::DenseSet<CanonicalDeclPtr<const CXXRecordDecl>> &SeenTypes,
2189  llvm::DINode::DIFlags StartingFlags) {
2190  const ASTRecordLayout &RL = CGM.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
2191  for (const auto &BI : Bases) {
2192  const auto *Base =
2193  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(BI.getType()->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
2194  if (!SeenTypes.insert(Base).second)
2195  continue;
2196  auto *BaseTy = getOrCreateType(BI.getType(), Unit);
2197  llvm::DINode::DIFlags BFlags = StartingFlags;
2198  uint64_t BaseOffset;
2199  uint32_t VBPtrOffset = 0;
2200 
2201  if (BI.isVirtual()) {
2202  if (CGM.getTarget().getCXXABI().isItaniumFamily()) {
2203  // virtual base offset offset is -ve. The code generator emits dwarf
2204  // expression where it expects +ve number.
2205  BaseOffset = 0 - CGM.getItaniumVTableContext()
2206  .getVirtualBaseOffsetOffset(RD, Base)
2207  .getQuantity();
2208  } else {
2209  // In the MS ABI, store the vbtable offset, which is analogous to the
2210  // vbase offset offset in Itanium.
2211  BaseOffset =
2212  4 * CGM.getMicrosoftVTableContext().getVBTableIndex(RD, Base);
2213  VBPtrOffset = CGM.getContext()
2214  .getASTRecordLayout(RD)
2215  .getVBPtrOffset()
2216  .getQuantity();
2217  }
2218  BFlags |= llvm::DINode::FlagVirtual;
2219  } else
2220  BaseOffset = CGM.getContext().toBits(RL.getBaseClassOffset(Base));
2221  // FIXME: Inconsistent units for BaseOffset. It is in bytes when
2222  // BI->isVirtual() and bits when not.
2223 
2224  BFlags |= getAccessFlag(BI.getAccessSpecifier(), RD);
2225  llvm::DIType *DTy = DBuilder.createInheritance(RecordTy, BaseTy, BaseOffset,
2226  VBPtrOffset, BFlags);
2227  EltTys.push_back(DTy);
2228  }
2229 }
2230 
2231 llvm::DINodeArray
2232 CGDebugInfo::CollectTemplateParams(std::optional<TemplateArgs> OArgs,
2233  llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
2234  if (!OArgs)
2235  return llvm::DINodeArray();
2236  TemplateArgs &Args = *OArgs;
2237  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 16> TemplateParams;
2238  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Args.Args.size(); i != e; ++i) {
2239  const TemplateArgument &TA = Args.Args[i];
2240  StringRef Name;
2241  const bool defaultParameter = TA.getIsDefaulted();
2242  if (Args.TList)
2243  Name = Args.TList->getParam(i)->getName();
2244 
2245  switch (TA.getKind()) {
2246  case TemplateArgument::Type: {
2247  llvm::DIType *TTy = getOrCreateType(TA.getAsType(), Unit);
2248  TemplateParams.push_back(DBuilder.createTemplateTypeParameter(
2249  TheCU, Name, TTy, defaultParameter));
2250 
2251  } break;
2252  case TemplateArgument::Integral: {
2253  llvm::DIType *TTy = getOrCreateType(TA.getIntegralType(), Unit);
2254  TemplateParams.push_back(DBuilder.createTemplateValueParameter(
2255  TheCU, Name, TTy, defaultParameter,
2256  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), TA.getAsIntegral())));
2257  } break;
2258  case TemplateArgument::Declaration: {
2259  const ValueDecl *D = TA.getAsDecl();
2260  QualType T = TA.getParamTypeForDecl().getDesugaredType(CGM.getContext());
2261  llvm::DIType *TTy = getOrCreateType(T, Unit);
2262  llvm::Constant *V = nullptr;
2263  // Skip retrieve the value if that template parameter has cuda device
2264  // attribute, i.e. that value is not available at the host side.
2265  if (!CGM.getLangOpts().CUDA || CGM.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice ||
2266  !D->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>()) {
2267  // Variable pointer template parameters have a value that is the address
2268  // of the variable.
2269  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D))
2270  V = CGM.GetAddrOfGlobalVar(VD);
2271  // Member function pointers have special support for building them,
2272  // though this is currently unsupported in LLVM CodeGen.
2273  else if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(D);
2274  MD && MD->isImplicitObjectMemberFunction())
2275  V = CGM.getCXXABI().EmitMemberFunctionPointer(MD);
2276  else if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D))
2277  V = CGM.GetAddrOfFunction(FD);
2278  // Member data pointers have special handling too to compute the fixed
2279  // offset within the object.
2280  else if (const auto *MPT =
2281  dyn_cast<MemberPointerType>(T.getTypePtr())) {
2282  // These five lines (& possibly the above member function pointer
2283  // handling) might be able to be refactored to use similar code in
2284  // CodeGenModule::getMemberPointerConstant
2285  uint64_t fieldOffset = CGM.getContext().getFieldOffset(D);
2286  CharUnits chars =
2287  CGM.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits((int64_t)fieldOffset);
2288  V = CGM.getCXXABI().EmitMemberDataPointer(MPT, chars);
2289  } else if (const auto *GD = dyn_cast<MSGuidDecl>(D)) {
2290  V = CGM.GetAddrOfMSGuidDecl(GD).getPointer();
2291  } else if (const auto *TPO = dyn_cast<TemplateParamObjectDecl>(D)) {
2292  if (T->isRecordType())
2293  V = ConstantEmitter(CGM).emitAbstract(
2294  SourceLocation(), TPO->getValue(), TPO->getType());
2295  else
2296  V = CGM.GetAddrOfTemplateParamObject(TPO).getPointer();
2297  }
2298  assert(V && "Failed to find template parameter pointer");
2299  V = V->stripPointerCasts();
2300  }
2301  TemplateParams.push_back(DBuilder.createTemplateValueParameter(
2302  TheCU, Name, TTy, defaultParameter, cast_or_null<llvm::Constant>(V)));
2303  } break;
2304  case TemplateArgument::NullPtr: {
2305  QualType T = TA.getNullPtrType();
2306  llvm::DIType *TTy = getOrCreateType(T, Unit);
2307  llvm::Constant *V = nullptr;
2308  // Special case member data pointer null values since they're actually -1
2309  // instead of zero.
2310  if (const auto *MPT = dyn_cast<MemberPointerType>(T.getTypePtr()))
2311  // But treat member function pointers as simple zero integers because
2312  // it's easier than having a special case in LLVM's CodeGen. If LLVM
2313  // CodeGen grows handling for values of non-null member function
2314  // pointers then perhaps we could remove this special case and rely on
2315  // EmitNullMemberPointer for member function pointers.
2316  if (MPT->isMemberDataPointer())
2317  V = CGM.getCXXABI().EmitNullMemberPointer(MPT);
2318  if (!V)
2319  V = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int8Ty, 0);
2320  TemplateParams.push_back(DBuilder.createTemplateValueParameter(
2321  TheCU, Name, TTy, defaultParameter, V));
2322  } break;
2323  case TemplateArgument::StructuralValue: {
2324  QualType T = TA.getStructuralValueType();
2325  llvm::DIType *TTy = getOrCreateType(T, Unit);
2326  llvm::Constant *V = ConstantEmitter(CGM).emitAbstract(
2327  SourceLocation(), TA.getAsStructuralValue(), T);
2328  TemplateParams.push_back(DBuilder.createTemplateValueParameter(
2329  TheCU, Name, TTy, defaultParameter, V));
2330  } break;
2331  case TemplateArgument::Template: {
2332  std::string QualName;
2333  llvm::raw_string_ostream OS(QualName);
2334  TA.getAsTemplate().getAsTemplateDecl()->printQualifiedName(
2335  OS, getPrintingPolicy());
2336  TemplateParams.push_back(DBuilder.createTemplateTemplateParameter(
2337  TheCU, Name, nullptr, OS.str(), defaultParameter));
2338  break;
2339  }
2340  case TemplateArgument::Pack:
2341  TemplateParams.push_back(DBuilder.createTemplateParameterPack(
2342  TheCU, Name, nullptr,
2343  CollectTemplateParams({{nullptr, TA.getPackAsArray()}}, Unit)));
2344  break;
2345  case TemplateArgument::Expression: {
2346  const Expr *E = TA.getAsExpr();
2347  QualType T = E->getType();
2348  if (E->isGLValue())
2349  T = CGM.getContext().getLValueReferenceType(T);
2350  llvm::Constant *V = ConstantEmitter(CGM).emitAbstract(E, T);
2351  assert(V && "Expression in template argument isn't constant");
2352  llvm::DIType *TTy = getOrCreateType(T, Unit);
2353  TemplateParams.push_back(DBuilder.createTemplateValueParameter(
2354  TheCU, Name, TTy, defaultParameter, V->stripPointerCasts()));
2355  } break;
2356  // And the following should never occur:
2357  case TemplateArgument::TemplateExpansion:
2358  case TemplateArgument::Null:
2359  llvm_unreachable(
2360  "These argument types shouldn't exist in concrete types");
2361  }
2362  }
2363  return DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(TemplateParams);
2364 }

2366 std::optional<CGDebugInfo::TemplateArgs>
2367 CGDebugInfo::GetTemplateArgs(const FunctionDecl *FD) const {
2368  if (FD->getTemplatedKind() ==
2369  FunctionDecl::TK_FunctionTemplateSpecialization) {
2370  const TemplateParameterList *TList = FD->getTemplateSpecializationInfo()
2371  ->getTemplate()
2372  ->getTemplateParameters();
2373  return {{TList, FD->getTemplateSpecializationArgs()->asArray()}};
2374  }
2375  return std::nullopt;
2376 }
2377 std::optional<CGDebugInfo::TemplateArgs>
2378 CGDebugInfo::GetTemplateArgs(const VarDecl *VD) const {
2379  // Always get the full list of parameters, not just the ones from the
2380  // specialization. A partial specialization may have fewer parameters than
2381  // there are arguments.
2382  auto *TS = dyn_cast<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(VD);
2383  if (!TS)
2384  return std::nullopt;
2385  VarTemplateDecl *T = TS->getSpecializedTemplate();
2386  const TemplateParameterList *TList = T->getTemplateParameters();
2387  auto TA = TS->getTemplateArgs().asArray();
2388  return {{TList, TA}};
2389 }
2390 std::optional<CGDebugInfo::TemplateArgs>
2391 CGDebugInfo::GetTemplateArgs(const RecordDecl *RD) const {
2392  if (auto *TSpecial = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RD)) {
2393  // Always get the full list of parameters, not just the ones from the
2394  // specialization. A partial specialization may have fewer parameters than
2395  // there are arguments.
2396  TemplateParameterList *TPList =
2397  TSpecial->getSpecializedTemplate()->getTemplateParameters();
2398  const TemplateArgumentList &TAList = TSpecial->getTemplateArgs();
2399  return {{TPList, TAList.asArray()}};
2400  }
2401  return std::nullopt;
2402 }

2428  llvm::MDString::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), I->getBTFDeclTag())};

2430  }

2434 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateVTablePtrType(llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
2435  if (VTablePtrType)
2436  return VTablePtrType;
2437 
2438  ASTContext &Context = CGM.getContext();
2439 
2440  /* Function type */
2441  llvm::Metadata *STy = getOrCreateType(Context.IntTy, Unit);
2442  llvm::DITypeRefArray SElements = DBuilder.getOrCreateTypeArray(STy);
2443  llvm::DIType *SubTy = DBuilder.createSubroutineType(SElements);
2444  unsigned Size = Context.getTypeSize(Context.VoidPtrTy);
2445  unsigned VtblPtrAddressSpace = CGM.getTarget().getVtblPtrAddressSpace();
2446  std::optional<unsigned> DWARFAddressSpace =
2447  CGM.getTarget().getDWARFAddressSpace(VtblPtrAddressSpace);
2448 
2449  llvm::DIType *vtbl_ptr_type = DBuilder.createPointerType(
2450  SubTy, Size, 0, DWARFAddressSpace, "__vtbl_ptr_type");
2451  VTablePtrType = DBuilder.createPointerType(vtbl_ptr_type, Size);
2452  return VTablePtrType;
2453 }

2459 
2460 StringRef CGDebugInfo::getDynamicInitializerName(const VarDecl *VD,
2461  DynamicInitKind StubKind,
2462  llvm::Function *InitFn) {
2463  // If we're not emitting codeview, use the mangled name. For Itanium, this is
2464  // arbitrary.
2465  if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCodeView ||
2466  StubKind == DynamicInitKind::GlobalArrayDestructor)
2467  return InitFn->getName();
2468 
2469  // Print the normal qualified name for the variable, then break off the last
2470  // NNS, and add the appropriate other text. Clang always prints the global
2471  // variable name without template arguments, so we can use rsplit("::") and
2472  // then recombine the pieces.
2473  SmallString<128> QualifiedGV;
2474  StringRef Quals;
2475  StringRef GVName;
2476  {
2477  llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(QualifiedGV);
2478  VD->printQualifiedName(OS, getPrintingPolicy());
2479  std::tie(Quals, GVName) = OS.str().rsplit("::");
2480  if (GVName.empty())
2481  std::swap(Quals, GVName);
2482  }
2483 
2484  SmallString<128> InitName;
2485  llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(InitName);
2486  if (!Quals.empty())
2487  OS << Quals << "::";
2488 
2489  switch (StubKind) {
2490  case DynamicInitKind::NoStub:
2491  case DynamicInitKind::GlobalArrayDestructor:
2492  llvm_unreachable("not an initializer");
2493  case DynamicInitKind::Initializer:
2494  OS << "`dynamic initializer for '";
2495  break;
2496  case DynamicInitKind::AtExit:
2497  OS << "`dynamic atexit destructor for '";
2498  break;
2499  }
2500 
2501  OS << GVName;
2502 
2503  // Add any template specialization args.
2504  if (const auto *VTpl = dyn_cast<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(VD)) {
2505  printTemplateArgumentList(OS, VTpl->getTemplateArgs().asArray(),
2506  getPrintingPolicy());
2507  }
2508 
2509  OS << '\'';
2510 
2511  return internString(OS.str());
2512 }
2513 
2514 void CGDebugInfo::CollectVTableInfo(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, llvm::DIFile *Unit,
2515  SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Metadata *> &EltTys) {
2516  // If this class is not dynamic then there is not any vtable info to collect.
2517  if (!RD->isDynamicClass())
2518  return;
2519 
2520  // Don't emit any vtable shape or vptr info if this class doesn't have an
2521  // extendable vfptr. This can happen if the class doesn't have virtual
2522  // methods, or in the MS ABI if those virtual methods only come from virtually
2523  // inherited bases.
2524  const ASTRecordLayout &RL = CGM.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
2525  if (!RL.hasExtendableVFPtr())
2526  return;
2527 
2528  // CodeView needs to know how large the vtable of every dynamic class is, so
2529  // emit a special named pointer type into the element list. The vptr type
2530  // points to this type as well.
2531  llvm::DIType *VPtrTy = nullptr;
2532  bool NeedVTableShape = CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCodeView &&
2533  CGM.getTarget().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft();
2534  if (NeedVTableShape) {
2535  uint64_t PtrWidth =
2536  CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(CGM.getContext().VoidPtrTy);
2537  const VTableLayout &VFTLayout =
2538  CGM.getMicrosoftVTableContext().getVFTableLayout(RD, CharUnits::Zero());
2539  unsigned VSlotCount =
2540  VFTLayout.vtable_components().size() - CGM.getLangOpts().RTTIData;
2541  unsigned VTableWidth = PtrWidth * VSlotCount;
2542  unsigned VtblPtrAddressSpace = CGM.getTarget().getVtblPtrAddressSpace();
2543  std::optional<unsigned> DWARFAddressSpace =
2544  CGM.getTarget().getDWARFAddressSpace(VtblPtrAddressSpace);
2545 
2546  // Create a very wide void* type and insert it directly in the element list.
2547  llvm::DIType *VTableType = DBuilder.createPointerType(
2548  nullptr, VTableWidth, 0, DWARFAddressSpace, "__vtbl_ptr_type");
2549  EltTys.push_back(VTableType);
2550 
2551  // The vptr is a pointer to this special vtable type.
2552  VPtrTy = DBuilder.createPointerType(VTableType, PtrWidth);
2553  }
2554 
2555  // If there is a primary base then the artificial vptr member lives there.
2556  if (RL.getPrimaryBase())
2557  return;
2558 
2559  if (!VPtrTy)
2560  VPtrTy = getOrCreateVTablePtrType(Unit);
2561 
2562  unsigned Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(CGM.getContext().VoidPtrTy);
2563  llvm::DIType *VPtrMember =
2564  DBuilder.createMemberType(Unit, getVTableName(RD), Unit, 0, Size, 0, 0,
2565  llvm::DINode::FlagArtificial, VPtrTy);
2566  EltTys.push_back(VPtrMember);
2567 }

2592 void CGDebugInfo::addHeapAllocSiteMetadata(llvm::CallBase *CI,
2593  QualType AllocatedTy,
2594  SourceLocation Loc) {

2596  llvm::codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly)

2599  if (AllocatedTy->isVoidType())
2600  node = llvm::MDNode::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), std::nullopt);

2602  node = getOrCreateType(AllocatedTy, getOrCreateFile(Loc));

2607 void CGDebugInfo::completeType(const EnumDecl *ED) {
2608  if (DebugKind <= llvm::codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly)
2609  return;
2610  QualType Ty = CGM.getContext().getEnumType(ED);
2611  void *TyPtr = Ty.getAsOpaquePtr();
2612  auto I = TypeCache.find(TyPtr);
2613  if (I == TypeCache.end() || !cast<llvm::DIType>(I->second)->isForwardDecl())
2614  return;
2615  llvm::DIType *Res = CreateTypeDefinition(Ty->castAs<EnumType>());
2616  assert(!Res->isForwardDecl());
2617  TypeCache[TyPtr].reset(Res);
2618 }

2626 /// Return true if the class or any of its methods are marked dllimport.
2627 static bool isClassOrMethodDLLImport(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
2628  if (RD->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>())
2629  return true;
2630  for (const CXXMethodDecl *MD : RD->methods())
2631  if (MD->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>())
2632  return true;
2633  return false;
2634 }
2635 
2636 /// Does a type definition exist in an imported clang module?
2637 static bool isDefinedInClangModule(const RecordDecl *RD) {
2638  // Only definitions that where imported from an AST file come from a module.
2639  if (!RD || !RD->isFromASTFile())
2640  return false;
2641  // Anonymous entities cannot be addressed. Treat them as not from module.
2642  if (!RD->isExternallyVisible() && RD->getName().empty())
2643  return false;
2644  if (auto *CXXDecl = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD)) {
2645  if (!CXXDecl->isCompleteDefinition())
2646  return false;
2647  // Check wether RD is a template.
2648  auto TemplateKind = CXXDecl->getTemplateSpecializationKind();
2649  if (TemplateKind != TSK_Undeclared) {
2650  // Unfortunately getOwningModule() isn't accurate enough to find the
2651  // owning module of a ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl that is inside a
2652  // namespace spanning multiple modules.
2653  bool Explicit = false;
2654  if (auto *TD = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(CXXDecl))
2655  Explicit = TD->isExplicitInstantiationOrSpecialization();
2656  if (!Explicit && CXXDecl->getEnclosingNamespaceContext())
2657  return false;
2658  // This is a template, check the origin of the first member.
2659  if (CXXDecl->field_begin() == CXXDecl->field_end())
2660  return TemplateKind == TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDeclaration;
2661  if (!CXXDecl->field_begin()->isFromASTFile())
2662  return false;
2663  }
2664  }
2665  return true;
2666 }
2667 
2668 void CGDebugInfo::completeClassData(const RecordDecl *RD) {
2669  if (auto *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD))
2670  if (CXXRD->isDynamicClass() &&
2671  CGM.getVTableLinkage(CXXRD) ==
2672  llvm::GlobalValue::AvailableExternallyLinkage &&
2673  !isClassOrMethodDLLImport(CXXRD))
2674  return;
2675 
2676  if (DebugTypeExtRefs && isDefinedInClangModule(RD->getDefinition()))
2677  return;
2678 
2679  completeClass(RD);
2680 }
2681 
2682 void CGDebugInfo::completeClass(const RecordDecl *RD) {
2683  if (DebugKind <= llvm::codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly)
2684  return;
2685  QualType Ty = CGM.getContext().getRecordType(RD);
2686  void *TyPtr = Ty.getAsOpaquePtr();
2687  auto I = TypeCache.find(TyPtr);
2688  if (I != TypeCache.end() && !cast<llvm::DIType>(I->second)->isForwardDecl())
2689  return;
2690 
2691  // We want the canonical definition of the structure to not
2692  // be the typedef. Since that would lead to circular typedef
2693  // metadata.
2694  auto [Res, PrefRes] = CreateTypeDefinition(Ty->castAs<RecordType>());
2695  assert(!Res->isForwardDecl());
2696  TypeCache[TyPtr].reset(Res);
2697 }
2698 
2699 static bool hasExplicitMemberDefinition(CXXRecordDecl::method_iterator I,
2700  CXXRecordDecl::method_iterator End) {
2701  for (CXXMethodDecl *MD : llvm::make_range(I, End))
2702  if (FunctionDecl *Tmpl = MD->getInstantiatedFromMemberFunction())
2703  if (!Tmpl->isImplicit() && Tmpl->isThisDeclarationADefinition() &&
2704  !MD->getMemberSpecializationInfo()->isExplicitSpecialization())
2705  return true;
2706  return false;
2707 }
2708 
2709 static bool canUseCtorHoming(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
2710  // Constructor homing can be used for classes that cannnot be constructed
2711  // without emitting code for one of their constructors. This is classes that
2712  // don't have trivial or constexpr constructors, or can be created from
2713  // aggregate initialization. Also skip lambda objects because they don't call
2714  // constructors.
2715 
2716  // Skip this optimization if the class or any of its methods are marked
2717  // dllimport.
2718  if (isClassOrMethodDLLImport(RD))
2719  return false;
2720 
2721  if (RD->isLambda() || RD->isAggregate() ||
2722  RD->hasTrivialDefaultConstructor() ||
2723  RD->hasConstexprNonCopyMoveConstructor())
2724  return false;
2725 
2726  for (const CXXConstructorDecl *Ctor : RD->ctors()) {
2727  if (Ctor->isCopyOrMoveConstructor())
2728  continue;
2729  if (!Ctor->isDeleted())
2730  return true;
2731  }
2732  return false;
2733 }
2734 
2735 static bool shouldOmitDefinition(llvm::codegenoptions::DebugInfoKind DebugKind,
2736  bool DebugTypeExtRefs, const RecordDecl *RD,
2737  const LangOptions &LangOpts) {
2738  if (DebugTypeExtRefs && isDefinedInClangModule(RD->getDefinition()))
2739  return true;
2740 
2741  if (auto *ES = RD->getASTContext().getExternalSource())
2742  if (ES->hasExternalDefinitions(RD) == ExternalASTSource::EK_Always)
2743  return true;
2744 
2745  // Only emit forward declarations in line tables only to keep debug info size
2746  // small. This only applies to CodeView, since we don't emit types in DWARF
2747  // line tables only.
2748  if (DebugKind == llvm::codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly)
2749  return true;
2750 
2751  if (DebugKind > llvm::codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo ||
2752  RD->hasAttr<StandaloneDebugAttr>())
2753  return false;
2754 
2755  if (!LangOpts.CPlusPlus)
2756  return false;
2757 
2758  if (!RD->isCompleteDefinitionRequired())
2759  return true;
2760 
2761  const auto *CXXDecl = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD);
2762 
2763  if (!CXXDecl)
2764  return false;
2765 
2766  // Only emit complete debug info for a dynamic class when its vtable is
2767  // emitted. However, Microsoft debuggers don't resolve type information
2768  // across DLL boundaries, so skip this optimization if the class or any of its
2769  // methods are marked dllimport. This isn't a complete solution, since objects
2770  // without any dllimport methods can be used in one DLL and constructed in
2771  // another, but it is the current behavior of LimitedDebugInfo.
2772  if (CXXDecl->hasDefinition() && CXXDecl->isDynamicClass() &&
2773  !isClassOrMethodDLLImport(CXXDecl))
2774  return true;
2775 
2776  TemplateSpecializationKind Spec = TSK_Undeclared;
2777  if (const auto *SD = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RD))
2778  Spec = SD->getSpecializationKind();
2779 
2780  if (Spec == TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDeclaration &&
2781  hasExplicitMemberDefinition(CXXDecl->method_begin(),
2782  CXXDecl->method_end()))
2783  return true;
2784 
2785  // In constructor homing mode, only emit complete debug info for a class
2786  // when its constructor is emitted.
2787  if ((DebugKind == llvm::codegenoptions::DebugInfoConstructor) &&
2788  canUseCtorHoming(CXXDecl))
2789  return true;
2790 
2791  return false;
2792 }
2793 
2794 void CGDebugInfo::completeRequiredType(const RecordDecl *RD) {
2795  if (shouldOmitDefinition(DebugKind, DebugTypeExtRefs, RD, CGM.getLangOpts()))
2796  return;
2797 
2798  QualType Ty = CGM.getContext().getRecordType(RD);
2799  llvm::DIType *T = getTypeOrNull(Ty);
2800  if (T && T->isForwardDecl())
2801  completeClassData(RD);
2802 }
2803 
2804 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const RecordType *Ty) {
2805  RecordDecl *RD = Ty->getDecl();
2806  llvm::DIType *T = cast_or_null<llvm::DIType>(getTypeOrNull(QualType(Ty, 0)));
2807  if (T || shouldOmitDefinition(DebugKind, DebugTypeExtRefs, RD,
2808  CGM.getLangOpts())) {
2809  if (!T)
2810  T = getOrCreateRecordFwdDecl(Ty, getDeclContextDescriptor(RD));
2811  return T;
2812  }
2813 
2814  auto [Def, Pref] = CreateTypeDefinition(Ty);
2815 
2816  return Pref ? Pref : Def;
2817 }

2819 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::GetPreferredNameType(const CXXRecordDecl *RD,
2820  llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
2821  if (!RD)
2822  return nullptr;
2823 
2824  auto const *PNA = RD->getAttr<PreferredNameAttr>();
2825  if (!PNA)
2826  return nullptr;
2827 
2828  return getOrCreateType(PNA->getTypedefType(), Unit);
2829 }
2830 
2831 std::pair<llvm::DIType *, llvm::DIType *>
2832 CGDebugInfo::CreateTypeDefinition(const RecordType *Ty) {
2833  RecordDecl *RD = Ty->getDecl();
2834 
2835  // Get overall information about the record type for the debug info.
2836  llvm::DIFile *DefUnit = getOrCreateFile(RD->getLocation());
2837 
2838  // Records and classes and unions can all be recursive. To handle them, we
2839  // first generate a debug descriptor for the struct as a forward declaration.
2840  // Then (if it is a definition) we go through and get debug info for all of
2841  // its members. Finally, we create a descriptor for the complete type (which
2842  // may refer to the forward decl if the struct is recursive) and replace all
2843  // uses of the forward declaration with the final definition.
2844  llvm::DICompositeType *FwdDecl = getOrCreateLimitedType(Ty);
2845 
2846  const RecordDecl *D = RD->getDefinition();
2847  if (!D || !D->isCompleteDefinition())
2848  return {FwdDecl, nullptr};
2849 
2850  if (const auto *CXXDecl = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD))
2851  CollectContainingType(CXXDecl, FwdDecl);
2852 
2853  // Push the struct on region stack.
2854  LexicalBlockStack.emplace_back(&*FwdDecl);
2855  RegionMap[Ty->getDecl()].reset(FwdDecl);
2856 
2857  // Convert all the elements.
2858  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 16> EltTys;
2859  // what about nested types?
2860 
2861  // Note: The split of CXXDecl information here is intentional, the
2862  // gdb tests will depend on a certain ordering at printout. The debug
2863  // information offsets are still correct if we merge them all together
2864  // though.
2865  const auto *CXXDecl = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD);
2866  if (CXXDecl) {
2867  CollectCXXBases(CXXDecl, DefUnit, EltTys, FwdDecl);
2868  CollectVTableInfo(CXXDecl, DefUnit, EltTys);
2869  }
2870 
2871  // Collect data fields (including static variables and any initializers).
2872  CollectRecordFields(RD, DefUnit, EltTys, FwdDecl);
2873  if (CXXDecl)
2874  CollectCXXMemberFunctions(CXXDecl, DefUnit, EltTys, FwdDecl);
2875 
2876  LexicalBlockStack.pop_back();
2877  RegionMap.erase(Ty->getDecl());
2878 
2879  llvm::DINodeArray Elements = DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(EltTys);
2880  DBuilder.replaceArrays(FwdDecl, Elements);
2881 
2882  if (FwdDecl->isTemporary())
2883  FwdDecl =
2884  llvm::MDNode::replaceWithPermanent(llvm::TempDICompositeType(FwdDecl));
2885 
2886  RegionMap[Ty->getDecl()].reset(FwdDecl);
2887 
2888  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().getDebuggerTuning() == llvm::DebuggerKind::LLDB)
2889  if (auto *PrefDI = GetPreferredNameType(CXXDecl, DefUnit))
2890  return {FwdDecl, PrefDI};
2891 
2892  return {FwdDecl, nullptr};
2893 }
2894 
2895 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const ObjCObjectType *Ty,
2896  llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
2897  // Ignore protocols.
2898  return getOrCreateType(Ty->getBaseType(), Unit);
2899 }

2901 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const ObjCTypeParamType *Ty,
2902  llvm::DIFile *Unit) {

2913 /// \return true if Getter has the default name for the property PD.
2914 static bool hasDefaultGetterName(const ObjCPropertyDecl *PD,
2915  const ObjCMethodDecl *Getter) {
2916  assert(PD);
2917  if (!Getter)
2918  return true;
2919 
2920  assert(Getter->getDeclName().isObjCZeroArgSelector());
2921  return PD->getName() ==
2922  Getter->getDeclName().getObjCSelector().getNameForSlot(0);
2923 }
2924 
2925 /// \return true if Setter has the default name for the property PD.
2926 static bool hasDefaultSetterName(const ObjCPropertyDecl *PD,
2927  const ObjCMethodDecl *Setter) {
2928  assert(PD);
2929  if (!Setter)
2930  return true;
2931 
2932  assert(Setter->getDeclName().isObjCOneArgSelector());
2933  return SelectorTable::constructSetterName(PD->getName()) ==
2934  Setter->getDeclName().getObjCSelector().getNameForSlot(0);
2935 }
