2937 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const ObjCInterfaceType *Ty,
2938  llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
2939  ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID = Ty->getDecl();
2940  if (!ID)
2941  return nullptr;
2942 
2943  // Return a forward declaration if this type was imported from a clang module,
2944  // and this is not the compile unit with the implementation of the type (which
2945  // may contain hidden ivars).
2946  if (DebugTypeExtRefs && ID->isFromASTFile() && ID->getDefinition() &&
2947  !ID->getImplementation())
2948  return DBuilder.createForwardDecl(llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_structure_type,
2949  ID->getName(),
2950  getDeclContextDescriptor(ID), Unit, 0);
2951 
2952  // Get overall information about the record type for the debug info.
2953  llvm::DIFile *DefUnit = getOrCreateFile(ID->getLocation());
2954  unsigned Line = getLineNumber(ID->getLocation());
2955  auto RuntimeLang =
2956  static_cast<llvm::dwarf::SourceLanguage>(TheCU->getSourceLanguage());
2957 
2958  // If this is just a forward declaration return a special forward-declaration
2959  // debug type since we won't be able to lay out the entire type.
2960  ObjCInterfaceDecl *Def = ID->getDefinition();
2961  if (!Def || !Def->getImplementation()) {
2962  llvm::DIScope *Mod = getParentModuleOrNull(ID);
2963  llvm::DIType *FwdDecl = DBuilder.createReplaceableCompositeType(
2964  llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_structure_type, ID->getName(), Mod ? Mod : TheCU,
2965  DefUnit, Line, RuntimeLang);
2966  ObjCInterfaceCache.push_back(ObjCInterfaceCacheEntry(Ty, FwdDecl, Unit));
2967  return FwdDecl;
2968  }
2969 
2970  return CreateTypeDefinition(Ty, Unit);
2971 }
2972 
2973 llvm::DIModule *CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateModuleRef(ASTSourceDescriptor Mod,
2974  bool CreateSkeletonCU) {
2975  // Use the Module pointer as the key into the cache. This is a
2976  // nullptr if the "Module" is a PCH, which is safe because we don't
2977  // support chained PCH debug info, so there can only be a single PCH.
2978  const Module *M = Mod.getModuleOrNull();
2979  auto ModRef = ModuleCache.find(M);
2980  if (ModRef != ModuleCache.end())
2981  return cast<llvm::DIModule>(ModRef->second);
2982 
2983  // Macro definitions that were defined with "-D" on the command line.
2984  SmallString<128> ConfigMacros;
2985  {
2986  llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(ConfigMacros);
2987  const auto &PPOpts = CGM.getPreprocessorOpts();
2988  unsigned I = 0;
2989  // Translate the macro definitions back into a command line.
2990  for (auto &M : PPOpts.Macros) {
2991  if (++I > 1)
2992  OS << " ";
2993  const std::string &Macro = M.first;
2994  bool Undef = M.second;
2995  OS << "\"-" << (Undef ? 'U' : 'D');
2996  for (char c : Macro)
2997  switch (c) {
2998  case '\\':
2999  OS << "\\\\";
3000  break;
3001  case '"':
3002  OS << "\\\"";
3003  break;
3004  default:
3005  OS << c;
3006  }
3007  OS << '\"';
3008  }
3009  }
3010 
3011  bool IsRootModule = M ? !M->Parent : true;
3012  // When a module name is specified as -fmodule-name, that module gets a
3013  // clang::Module object, but it won't actually be built or imported; it will
3014  // be textual.
3015  if (CreateSkeletonCU && IsRootModule && Mod.getASTFile().empty() && M)
3016  assert(StringRef(M->Name).starts_with(CGM.getLangOpts().ModuleName) &&
3017  "clang module without ASTFile must be specified by -fmodule-name");
3018 
3019  // Return a StringRef to the remapped Path.
3020  auto RemapPath = [this](StringRef Path) -> std::string {
3021  std::string Remapped = remapDIPath(Path);
3022  StringRef Relative(Remapped);
3023  StringRef CompDir = TheCU->getDirectory();
3024  if (Relative.consume_front(CompDir))
3025  Relative.consume_front(llvm::sys::path::get_separator());
3026 
3027  return Relative.str();
3028  };
3029 
3030  if (CreateSkeletonCU && IsRootModule && !Mod.getASTFile().empty()) {
3031  // PCH files don't have a signature field in the control block,
3032  // but LLVM detects skeleton CUs by looking for a non-zero DWO id.
3033  // We use the lower 64 bits for debug info.
3034 
3035  uint64_t Signature = 0;
3036  if (const auto &ModSig = Mod.getSignature())
3037  Signature = ModSig.truncatedValue();
3038  else
3039  Signature = ~1ULL;
3040 
3041  llvm::DIBuilder DIB(CGM.getModule());
3042  SmallString<0> PCM;
3043  if (!llvm::sys::path::is_absolute(Mod.getASTFile())) {
3044  if (CGM.getHeaderSearchOpts().ModuleFileHomeIsCwd)
3045  PCM = getCurrentDirname();
3046  else
3047  PCM = Mod.getPath();
3048  }
3049  llvm::sys::path::append(PCM, Mod.getASTFile());
3050  DIB.createCompileUnit(
3051  TheCU->getSourceLanguage(),
3052  // TODO: Support "Source" from external AST providers?
3053  DIB.createFile(Mod.getModuleName(), TheCU->getDirectory()),
3054  TheCU->getProducer(), false, StringRef(), 0, RemapPath(PCM),
3055  llvm::DICompileUnit::FullDebug, Signature);
3056  DIB.finalize();
3057  }
3058 
3059  llvm::DIModule *Parent =
3060  IsRootModule ? nullptr
3061  : getOrCreateModuleRef(ASTSourceDescriptor(*M->Parent),
3062  CreateSkeletonCU);
3063  std::string IncludePath = Mod.getPath().str();
3064  llvm::DIModule *DIMod =
3065  DBuilder.createModule(Parent, Mod.getModuleName(), ConfigMacros,
3066  RemapPath(IncludePath));
3067  ModuleCache[M].reset(DIMod);
3068  return DIMod;
3069 }
3070 
3071 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateTypeDefinition(const ObjCInterfaceType *Ty,
3072  llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
3073  ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID = Ty->getDecl();
3074  llvm::DIFile *DefUnit = getOrCreateFile(ID->getLocation());
3075  unsigned Line = getLineNumber(ID->getLocation());
3076  unsigned RuntimeLang = TheCU->getSourceLanguage();
3077 
3078  // Bit size, align and offset of the type.
3079  uint64_t Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
3080  auto Align = getTypeAlignIfRequired(Ty, CGM.getContext());
3081 
3082  llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
3083  if (ID->getImplementation())
3084  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagObjcClassComplete;
3085 
3086  llvm::DIScope *Mod = getParentModuleOrNull(ID);
3087  llvm::DICompositeType *RealDecl = DBuilder.createStructType(
3088  Mod ? Mod : Unit, ID->getName(), DefUnit, Line, Size, Align, Flags,
3089  nullptr, llvm::DINodeArray(), RuntimeLang);
3090 
3091  QualType QTy(Ty, 0);
3092  TypeCache[QTy.getAsOpaquePtr()].reset(RealDecl);
3093 
3094  // Push the struct on region stack.
3095  LexicalBlockStack.emplace_back(RealDecl);
3096  RegionMap[Ty->getDecl()].reset(RealDecl);
3097 
3098  // Convert all the elements.
3099  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 16> EltTys;
3100 
3101  ObjCInterfaceDecl *SClass = ID->getSuperClass();
3102  if (SClass) {
3103  llvm::DIType *SClassTy =
3104  getOrCreateType(CGM.getContext().getObjCInterfaceType(SClass), Unit);
3105  if (!SClassTy)
3106  return nullptr;
3107 
3108  llvm::DIType *InhTag = DBuilder.createInheritance(RealDecl, SClassTy, 0, 0,
3109  llvm::DINode::FlagZero);
3110  EltTys.push_back(InhTag);
3111  }
3112 
3113  // Create entries for all of the properties.
3114  auto AddProperty = [&](const ObjCPropertyDecl *PD) {
3115  SourceLocation Loc = PD->getLocation();
3116  llvm::DIFile *PUnit = getOrCreateFile(Loc);
3117  unsigned PLine = getLineNumber(Loc);
3118  ObjCMethodDecl *Getter = PD->getGetterMethodDecl();
3119  ObjCMethodDecl *Setter = PD->getSetterMethodDecl();
3120  llvm::MDNode *PropertyNode = DBuilder.createObjCProperty(
3121  PD->getName(), PUnit, PLine,
3122  hasDefaultGetterName(PD, Getter) ? ""
3123  : getSelectorName(PD->getGetterName()),
3124  hasDefaultSetterName(PD, Setter) ? ""
3125  : getSelectorName(PD->getSetterName()),
3126  PD->getPropertyAttributes(), getOrCreateType(PD->getType(), PUnit));
3127  EltTys.push_back(PropertyNode);
3128  };
3129  {
3130  // Use 'char' for the isClassProperty bit as DenseSet requires space for
3131  // empty/tombstone keys in the data type (and bool is too small for that).
3132  typedef std::pair<char, const IdentifierInfo *> IsClassAndIdent;
3133  /// List of already emitted properties. Two distinct class and instance
3134  /// properties can share the same identifier (but not two instance
3135  /// properties or two class properties).
3136  llvm::DenseSet<IsClassAndIdent> PropertySet;
3137  /// Returns the IsClassAndIdent key for the given property.
3138  auto GetIsClassAndIdent = [](const ObjCPropertyDecl *PD) {
3139  return std::make_pair(PD->isClassProperty(), PD->getIdentifier());
3140  };
3141  for (const ObjCCategoryDecl *ClassExt : ID->known_extensions())
3142  for (auto *PD : ClassExt->properties()) {
3143  PropertySet.insert(GetIsClassAndIdent(PD));
3144  AddProperty(PD);
3145  }
3146  for (const auto *PD : ID->properties()) {
3147  // Don't emit duplicate metadata for properties that were already in a
3148  // class extension.
3149  if (!PropertySet.insert(GetIsClassAndIdent(PD)).second)
3150  continue;
3151  AddProperty(PD);
3152  }
3153  }
3154 
3155  const ASTRecordLayout &RL = CGM.getContext().getASTObjCInterfaceLayout(ID);
3156  unsigned FieldNo = 0;
3157  for (ObjCIvarDecl *Field = ID->all_declared_ivar_begin(); Field;
3158  Field = Field->getNextIvar(), ++FieldNo) {
3159  llvm::DIType *FieldTy = getOrCreateType(Field->getType(), Unit);
3160  if (!FieldTy)
3161  return nullptr;
3162 
3163  StringRef FieldName = Field->getName();
3164 
3165  // Ignore unnamed fields.
3166  if (FieldName.empty())
3167  continue;
3168 
3169  // Get the location for the field.
3170  llvm::DIFile *FieldDefUnit = getOrCreateFile(Field->getLocation());
3171  unsigned FieldLine = getLineNumber(Field->getLocation());
3172  QualType FType = Field->getType();
3173  uint64_t FieldSize = 0;
3174  uint32_t FieldAlign = 0;
3175 
3176  if (!FType->isIncompleteArrayType()) {
3177 
3178  // Bit size, align and offset of the type.
3179  FieldSize = Field->isBitField()
3180  ? Field->getBitWidthValue(CGM.getContext())
3181  : CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(FType);
3182  FieldAlign = getTypeAlignIfRequired(FType, CGM.getContext());
3183  }
3184 
3185  uint64_t FieldOffset;
3186  if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCRuntime.isNonFragile()) {
3187  // We don't know the runtime offset of an ivar if we're using the
3188  // non-fragile ABI. For bitfields, use the bit offset into the first
3189  // byte of storage of the bitfield. For other fields, use zero.
3190  if (Field->isBitField()) {
3191  FieldOffset =
3192  CGM.getObjCRuntime().ComputeBitfieldBitOffset(CGM, ID, Field);
3193  FieldOffset %= CGM.getContext().getCharWidth();
3194  } else {
3195  FieldOffset = 0;
3196  }
3197  } else {
3198  FieldOffset = RL.getFieldOffset(FieldNo);
3199  }
3200 
3201  llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
3202  if (Field->getAccessControl() == ObjCIvarDecl::Protected)
3203  Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagProtected;
3204  else if (Field->getAccessControl() == ObjCIvarDecl::Private)
3205  Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagPrivate;
3206  else if (Field->getAccessControl() == ObjCIvarDecl::Public)
3207  Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagPublic;
3208 
3209  if (Field->isBitField())
3210  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagBitField;
3211 
3212  llvm::MDNode *PropertyNode = nullptr;
3213  if (ObjCImplementationDecl *ImpD = ID->getImplementation()) {
3214  if (ObjCPropertyImplDecl *PImpD =
3215  ImpD->FindPropertyImplIvarDecl(Field->getIdentifier())) {
3216  if (ObjCPropertyDecl *PD = PImpD->getPropertyDecl()) {
3217  SourceLocation Loc = PD->getLocation();
3218  llvm::DIFile *PUnit = getOrCreateFile(Loc);
3219  unsigned PLine = getLineNumber(Loc);
3220  ObjCMethodDecl *Getter = PImpD->getGetterMethodDecl();
3221  ObjCMethodDecl *Setter = PImpD->getSetterMethodDecl();
3222  PropertyNode = DBuilder.createObjCProperty(
3223  PD->getName(), PUnit, PLine,
3224  hasDefaultGetterName(PD, Getter)
3225  ? ""
3226  : getSelectorName(PD->getGetterName()),
3227  hasDefaultSetterName(PD, Setter)
3228  ? ""
3229  : getSelectorName(PD->getSetterName()),
3230  PD->getPropertyAttributes(),
3231  getOrCreateType(PD->getType(), PUnit));
3232  }
3233  }
3234  }
3235  FieldTy = DBuilder.createObjCIVar(FieldName, FieldDefUnit, FieldLine,
3236  FieldSize, FieldAlign, FieldOffset, Flags,
3237  FieldTy, PropertyNode);
3238  EltTys.push_back(FieldTy);
3239  }
3240 
3241  llvm::DINodeArray Elements = DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(EltTys);
3242  DBuilder.replaceArrays(RealDecl, Elements);
3243 
3244  LexicalBlockStack.pop_back();
3245  return RealDecl;
3246 }
3247 
3248 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const VectorType *Ty,
3249  llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
3250  if (Ty->isExtVectorBoolType()) {
3251  // Boolean ext_vector_type(N) are special because their real element type
3252  // (bits of bit size) is not their Clang element type (_Bool of size byte).
3253  // For now, we pretend the boolean vector were actually a vector of bytes
3254  // (where each byte represents 8 bits of the actual vector).
3255  // FIXME Debug info should actually represent this proper as a vector mask
3256  // type.
3257  auto &Ctx = CGM.getContext();
3258  uint64_t Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
3259  uint64_t NumVectorBytes = Size / Ctx.getCharWidth();
3260 
3261  // Construct the vector of 'char' type.
3262  QualType CharVecTy =
3263  Ctx.getVectorType(Ctx.CharTy, NumVectorBytes, VectorKind::Generic);
3264  return CreateType(CharVecTy->getAs<VectorType>(), Unit);
3265  }
3266 
3267  llvm::DIType *ElementTy = getOrCreateType(Ty->getElementType(), Unit);
3268  int64_t Count = Ty->getNumElements();
3269 
3270  llvm::Metadata *Subscript;
3271  QualType QTy(Ty, 0);
3272  auto SizeExpr = SizeExprCache.find(QTy);
3273  if (SizeExpr != SizeExprCache.end())
3274  Subscript = DBuilder.getOrCreateSubrange(
3275  SizeExpr->getSecond() /*count*/, nullptr /*lowerBound*/,
3276  nullptr /*upperBound*/, nullptr /*stride*/);
3277  else {
3278  auto *CountNode =
3279  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::getSigned(
3280  llvm::Type::getInt64Ty(CGM.getLLVMContext()), Count ? Count : -1));
3281  Subscript = DBuilder.getOrCreateSubrange(
3282  CountNode /*count*/, nullptr /*lowerBound*/, nullptr /*upperBound*/,
3283  nullptr /*stride*/);
3284  }
3285  llvm::DINodeArray SubscriptArray = DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(Subscript);
3286 
3287  uint64_t Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
3288  auto Align = getTypeAlignIfRequired(Ty, CGM.getContext());
3289 
3290  return DBuilder.createVectorType(Size, Align, ElementTy, SubscriptArray);
3291 }
3292 
3293 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const ConstantMatrixType *Ty,
3294  llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
3295  // FIXME: Create another debug type for matrices
3296  // For the time being, it treats it like a nested ArrayType.
3297 
3298  llvm::DIType *ElementTy = getOrCreateType(Ty->getElementType(), Unit);
3299  uint64_t Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
3300  uint32_t Align = getTypeAlignIfRequired(Ty, CGM.getContext());
3301 
3302  // Create ranges for both dimensions.
3303  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 2> Subscripts;
3304  auto *ColumnCountNode =
3305  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::getSigned(
3306  llvm::Type::getInt64Ty(CGM.getLLVMContext()), Ty->getNumColumns()));
3307  auto *RowCountNode =
3308  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::getSigned(
3309  llvm::Type::getInt64Ty(CGM.getLLVMContext()), Ty->getNumRows()));
3310  Subscripts.push_back(DBuilder.getOrCreateSubrange(
3311  ColumnCountNode /*count*/, nullptr /*lowerBound*/, nullptr /*upperBound*/,
3312  nullptr /*stride*/));
3313  Subscripts.push_back(DBuilder.getOrCreateSubrange(
3314  RowCountNode /*count*/, nullptr /*lowerBound*/, nullptr /*upperBound*/,
3315  nullptr /*stride*/));
3316  llvm::DINodeArray SubscriptArray = DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(Subscripts);
3317  return DBuilder.createArrayType(Size, Align, ElementTy, SubscriptArray);
3318 }
3319 
3320 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const ArrayType *Ty, llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
3321  uint64_t Size;
3322  uint32_t Align;
3323 
3324  // FIXME: make getTypeAlign() aware of VLAs and incomplete array types
3325  if (const auto *VAT = dyn_cast<VariableArrayType>(Ty)) {
3326  Size = 0;
3327  Align = getTypeAlignIfRequired(CGM.getContext().getBaseElementType(VAT),
3328  CGM.getContext());
3329  } else if (Ty->isIncompleteArrayType()) {
3330  Size = 0;
3331  if (Ty->getElementType()->isIncompleteType())
3332  Align = 0;
3333  else
3334  Align = getTypeAlignIfRequired(Ty->getElementType(), CGM.getContext());
3335  } else if (Ty->isIncompleteType()) {
3336  Size = 0;
3337  Align = 0;
3338  } else {
3339  // Size and align of the whole array, not the element type.
3340  Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
3341  Align = getTypeAlignIfRequired(Ty, CGM.getContext());
3342  }
3343 
3344  // Add the dimensions of the array. FIXME: This loses CV qualifiers from
3345  // interior arrays, do we care? Why aren't nested arrays represented the
3346  // obvious/recursive way?
3347  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> Subscripts;
3348  QualType EltTy(Ty, 0);
3349  while ((Ty = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(EltTy))) {
3350  // If the number of elements is known, then count is that number. Otherwise,
3351  // it's -1. This allows us to represent a subrange with an array of 0
3352  // elements, like this:
3353  //
3354  // struct foo {
3355  // int x[0];
3356  // };
3357  int64_t Count = -1; // Count == -1 is an unbounded array.
3358  if (const auto *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(Ty))
3359  Count = CAT->getZExtSize();
3360  else if (const auto *VAT = dyn_cast<VariableArrayType>(Ty)) {
3361  if (Expr *Size = VAT->getSizeExpr()) {
3362  Expr::EvalResult Result;
3363  if (Size->EvaluateAsInt(Result, CGM.getContext()))
3364  Count = Result.Val.getInt().getExtValue();
3365  }
3366  }
3367 
3368  auto SizeNode = SizeExprCache.find(EltTy);
3369  if (SizeNode != SizeExprCache.end())
3370  Subscripts.push_back(DBuilder.getOrCreateSubrange(
3371  SizeNode->getSecond() /*count*/, nullptr /*lowerBound*/,
3372  nullptr /*upperBound*/, nullptr /*stride*/));
3373  else {
3374  auto *CountNode =
3375  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::getSigned(
3376  llvm::Type::getInt64Ty(CGM.getLLVMContext()), Count));
3377  Subscripts.push_back(DBuilder.getOrCreateSubrange(
3378  CountNode /*count*/, nullptr /*lowerBound*/, nullptr /*upperBound*/,
3379  nullptr /*stride*/));
3380  }
3381  EltTy = Ty->getElementType();
3382  }
3383 
3384  llvm::DINodeArray SubscriptArray = DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(Subscripts);
3385 
3386  return DBuilder.createArrayType(Size, Align, getOrCreateType(EltTy, Unit),
3387  SubscriptArray);
3388 }

3391  llvm::DIFile *Unit) {

3393  Ty->getPointeeType(), Unit);

3396 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const RValueReferenceType *Ty,
3397  llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
3398  llvm::dwarf::Tag Tag = llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_rvalue_reference_type;
3399  // DW_TAG_rvalue_reference_type was introduced in DWARF 4.
3400  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DebugStrictDwarf &&
3401  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DwarfVersion < 4)
3402  Tag = llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_reference_type;

3404  return CreatePointerLikeType(Tag, Ty, Ty->getPointeeType(), Unit);

3406 
3407 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const MemberPointerType *Ty,
3408  llvm::DIFile *U) {
3409  llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
3410  uint64_t Size = 0;
3411 
3412  if (!Ty->isIncompleteType()) {
3413  Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
3414 
3415  // Set the MS inheritance model. There is no flag for the unspecified model.
3416  if (CGM.getTarget().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft()) {
3417  switch (Ty->getMostRecentCXXRecordDecl()->getMSInheritanceModel()) {
3418  case MSInheritanceModel::Single:
3419  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagSingleInheritance;
3420  break;
3421  case MSInheritanceModel::Multiple:
3422  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagMultipleInheritance;
3423  break;
3424  case MSInheritanceModel::Virtual:
3425  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagVirtualInheritance;
3426  break;
3427  case MSInheritanceModel::Unspecified:
3428  break;
3429  }
3430  }
3431  }
3432 
3433  llvm::DIType *ClassType = getOrCreateType(QualType(Ty->getClass(), 0), U);
3434  if (Ty->isMemberDataPointerType())
3435  return DBuilder.createMemberPointerType(
3436  getOrCreateType(Ty->getPointeeType(), U), ClassType, Size, /*Align=*/0,
3437  Flags);
3438 
3439  const FunctionProtoType *FPT =
3440  Ty->getPointeeType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
3441  return DBuilder.createMemberPointerType(
3442  getOrCreateInstanceMethodType(
3443  CXXMethodDecl::getThisType(FPT, Ty->getMostRecentCXXRecordDecl()),
3444  FPT, U),
3445  ClassType, Size, /*Align=*/0, Flags);
3446 }

3456 
3457 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateEnumType(const EnumType *Ty) {
3458  const EnumDecl *ED = Ty->getDecl();
3459 
3460  uint64_t Size = 0;
3461  uint32_t Align = 0;
3462  if (!ED->getTypeForDecl()->isIncompleteType()) {
3463  Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(ED->getTypeForDecl());
3464  Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(ED, CGM.getContext());
3465  }
3466 
3467  SmallString<256> Identifier = getTypeIdentifier(Ty, CGM, TheCU);
3468 
3469  bool isImportedFromModule =
3470  DebugTypeExtRefs && ED->isFromASTFile() && ED->getDefinition();
3471 
3472  // If this is just a forward declaration, construct an appropriately
3473  // marked node and just return it.
3474  if (isImportedFromModule || !ED->getDefinition()) {
3475  // Note that it is possible for enums to be created as part of
3476  // their own declcontext. In this case a FwdDecl will be created
3477  // twice. This doesn't cause a problem because both FwdDecls are
3478  // entered into the ReplaceMap: finalize() will replace the first
3479  // FwdDecl with the second and then replace the second with
3480  // complete type.
3481  llvm::DIScope *EDContext = getDeclContextDescriptor(ED);
3482  llvm::DIFile *DefUnit = getOrCreateFile(ED->getLocation());
3483  llvm::TempDIScope TmpContext(DBuilder.createReplaceableCompositeType(
3484  llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_enumeration_type, "", TheCU, DefUnit, 0));
3485 
3486  unsigned Line = getLineNumber(ED->getLocation());
3487  StringRef EDName = ED->getName();
3488  llvm::DIType *RetTy = DBuilder.createReplaceableCompositeType(
3489  llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_enumeration_type, EDName, EDContext, DefUnit, Line,
3490  0, Size, Align, llvm::DINode::FlagFwdDecl, Identifier);
3491 
3492  ReplaceMap.emplace_back(
3493  std::piecewise_construct, std::make_tuple(Ty),
3494  std::make_tuple(static_cast<llvm::Metadata *>(RetTy)));
3495  return RetTy;
3496  }
3497 
3498  return CreateTypeDefinition(Ty);
3499 }
3500 
3501 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateTypeDefinition(const EnumType *Ty) {
3502  const EnumDecl *ED = Ty->getDecl();
3503  uint64_t Size = 0;
3504  uint32_t Align = 0;
3505  if (!ED->getTypeForDecl()->isIncompleteType()) {
3506  Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(ED->getTypeForDecl());
3507  Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(ED, CGM.getContext());
3508  }
3509 
3510  SmallString<256> Identifier = getTypeIdentifier(Ty, CGM, TheCU);
3511 
3512  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 16> Enumerators;
3513  ED = ED->getDefinition();
3514  for (const auto *Enum : ED->enumerators()) {
3515  Enumerators.push_back(
3516  DBuilder.createEnumerator(Enum->getName(), Enum->getInitVal()));
3517  }
3518 
3519  // Return a CompositeType for the enum itself.
3520  llvm::DINodeArray EltArray = DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(Enumerators);
3521 
3522  llvm::DIFile *DefUnit = getOrCreateFile(ED->getLocation());
3523  unsigned Line = getLineNumber(ED->getLocation());
3524  llvm::DIScope *EnumContext = getDeclContextDescriptor(ED);
3525  llvm::DIType *ClassTy = getOrCreateType(ED->getIntegerType(), DefUnit);
3526  return DBuilder.createEnumerationType(
3527  EnumContext, ED->getName(), DefUnit, Line, Size, Align, EltArray, ClassTy,
3528  /*RunTimeLang=*/0, Identifier, ED->isScoped());
3529 }

3545 
3546 static QualType UnwrapTypeForDebugInfo(QualType T, const ASTContext &C) {
3547  Qualifiers Quals;
3548  do {
3549  Qualifiers InnerQuals = T.getLocalQualifiers();
3550  // Qualifiers::operator+() doesn't like it if you add a Qualifier
3551  // that is already there.
3552  Quals += Qualifiers::removeCommonQualifiers(Quals, InnerQuals);
3553  Quals += InnerQuals;
3554  QualType LastT = T;
3555  switch (T->getTypeClass()) {
3556  default:
3557  return C.getQualifiedType(T.getTypePtr(), Quals);
3558  case Type::TemplateSpecialization: {
3559  const auto *Spec = cast<TemplateSpecializationType>(T);
3560  if (Spec->isTypeAlias())
3561  return C.getQualifiedType(T.getTypePtr(), Quals);
3562  T = Spec->desugar();
3563  break;
3564  }
3565  case Type::TypeOfExpr:
3566  T = cast<TypeOfExprType>(T)->getUnderlyingExpr()->getType();
3567  break;
3568  case Type::TypeOf:
3569  T = cast<TypeOfType>(T)->getUnmodifiedType();
3570  break;
3571  case Type::Decltype:
3572  T = cast<DecltypeType>(T)->getUnderlyingType();
3573  break;
3574  case Type::UnaryTransform:
3575  T = cast<UnaryTransformType>(T)->getUnderlyingType();
3576  break;
3577  case Type::Attributed:
3578  T = cast<AttributedType>(T)->getEquivalentType();
3579  break;
3580  case Type::BTFTagAttributed:
3581  T = cast<BTFTagAttributedType>(T)->getWrappedType();
3582  break;
3583  case Type::CountAttributed:
3584  T = cast<CountAttributedType>(T)->desugar();
3585  break;
3586  case Type::Elaborated:
3587  T = cast<ElaboratedType>(T)->getNamedType();
3588  break;
3589  case Type::Using:
3590  T = cast<UsingType>(T)->getUnderlyingType();
3591  break;
3592  case Type::Paren:
3593  T = cast<ParenType>(T)->getInnerType();
3594  break;
3595  case Type::MacroQualified:
3596  T = cast<MacroQualifiedType>(T)->getUnderlyingType();
3597  break;
3598  case Type::SubstTemplateTypeParm:
3599  T = cast<SubstTemplateTypeParmType>(T)->getReplacementType();
3600  break;
3601  case Type::Auto:
3602  case Type::DeducedTemplateSpecialization: {
3603  QualType DT = cast<DeducedType>(T)->getDeducedType();
3604  assert(!DT.isNull() && "Undeduced types shouldn't reach here.");
3605  T = DT;
3606  break;
3607  }
3608  case Type::PackIndexing: {
3609  T = cast<PackIndexingType>(T)->getSelectedType();
3610  break;
3611  }
3612  case Type::Adjusted:
3613  case Type::Decayed:
3614  // Decayed and adjusted types use the adjusted type in LLVM and DWARF.
3615  T = cast<AdjustedType>(T)->getAdjustedType();
3616  break;
3617  }
3618 
3619  assert(T != LastT && "Type unwrapping failed to unwrap!");
3620  (void)LastT;
3621  } while (true);
3622 }
3623 
3624 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::getTypeOrNull(QualType Ty) {
3625  assert(Ty == UnwrapTypeForDebugInfo(Ty, CGM.getContext()));
3626  auto It = TypeCache.find(Ty.getAsOpaquePtr());
3627  if (It != TypeCache.end()) {
3628  // Verify that the debug info still exists.
3629  if (llvm::Metadata *V = It->second)
3630  return cast<llvm::DIType>(V);
3631  }
3632 
3633  return nullptr;
3634 }

3637  const ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl &SD) {
3638  completeUnusedClass(SD);
3639 }
3640 
3641 void CGDebugInfo::completeUnusedClass(const CXXRecordDecl &D) {
3642  if (DebugKind <= llvm::codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly ||
3643  D.isDynamicClass())
3644  return;
3645 
3646  completeClassData(&D);
3647  // In case this type has no member function definitions being emitted, ensure
3648  // it is retained
3649  RetainedTypes.push_back(CGM.getContext().getRecordType(&D).getAsOpaquePtr());
3650 }
3651 
3652 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateType(QualType Ty, llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
3653  if (Ty.isNull())
3654  return nullptr;
3655 
3656  llvm::TimeTraceScope TimeScope("DebugType", [&]() {
3657  std::string Name;
3658  llvm::raw_string_ostream OS(Name);
3659  Ty.print(OS, getPrintingPolicy());
3660  return Name;
3661  });
3662 
3663  // Unwrap the type as needed for debug information.
3664  Ty = UnwrapTypeForDebugInfo(Ty, CGM.getContext());
3665 
3666  if (auto *T = getTypeOrNull(Ty))
3667  return T;
3668 
3669  llvm::DIType *Res = CreateTypeNode(Ty, Unit);
3670  void *TyPtr = Ty.getAsOpaquePtr();
3671 
3672  // And update the type cache.
3673  TypeCache[TyPtr].reset(Res);
3674 
3675  return Res;
3676 }
3677 
3678 llvm::DIModule *CGDebugInfo::getParentModuleOrNull(const Decl *D) {
3679  // A forward declaration inside a module header does not belong to the module.
3680  if (isa<RecordDecl>(D) && !cast<RecordDecl>(D)->getDefinition())
3681  return nullptr;
3682  if (DebugTypeExtRefs && D->isFromASTFile()) {
3683  // Record a reference to an imported clang module or precompiled header.
3684  auto *Reader = CGM.getContext().getExternalSource();
3685  auto Idx = D->getOwningModuleID();
3686  auto Info = Reader->getSourceDescriptor(Idx);
3687  if (Info)
3688  return getOrCreateModuleRef(*Info, /*SkeletonCU=*/true);
3689  } else if (ClangModuleMap) {
3690  // We are building a clang module or a precompiled header.
3691  //
3692  // TODO: When D is a CXXRecordDecl or a C++ Enum, the ODR applies
3693  // and it wouldn't be necessary to specify the parent scope
3694  // because the type is already unique by definition (it would look
3695  // like the output of -fno-standalone-debug). On the other hand,
3696  // the parent scope helps a consumer to quickly locate the object
3697  // file where the type's definition is located, so it might be
3698  // best to make this behavior a command line or debugger tuning
3699  // option.
3700  if (Module *M = D->getOwningModule()) {
3701  // This is a (sub-)module.
3702  auto Info = ASTSourceDescriptor(*M);
3703  return getOrCreateModuleRef(Info, /*SkeletonCU=*/false);
3704  } else {
3705  // This the precompiled header being built.
3706  return getOrCreateModuleRef(PCHDescriptor, /*SkeletonCU=*/false);
3707  }
3708  }
3709 
3710  return nullptr;
3711 }
3712 
3713 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateTypeNode(QualType Ty, llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
3714  // Handle qualifiers, which recursively handles what they refer to.
3715  if (Ty.hasLocalQualifiers())
3716  return CreateQualifiedType(Ty, Unit);
3717 
3718  // Work out details of type.
3719  switch (Ty->getTypeClass()) {
3720 #define TYPE(Class, Base)
3721 #define ABSTRACT_TYPE(Class, Base)
3722 #define NON_CANONICAL_TYPE(Class, Base)
3723 #define DEPENDENT_TYPE(Class, Base) case Type::Class:
3724 #include "clang/AST/TypeNodes.inc"
3725  llvm_unreachable("Dependent types cannot show up in debug information");
3726 
3727  case Type::ExtVector:
3728  case Type::Vector:
3729  return CreateType(cast<VectorType>(Ty), Unit);
3730  case Type::ConstantMatrix:
3731  return CreateType(cast<ConstantMatrixType>(Ty), Unit);
3732  case Type::ObjCObjectPointer:
3733  return CreateType(cast<ObjCObjectPointerType>(Ty), Unit);
3734  case Type::ObjCObject:
3735  return CreateType(cast<ObjCObjectType>(Ty), Unit);
3736  case Type::ObjCTypeParam:
3737  return CreateType(cast<ObjCTypeParamType>(Ty), Unit);
3738  case Type::ObjCInterface:
3739  return CreateType(cast<ObjCInterfaceType>(Ty), Unit);
3740  case Type::Builtin:
3741  return CreateType(cast<BuiltinType>(Ty));
3742  case Type::Complex:
3743  return CreateType(cast<ComplexType>(Ty));
3744  case Type::Pointer:
3745  return CreateType(cast<PointerType>(Ty), Unit);
3746  case Type::BlockPointer:
3747  return CreateType(cast<BlockPointerType>(Ty), Unit);
3748  case Type::Typedef:
3749  return CreateType(cast<TypedefType>(Ty), Unit);
3750  case Type::Record:
3751  return CreateType(cast<RecordType>(Ty));
3752  case Type::Enum:
3753  return CreateEnumType(cast<EnumType>(Ty));
3754  case Type::FunctionProto:
3755  case Type::FunctionNoProto:
3756  return CreateType(cast<FunctionType>(Ty), Unit);
3757  case Type::ConstantArray:
3758  case Type::VariableArray:
3759  case Type::IncompleteArray:
3760  case Type::ArrayParameter:
3761  return CreateType(cast<ArrayType>(Ty), Unit);
3762 
3763  case Type::LValueReference:
3764  return CreateType(cast<LValueReferenceType>(Ty), Unit);
3765  case Type::RValueReference:
3766  return CreateType(cast<RValueReferenceType>(Ty), Unit);
3767 
3768  case Type::MemberPointer:
3769  return CreateType(cast<MemberPointerType>(Ty), Unit);
3770 
3771  case Type::Atomic:
3772  return CreateType(cast<AtomicType>(Ty), Unit);
3773 
3774  case Type::BitInt:
3775  return CreateType(cast<BitIntType>(Ty));
3776  case Type::Pipe:
3777  return CreateType(cast<PipeType>(Ty), Unit);
3778 
3779  case Type::TemplateSpecialization:
3780  return CreateType(cast<TemplateSpecializationType>(Ty), Unit);
3781 
3782  case Type::CountAttributed:
3783  case Type::Auto:
3784  case Type::Attributed:
3785  case Type::BTFTagAttributed:
3786  case Type::Adjusted:
3787  case Type::Decayed:
3788  case Type::DeducedTemplateSpecialization:
3789  case Type::Elaborated:
3790  case Type::Using:
3791  case Type::Paren:
3792  case Type::MacroQualified:
3793  case Type::SubstTemplateTypeParm:
3794  case Type::TypeOfExpr:
3795  case Type::TypeOf:
3796  case Type::Decltype:
3797  case Type::PackIndexing:
3798  case Type::UnaryTransform:
3799  break;
3800  }
3801 
3802  llvm_unreachable("type should have been unwrapped!");
3803 }
3804 
3805 llvm::DICompositeType *
3806 CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateLimitedType(const RecordType *Ty) {
3807  QualType QTy(Ty, 0);
3808 
3809  auto *T = cast_or_null<llvm::DICompositeType>(getTypeOrNull(QTy));
3810 
3811  // We may have cached a forward decl when we could have created
3812  // a non-forward decl. Go ahead and create a non-forward decl
3813  // now.
3814  if (T && !T->isForwardDecl())
3815  return T;
3816 
3817  // Otherwise create the type.
3818  llvm::DICompositeType *Res = CreateLimitedType(Ty);
3819 
3820  // Propagate members from the declaration to the definition
3821  // CreateType(const RecordType*) will overwrite this with the members in the
3822  // correct order if the full type is needed.
3823  DBuilder.replaceArrays(Res, T ? T->getElements() : llvm::DINodeArray());
3824 
3825  // And update the type cache.
3826  TypeCache[QTy.getAsOpaquePtr()].reset(Res);
3827  return Res;
3828 }
3829 
3830 // TODO: Currently used for context chains when limiting debug info.
3831 llvm::DICompositeType *CGDebugInfo::CreateLimitedType(const RecordType *Ty) {
3832  RecordDecl *RD = Ty->getDecl();
3833 
3834  // Get overall information about the record type for the debug info.
3835  StringRef RDName = getClassName(RD);
3836  const SourceLocation Loc = RD->getLocation();
3837  llvm::DIFile *DefUnit = nullptr;
3838  unsigned Line = 0;
3839  if (Loc.isValid()) {
3840  DefUnit = getOrCreateFile(Loc);
3841  Line = getLineNumber(Loc);
3842  }
3843 
3844  llvm::DIScope *RDContext = getDeclContextDescriptor(RD);
3845 
3846  // If we ended up creating the type during the context chain construction,
3847  // just return that.
3848  auto *T = cast_or_null<llvm::DICompositeType>(
3849  getTypeOrNull(CGM.getContext().getRecordType(RD)));
3850  if (T && (!T->isForwardDecl() || !RD->getDefinition()))
3851  return T;
3852 
3853  // If this is just a forward or incomplete declaration, construct an
3854  // appropriately marked node and just return it.
3855  const RecordDecl *D = RD->getDefinition();
3856  if (!D || !D->isCompleteDefinition())
3857  return getOrCreateRecordFwdDecl(Ty, RDContext);
3858 
3859  uint64_t Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
3860  // __attribute__((aligned)) can increase or decrease alignment *except* on a
3861  // struct or struct member, where it only increases alignment unless 'packed'
3862  // is also specified. To handle this case, the `getTypeAlignIfRequired` needs
3863  // to be used.
3864  auto Align = getTypeAlignIfRequired(Ty, CGM.getContext());
3865 
3866  SmallString<256> Identifier = getTypeIdentifier(Ty, CGM, TheCU);
3867 
3868  // Explicitly record the calling convention and export symbols for C++
3869  // records.
3870  auto Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
3871  if (auto CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD)) {
3872  if (CGM.getCXXABI().getRecordArgABI(CXXRD) == CGCXXABI::RAA_Indirect)
3873  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagTypePassByReference;
3874  else
3875  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagTypePassByValue;
3876 
3877  // Record if a C++ record is non-trivial type.
3878  if (!CXXRD->isTrivial())
3879  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagNonTrivial;
3880 
3881  // Record exports it symbols to the containing structure.
3882  if (CXXRD->isAnonymousStructOrUnion())
3883  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagExportSymbols;
3884 
3885  Flags |= getAccessFlag(CXXRD->getAccess(),
3886  dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(CXXRD->getDeclContext()));
3887  }
3888 
3889  llvm::DINodeArray Annotations = CollectBTFDeclTagAnnotations(D);
3890  llvm::DICompositeType *RealDecl = DBuilder.createReplaceableCompositeType(
3891  getTagForRecord(RD), RDName, RDContext, DefUnit, Line, 0, Size, Align,
3892  Flags, Identifier, Annotations);
3893 
3894  // Elements of composite types usually have back to the type, creating
3895  // uniquing cycles. Distinct nodes are more efficient.
3896  switch (RealDecl->getTag()) {
3897  default:
3898  llvm_unreachable("invalid composite type tag");
3899 
3900  case llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_array_type:
3901  case llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_enumeration_type:
3902  // Array elements and most enumeration elements don't have back references,
3903  // so they don't tend to be involved in uniquing cycles and there is some
3904  // chance of merging them when linking together two modules. Only make
3905  // them distinct if they are ODR-uniqued.
3906  if (Identifier.empty())
3907  break;
3908  [[fallthrough]];
3909 
3910  case llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_structure_type:
3911  case llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_union_type:
3912  case llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_class_type:
3913  // Immediately resolve to a distinct node.
3914  RealDecl =
3915  llvm::MDNode::replaceWithDistinct(llvm::TempDICompositeType(RealDecl));
3916  break;
3917  }
3918 
3919  RegionMap[Ty->getDecl()].reset(RealDecl);
3920  TypeCache[QualType(Ty, 0).getAsOpaquePtr()].reset(RealDecl);
3921 
3922  if (const auto *TSpecial = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RD))
3923  DBuilder.replaceArrays(RealDecl, llvm::DINodeArray(),
3924  CollectCXXTemplateParams(TSpecial, DefUnit));
3925  return RealDecl;
3926 }
3927 
3928 void CGDebugInfo::CollectContainingType(const CXXRecordDecl *RD,
3929  llvm::DICompositeType *RealDecl) {
3930  // A class's primary base or the class itself contains the vtable.
3931  llvm::DIType *ContainingType = nullptr;
3932  const ASTRecordLayout &RL = CGM.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
3933  if (const CXXRecordDecl *PBase = RL.getPrimaryBase()) {
3934  // Seek non-virtual primary base root.
3935  while (true) {
3936  const ASTRecordLayout &BRL = CGM.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(PBase);
3937  const CXXRecordDecl *PBT = BRL.getPrimaryBase();
3938  if (PBT && !BRL.isPrimaryBaseVirtual())
3939  PBase = PBT;
3940  else
3941  break;
3942  }
3943  ContainingType = getOrCreateType(QualType(PBase->getTypeForDecl(), 0),
3944  getOrCreateFile(RD->getLocation()));
3945  } else if (RD->isDynamicClass())
3946  ContainingType = RealDecl;
3947 
3948  DBuilder.replaceVTableHolder(RealDecl, ContainingType);
3949 }

3951 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateMemberType(llvm::DIFile *Unit, QualType FType,
3952  StringRef Name, uint64_t *Offset) {
3953  llvm::DIType *FieldTy = CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateType(FType, Unit);
3954  uint64_t FieldSize = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(FType);
3955  auto FieldAlign = getTypeAlignIfRequired(FType, CGM.getContext());
3956  llvm::DIType *Ty =
3957  DBuilder.createMemberType(Unit, Name, Unit, 0, FieldSize, FieldAlign,
3958  *Offset, llvm::DINode::FlagZero, FieldTy);
3959  *Offset += FieldSize;
3960  return Ty;
3961 }
3962 
3963 void CGDebugInfo::collectFunctionDeclProps(GlobalDecl GD, llvm::DIFile *Unit,
3964  StringRef &Name,
3965  StringRef &LinkageName,
3966  llvm::DIScope *&FDContext,
3967  llvm::DINodeArray &TParamsArray,
3968  llvm::DINode::DIFlags &Flags) {
3969  const auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getCanonicalDecl().getDecl());
3970  Name = getFunctionName(FD);
3971  // Use mangled name as linkage name for C/C++ functions.
3972  if (FD->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>())
3973  LinkageName = CGM.getMangledName(GD);
3974  if (FD->hasPrototype())
3975  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagPrototyped;
3976  // No need to replicate the linkage name if it isn't different from the
3977  // subprogram name, no need to have it at all unless coverage is enabled or
3978  // debug is set to more than just line tables or extra debug info is needed.
3979  if (LinkageName == Name ||
3980  (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().CoverageNotesFile.empty() &&
3981  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().CoverageDataFile.empty() &&
3982  !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DebugInfoForProfiling &&
3983  !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().PseudoProbeForProfiling &&
3984  DebugKind <= llvm::codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly))
3985  LinkageName = StringRef();
3986 
3987  // Emit the function scope in line tables only mode (if CodeView) to
3988  // differentiate between function names.
3989  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo() ||
3990  (DebugKind == llvm::codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly &&
3991  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCodeView)) {
3992  if (const NamespaceDecl *NSDecl =
3993  dyn_cast_or_null<NamespaceDecl>(FD->getDeclContext()))
3994  FDContext = getOrCreateNamespace(NSDecl);
3995  else if (const RecordDecl *RDecl =
3996  dyn_cast_or_null<RecordDecl>(FD->getDeclContext())) {
3997  llvm::DIScope *Mod = getParentModuleOrNull(RDecl);
3998  FDContext = getContextDescriptor(RDecl, Mod ? Mod : TheCU);
3999  }
4000  }
4001  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo()) {
4002  // Check if it is a noreturn-marked function
4003  if (FD->isNoReturn())
4004  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagNoReturn;
4005  // Collect template parameters.
4006  TParamsArray = CollectFunctionTemplateParams(FD, Unit);
4007  }
4008 }
4009 
4010 void CGDebugInfo::collectVarDeclProps(const VarDecl *VD, llvm::DIFile *&Unit,
4011  unsigned &LineNo, QualType &T,
4012  StringRef &Name, StringRef &LinkageName,
4013  llvm::MDTuple *&TemplateParameters,
4014  llvm::DIScope *&VDContext) {
4015  Unit = getOrCreateFile(VD->getLocation());
4016  LineNo = getLineNumber(VD->getLocation());
4017 
4018  setLocation(VD->getLocation());
4019 
4020  T = VD->getType();
4021  if (T->isIncompleteArrayType()) {
4022  // CodeGen turns int[] into int[1] so we'll do the same here.
4023  llvm::APInt ConstVal(32, 1);
4024  QualType ET = CGM.getContext().getAsArrayType(T)->getElementType();
4025 
4026  T = CGM.getContext().getConstantArrayType(ET, ConstVal, nullptr,
4027  ArraySizeModifier::Normal, 0);
4028  }
4029 
4030  Name = VD->getName();
4031  if (VD->getDeclContext() && !isa<FunctionDecl>(VD->getDeclContext()) &&
4032  !isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(VD->getDeclContext()))
4033  LinkageName = CGM.getMangledName(VD);
4034  if (LinkageName == Name)
4035  LinkageName = StringRef();
4036 
4037  if (isa<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(VD)) {
4038  llvm::DINodeArray parameterNodes = CollectVarTemplateParams(VD, &*Unit);
4039  TemplateParameters = parameterNodes.get();
4040  } else {
4041  TemplateParameters = nullptr;
4042  }
4043 
4044  // Since we emit declarations (DW_AT_members) for static members, place the
4045  // definition of those static members in the namespace they were declared in
4046  // in the source code (the lexical decl context).
4047  // FIXME: Generalize this for even non-member global variables where the
4048  // declaration and definition may have different lexical decl contexts, once
4049  // we have support for emitting declarations of (non-member) global variables.
4050  const DeclContext *DC = VD->isStaticDataMember() ? VD->getLexicalDeclContext()
4051  : VD->getDeclContext();
4052  // When a record type contains an in-line initialization of a static data
4053  // member, and the record type is marked as __declspec(dllexport), an implicit
4054  // definition of the member will be created in the record context. DWARF
4055  // doesn't seem to have a nice way to describe this in a form that consumers
4056  // are likely to understand, so fake the "normal" situation of a definition
4057  // outside the class by putting it in the global scope.
4058  if (DC->isRecord())
4059  DC = CGM.getContext().getTranslationUnitDecl();
4060 
4061  llvm::DIScope *Mod = getParentModuleOrNull(VD);
4062  VDContext = getContextDescriptor(cast<Decl>(DC), Mod ? Mod : TheCU);
4063 }
4064 
4065 llvm::DISubprogram *CGDebugInfo::getFunctionFwdDeclOrStub(GlobalDecl GD,
4066  bool Stub) {
4067  llvm::DINodeArray TParamsArray;
4068  StringRef Name, LinkageName;
4069  llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
4070  llvm::DISubprogram::DISPFlags SPFlags = llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagZero;
4071  SourceLocation Loc = GD.getDecl()->getLocation();
4072  llvm::DIFile *Unit = getOrCreateFile(Loc);
4073  llvm::DIScope *DContext = Unit;
4074  unsigned Line = getLineNumber(Loc);
4075  collectFunctionDeclProps(GD, Unit, Name, LinkageName, DContext, TParamsArray,
4076  Flags);
4077  auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
4078 
4079  // Build function type.
4080  SmallVector<QualType, 16> ArgTypes;
4081  for (const ParmVarDecl *Parm : FD->parameters())
4082  ArgTypes.push_back(Parm->getType());
4083 
4084  CallingConv CC = FD->getType()->castAs<FunctionType>()->getCallConv();
4085  QualType FnType = CGM.getContext().getFunctionType(
4086  FD->getReturnType(), ArgTypes, FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo(CC));
4087  if (!FD->isExternallyVisible())
4088  SPFlags |= llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagLocalToUnit;
4089  if (CGM.getLangOpts().Optimize)
4090  SPFlags |= llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagOptimized;
4091 
4092  if (Stub) {
4093  Flags |= getCallSiteRelatedAttrs();
4094  SPFlags |= llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagDefinition;
4095  return DBuilder.createFunction(
4096  DContext, Name, LinkageName, Unit, Line,
4097  getOrCreateFunctionType(GD.getDecl(), FnType, Unit), 0, Flags, SPFlags,
4098  TParamsArray.get(), getFunctionDeclaration(FD));
4099  }
4100 
4101  llvm::DISubprogram *SP = DBuilder.createTempFunctionFwdDecl(
4102  DContext, Name, LinkageName, Unit, Line,
4103  getOrCreateFunctionType(GD.getDecl(), FnType, Unit), 0, Flags, SPFlags,
4104  TParamsArray.get(), getFunctionDeclaration(FD));
4105  const FunctionDecl *CanonDecl = FD->getCanonicalDecl();
4106  FwdDeclReplaceMap.emplace_back(std::piecewise_construct,
4107  std::make_tuple(CanonDecl),
4108  std::make_tuple(SP));
4109  return SP;
4110 }
4111 
4112 llvm::DISubprogram *CGDebugInfo::getFunctionForwardDeclaration(GlobalDecl GD) {
4113  return getFunctionFwdDeclOrStub(GD, /* Stub = */ false);
4114 }
4115 
4116 llvm::DISubprogram *CGDebugInfo::getFunctionStub(GlobalDecl GD) {
4117  return getFunctionFwdDeclOrStub(GD, /* Stub = */ true);
4118 }
