4120 llvm::DIGlobalVariable *
4121 CGDebugInfo::getGlobalVariableForwardDeclaration(const VarDecl *VD) {
4122  QualType T;
4123  StringRef Name, LinkageName;
4124  SourceLocation Loc = VD->getLocation();
4125  llvm::DIFile *Unit = getOrCreateFile(Loc);
4126  llvm::DIScope *DContext = Unit;
4127  unsigned Line = getLineNumber(Loc);
4128  llvm::MDTuple *TemplateParameters = nullptr;
4129 
4130  collectVarDeclProps(VD, Unit, Line, T, Name, LinkageName, TemplateParameters,
4131  DContext);
4132  auto Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(VD, CGM.getContext());
4133  auto *GV = DBuilder.createTempGlobalVariableFwdDecl(
4134  DContext, Name, LinkageName, Unit, Line, getOrCreateType(T, Unit),
4135  !VD->isExternallyVisible(), nullptr, TemplateParameters, Align);
4136  FwdDeclReplaceMap.emplace_back(
4137  std::piecewise_construct,
4138  std::make_tuple(cast<VarDecl>(VD->getCanonicalDecl())),
4139  std::make_tuple(static_cast<llvm::Metadata *>(GV)));
4140  return GV;
4141 }
4142 
4143 llvm::DINode *CGDebugInfo::getDeclarationOrDefinition(const Decl *D) {
4144  // We only need a declaration (not a definition) of the type - so use whatever
4145  // we would otherwise do to get a type for a pointee. (forward declarations in
4146  // limited debug info, full definitions (if the type definition is available)
4147  // in unlimited debug info)
4148  if (const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypeDecl>(D))
4149  return getOrCreateType(CGM.getContext().getTypeDeclType(TD),
4150  getOrCreateFile(TD->getLocation()));
4151  auto I = DeclCache.find(D->getCanonicalDecl());
4152 
4153  if (I != DeclCache.end()) {
4154  auto N = I->second;
4155  if (auto *GVE = dyn_cast_or_null<llvm::DIGlobalVariableExpression>(N))
4156  return GVE->getVariable();
4157  return cast<llvm::DINode>(N);
4158  }
4159 
4160  // Search imported declaration cache if it is already defined
4161  // as imported declaration.
4162  auto IE = ImportedDeclCache.find(D->getCanonicalDecl());
4163 
4164  if (IE != ImportedDeclCache.end()) {
4165  auto N = IE->second;
4166  if (auto *GVE = dyn_cast_or_null<llvm::DIImportedEntity>(N))
4167  return cast<llvm::DINode>(GVE);
4168  return dyn_cast_or_null<llvm::DINode>(N);
4169  }
4170 
4171  // No definition for now. Emit a forward definition that might be
4172  // merged with a potential upcoming definition.
4173  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D))
4174  return getFunctionForwardDeclaration(FD);
4175  else if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D))
4176  return getGlobalVariableForwardDeclaration(VD);
4177 
4178  return nullptr;
4179 }
4180 
4181 llvm::DISubprogram *CGDebugInfo::getFunctionDeclaration(const Decl *D) {
4182  if (!D || DebugKind <= llvm::codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly)
4183  return nullptr;
4184 
4185  const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
4186  if (!FD)
4187  return nullptr;
4188 
4189  // Setup context.
4190  auto *S = getDeclContextDescriptor(D);
4191 
4192  auto MI = SPCache.find(FD->getCanonicalDecl());
4193  if (MI == SPCache.end()) {
4194  if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD->getCanonicalDecl())) {
4195  return CreateCXXMemberFunction(MD, getOrCreateFile(MD->getLocation()),
4196  cast<llvm::DICompositeType>(S));
4197  }
4198  }
4199  if (MI != SPCache.end()) {
4200  auto *SP = dyn_cast_or_null<llvm::DISubprogram>(MI->second);
4201  if (SP && !SP->isDefinition())
4202  return SP;
4203  }
4204 
4205  for (auto *NextFD : FD->redecls()) {
4206  auto MI = SPCache.find(NextFD->getCanonicalDecl());
4207  if (MI != SPCache.end()) {
4208  auto *SP = dyn_cast_or_null<llvm::DISubprogram>(MI->second);
4209  if (SP && !SP->isDefinition())
4210  return SP;
4211  }
4212  }
4213  return nullptr;
4214 }
4215 
4216 llvm::DISubprogram *CGDebugInfo::getObjCMethodDeclaration(
4217  const Decl *D, llvm::DISubroutineType *FnType, unsigned LineNo,
4218  llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags, llvm::DISubprogram::DISPFlags SPFlags) {
4219  if (!D || DebugKind <= llvm::codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly)
4220  return nullptr;
4221 
4222  const auto *OMD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D);
4223  if (!OMD)
4224  return nullptr;
4225 
4226  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DwarfVersion < 5 && !OMD->isDirectMethod())
4227  return nullptr;
4228 
4229  if (OMD->isDirectMethod())
4230  SPFlags |= llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagObjCDirect;
4231 
4232  // Starting with DWARF V5 method declarations are emitted as children of
4233  // the interface type.
4234  auto *ID = dyn_cast_or_null<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(D->getDeclContext());
4235  if (!ID)
4236  ID = OMD->getClassInterface();
4237  if (!ID)
4238  return nullptr;
4239  QualType QTy(ID->getTypeForDecl(), 0);
4240  auto It = TypeCache.find(QTy.getAsOpaquePtr());
4241  if (It == TypeCache.end())
4242  return nullptr;
4243  auto *InterfaceType = cast<llvm::DICompositeType>(It->second);
4244  llvm::DISubprogram *FD = DBuilder.createFunction(
4245  InterfaceType, getObjCMethodName(OMD), StringRef(),
4246  InterfaceType->getFile(), LineNo, FnType, LineNo, Flags, SPFlags);
4247  DBuilder.finalizeSubprogram(FD);
4248  ObjCMethodCache[ID].push_back({FD, OMD->isDirectMethod()});
4249  return FD;
4250 }
4251 
4252 // getOrCreateFunctionType - Construct type. If it is a c++ method, include
4253 // implicit parameter "this".
4254 llvm::DISubroutineType *CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateFunctionType(const Decl *D,
4255  QualType FnType,
4256  llvm::DIFile *F) {
4257  // In CodeView, we emit the function types in line tables only because the
4258  // only way to distinguish between functions is by display name and type.
4259  if (!D || (DebugKind <= llvm::codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly &&
4260  !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCodeView))
4261  // Create fake but valid subroutine type. Otherwise -verify would fail, and
4262  // subprogram DIE will miss DW_AT_decl_file and DW_AT_decl_line fields.
4263  return DBuilder.createSubroutineType(
4264  DBuilder.getOrCreateTypeArray(std::nullopt));
4265 
4266  if (const auto *Method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(D))
4267  return getOrCreateMethodType(Method, F);
4268 
4269  const auto *FTy = FnType->getAs<FunctionType>();
4270  CallingConv CC = FTy ? FTy->getCallConv() : CallingConv::CC_C;
4271 
4272  if (const auto *OMethod = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)) {
4273  // Add "self" and "_cmd"
4274  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 16> Elts;
4275 
4276  // First element is always return type. For 'void' functions it is NULL.
4277  QualType ResultTy = OMethod->getReturnType();
4278 
4279  // Replace the instancetype keyword with the actual type.
4280  if (ResultTy == CGM.getContext().getObjCInstanceType())
4281  ResultTy = CGM.getContext().getPointerType(
4282  QualType(OMethod->getClassInterface()->getTypeForDecl(), 0));
4283 
4284  Elts.push_back(getOrCreateType(ResultTy, F));
4285  // "self" pointer is always first argument.
4286  QualType SelfDeclTy;
4287  if (auto *SelfDecl = OMethod->getSelfDecl())
4288  SelfDeclTy = SelfDecl->getType();
4289  else if (auto *FPT = dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(FnType))
4290  if (FPT->getNumParams() > 1)
4291  SelfDeclTy = FPT->getParamType(0);
4292  if (!SelfDeclTy.isNull())
4293  Elts.push_back(
4294  CreateSelfType(SelfDeclTy, getOrCreateType(SelfDeclTy, F)));
4295  // "_cmd" pointer is always second argument.
4296  Elts.push_back(DBuilder.createArtificialType(
4297  getOrCreateType(CGM.getContext().getObjCSelType(), F)));
4298  // Get rest of the arguments.
4299  for (const auto *PI : OMethod->parameters())
4300  Elts.push_back(getOrCreateType(PI->getType(), F));
4301  // Variadic methods need a special marker at the end of the type list.
4302  if (OMethod->isVariadic())
4303  Elts.push_back(DBuilder.createUnspecifiedParameter());
4304 
4305  llvm::DITypeRefArray EltTypeArray = DBuilder.getOrCreateTypeArray(Elts);
4306  return DBuilder.createSubroutineType(EltTypeArray, llvm::DINode::FlagZero,
4307  getDwarfCC(CC));
4308  }
4309 
4310  // Handle variadic function types; they need an additional
4311  // unspecified parameter.
4312  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D))
4313  if (FD->isVariadic()) {
4314  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 16> EltTys;
4315  EltTys.push_back(getOrCreateType(FD->getReturnType(), F));
4316  if (const auto *FPT = dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(FnType))
4317  for (QualType ParamType : FPT->param_types())
4318  EltTys.push_back(getOrCreateType(ParamType, F));
4319  EltTys.push_back(DBuilder.createUnspecifiedParameter());
4320  llvm::DITypeRefArray EltTypeArray = DBuilder.getOrCreateTypeArray(EltTys);
4321  return DBuilder.createSubroutineType(EltTypeArray, llvm::DINode::FlagZero,
4322  getDwarfCC(CC));
4323  }
4324 
4325  return cast<llvm::DISubroutineType>(getOrCreateType(FnType, F));
4326 }
4327 
4328 QualType
4329 CGDebugInfo::getFunctionType(const FunctionDecl *FD, QualType RetTy,
4330  const SmallVectorImpl<const VarDecl *> &Args) {
4331  CallingConv CC = CallingConv::CC_C;
4332  if (FD)
4333  if (const auto *SrcFnTy = FD->getType()->getAs<FunctionType>())
4334  CC = SrcFnTy->getCallConv();
4335  SmallVector<QualType, 16> ArgTypes;
4336  for (const VarDecl *VD : Args)
4337  ArgTypes.push_back(VD->getType());
4338  return CGM.getContext().getFunctionType(RetTy, ArgTypes,
4339  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo(CC));
4340 }
4341 
4342 void CGDebugInfo::emitFunctionStart(GlobalDecl GD, SourceLocation Loc,
4343  SourceLocation ScopeLoc, QualType FnType,
4344  llvm::Function *Fn, bool CurFuncIsThunk) {
4345  StringRef Name;
4346  StringRef LinkageName;
4347 
4348  FnBeginRegionCount.push_back(LexicalBlockStack.size());
4349 
4350  const Decl *D = GD.getDecl();
4351  bool HasDecl = (D != nullptr);
4352 
4353  llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
4354  llvm::DISubprogram::DISPFlags SPFlags = llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagZero;
4355  llvm::DIFile *Unit = getOrCreateFile(Loc);
4356  llvm::DIScope *FDContext = Unit;
4357  llvm::DINodeArray TParamsArray;
4358  if (!HasDecl) {
4359  // Use llvm function name.
4360  LinkageName = Fn->getName();
4361  } else if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
4362  // If there is a subprogram for this function available then use it.
4363  auto FI = SPCache.find(FD->getCanonicalDecl());
4364  if (FI != SPCache.end()) {
4365  auto *SP = dyn_cast_or_null<llvm::DISubprogram>(FI->second);
4366  if (SP && SP->isDefinition()) {
4367  LexicalBlockStack.emplace_back(SP);
4368  RegionMap[D].reset(SP);
4369  return;
4370  }
4371  }
4372  collectFunctionDeclProps(GD, Unit, Name, LinkageName, FDContext,
4373  TParamsArray, Flags);
4374  } else if (const auto *OMD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)) {
4375  Name = getObjCMethodName(OMD);
4376  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagPrototyped;
4377  } else if (isa<VarDecl>(D) &&
4378  GD.getDynamicInitKind() != DynamicInitKind::NoStub) {
4379  // This is a global initializer or atexit destructor for a global variable.
4380  Name = getDynamicInitializerName(cast<VarDecl>(D), GD.getDynamicInitKind(),
4381  Fn);
4382  } else {
4383  Name = Fn->getName();
4384 
4385  if (isa<BlockDecl>(D))
4386  LinkageName = Name;
4387 
4388  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagPrototyped;
4389  }
4390  if (Name.starts_with("\01"))
4391  Name = Name.substr(1);
4392 
4393  assert((!D || !isa<VarDecl>(D) ||
4394  GD.getDynamicInitKind() != DynamicInitKind::NoStub) &&
4395  "Unexpected DynamicInitKind !");
4396 
4397  if (!HasDecl || D->isImplicit() || D->hasAttr<ArtificialAttr>() ||
4398  isa<VarDecl>(D) || isa<CapturedDecl>(D)) {
4399  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagArtificial;
4400  // Artificial functions should not silently reuse CurLoc.
4401  CurLoc = SourceLocation();
4402  }
4403 
4404  if (CurFuncIsThunk)
4405  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagThunk;
4406 
4407  if (Fn->hasLocalLinkage())
4408  SPFlags |= llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagLocalToUnit;
4409  if (CGM.getLangOpts().Optimize)
4410  SPFlags |= llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagOptimized;
4411 
4412  llvm::DINode::DIFlags FlagsForDef = Flags | getCallSiteRelatedAttrs();
4413  llvm::DISubprogram::DISPFlags SPFlagsForDef =
4414  SPFlags | llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagDefinition;
4415 
4416  const unsigned LineNo = getLineNumber(Loc.isValid() ? Loc : CurLoc);
4417  unsigned ScopeLine = getLineNumber(ScopeLoc);
4418  llvm::DISubroutineType *DIFnType = getOrCreateFunctionType(D, FnType, Unit);
4419  llvm::DISubprogram *Decl = nullptr;
4420  llvm::DINodeArray Annotations = nullptr;
4421  if (D) {
4422  Decl = isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)
4423  ? getObjCMethodDeclaration(D, DIFnType, LineNo, Flags, SPFlags)
4424  : getFunctionDeclaration(D);
4425  Annotations = CollectBTFDeclTagAnnotations(D);
4426  }
4427 
4428  // FIXME: The function declaration we're constructing here is mostly reusing
4429  // declarations from CXXMethodDecl and not constructing new ones for arbitrary
4430  // FunctionDecls. When/if we fix this we can have FDContext be TheCU/null for
4431  // all subprograms instead of the actual context since subprogram definitions
4432  // are emitted as CU level entities by the backend.
4433  llvm::DISubprogram *SP = DBuilder.createFunction(
4434  FDContext, Name, LinkageName, Unit, LineNo, DIFnType, ScopeLine,
4435  FlagsForDef, SPFlagsForDef, TParamsArray.get(), Decl, nullptr,
4436  Annotations);
4437  Fn->setSubprogram(SP);
4438  // We might get here with a VarDecl in the case we're generating
4439  // code for the initialization of globals. Do not record these decls
4440  // as they will overwrite the actual VarDecl Decl in the cache.
4441  if (HasDecl && isa<FunctionDecl>(D))
4442  DeclCache[D->getCanonicalDecl()].reset(SP);
4443 
4444  // Push the function onto the lexical block stack.
4445  LexicalBlockStack.emplace_back(SP);
4446 
4447  if (HasDecl)
4448  RegionMap[D].reset(SP);
4449 }
4450 
4451 void CGDebugInfo::EmitFunctionDecl(GlobalDecl GD, SourceLocation Loc,
4452  QualType FnType, llvm::Function *Fn) {
4453  StringRef Name;
4454  StringRef LinkageName;
4455 
4456  const Decl *D = GD.getDecl();
4457  if (!D)
4458  return;
4459 
4460  llvm::TimeTraceScope TimeScope("DebugFunction", [&]() {
4461  return GetName(D, true);
4462  });
4463 
4464  llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
4465  llvm::DIFile *Unit = getOrCreateFile(Loc);
4466  bool IsDeclForCallSite = Fn ? true : false;
4467  llvm::DIScope *FDContext =
4468  IsDeclForCallSite ? Unit : getDeclContextDescriptor(D);
4469  llvm::DINodeArray TParamsArray;
4470  if (isa<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
4471  // If there is a DISubprogram for this function available then use it.
4472  collectFunctionDeclProps(GD, Unit, Name, LinkageName, FDContext,
4473  TParamsArray, Flags);
4474  } else if (const auto *OMD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)) {
4475  Name = getObjCMethodName(OMD);
4476  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagPrototyped;
4477  } else {
4478  llvm_unreachable("not a function or ObjC method");
4479  }
4480  if (!Name.empty() && Name[0] == '\01')
4481  Name = Name.substr(1);
4482 
4483  if (D->isImplicit()) {
4484  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagArtificial;
4485  // Artificial functions without a location should not silently reuse CurLoc.
4486  if (Loc.isInvalid())
4487  CurLoc = SourceLocation();
4488  }
4489  unsigned LineNo = getLineNumber(Loc);
4490  unsigned ScopeLine = 0;
4491  llvm::DISubprogram::DISPFlags SPFlags = llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagZero;
4492  if (CGM.getLangOpts().Optimize)
4493  SPFlags |= llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagOptimized;
4494 
4495  llvm::DINodeArray Annotations = CollectBTFDeclTagAnnotations(D);
4496  llvm::DISubroutineType *STy = getOrCreateFunctionType(D, FnType, Unit);
4497  llvm::DISubprogram *SP = DBuilder.createFunction(
4498  FDContext, Name, LinkageName, Unit, LineNo, STy, ScopeLine, Flags,
4499  SPFlags, TParamsArray.get(), nullptr, nullptr, Annotations);
4500 
4501  // Preserve btf_decl_tag attributes for parameters of extern functions
4502  // for BPF target. The parameters created in this loop are attached as
4503  // DISubprogram's retainedNodes in the subsequent finalizeSubprogram call.
4504  if (IsDeclForCallSite && CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isBPF()) {
4505  if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
4506  llvm::DITypeRefArray ParamTypes = STy->getTypeArray();
4507  unsigned ArgNo = 1;
4508  for (ParmVarDecl *PD : FD->parameters()) {
4509  llvm::DINodeArray ParamAnnotations = CollectBTFDeclTagAnnotations(PD);
4510  DBuilder.createParameterVariable(
4511  SP, PD->getName(), ArgNo, Unit, LineNo, ParamTypes[ArgNo], true,
4512  llvm::DINode::FlagZero, ParamAnnotations);
4513  ++ArgNo;
4514  }
4515  }
4516  }
4517 
4518  if (IsDeclForCallSite)
4519  Fn->setSubprogram(SP);
4520 
4521  DBuilder.finalizeSubprogram(SP);
4522 }
4523 
4524 void CGDebugInfo::EmitFuncDeclForCallSite(llvm::CallBase *CallOrInvoke,
4525  QualType CalleeType,
4526  const FunctionDecl *CalleeDecl) {
4527  if (!CallOrInvoke)
4528  return;
4529  auto *Func = CallOrInvoke->getCalledFunction();
4530  if (!Func)
4531  return;
4532  if (Func->getSubprogram())
4533  return;
4534 
4535  // Do not emit a declaration subprogram for a function with nodebug
4536  // attribute, or if call site info isn't required.
4537  if (CalleeDecl->hasAttr<NoDebugAttr>() ||
4538  noSystemDebugInfo(CalleeDecl, CGM) ||
4539  getCallSiteRelatedAttrs() == llvm::DINode::FlagZero)
4540  return;
4541 
4542  // If there is no DISubprogram attached to the function being called,
4543  // create the one describing the function in order to have complete
4544  // call site debug info.
4545  if (!CalleeDecl->isStatic() && !CalleeDecl->isInlined())
4546  EmitFunctionDecl(CalleeDecl, CalleeDecl->getLocation(), CalleeType, Func);
4547 }
4548 
4549 void CGDebugInfo::EmitInlineFunctionStart(CGBuilderTy &Builder, GlobalDecl GD) {
4550  const auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
4551  // If there is a subprogram for this function available then use it.
4552  auto FI = SPCache.find(FD->getCanonicalDecl());
4553  llvm::DISubprogram *SP = nullptr;
4554  if (FI != SPCache.end())
4555  SP = dyn_cast_or_null<llvm::DISubprogram>(FI->second);
4556  if (!SP || !SP->isDefinition())
4557  SP = getFunctionStub(GD);
4558  FnBeginRegionCount.push_back(LexicalBlockStack.size());
4559  LexicalBlockStack.emplace_back(SP);
4560  setInlinedAt(Builder.getCurrentDebugLocation());
4561  EmitLocation(Builder, FD->getLocation());
4562 }
4563 
4564 void CGDebugInfo::EmitInlineFunctionEnd(CGBuilderTy &Builder) {
4565  assert(CurInlinedAt && "unbalanced inline scope stack");
4566  EmitFunctionEnd(Builder, nullptr);
4567  setInlinedAt(llvm::DebugLoc(CurInlinedAt).getInlinedAt());
4568 }
4569 
4570 void CGDebugInfo::EmitLocation(CGBuilderTy &Builder, SourceLocation Loc) {
4571  // Update our current location
4572  setLocation(Loc);
4573 
4574  if (CurLoc.isInvalid() || CurLoc.isMacroID() || LexicalBlockStack.empty())
4575  return;
4576 
4577  llvm::MDNode *Scope = LexicalBlockStack.back();
4578  Builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(
4579  llvm::DILocation::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), getLineNumber(CurLoc),
4580  getColumnNumber(CurLoc), Scope, CurInlinedAt));
4581 }
4582 
4583 void CGDebugInfo::CreateLexicalBlock(SourceLocation Loc) {
4584  llvm::MDNode *Back = nullptr;
4585  if (!LexicalBlockStack.empty())
4586  Back = LexicalBlockStack.back().get();
4587  LexicalBlockStack.emplace_back(DBuilder.createLexicalBlock(
4588  cast<llvm::DIScope>(Back), getOrCreateFile(CurLoc), getLineNumber(CurLoc),
4589  getColumnNumber(CurLoc)));
4590 }
4591 
4592 void CGDebugInfo::AppendAddressSpaceXDeref(
4593  unsigned AddressSpace, SmallVectorImpl<uint64_t> &Expr) const {
4594  std::optional<unsigned> DWARFAddressSpace =
4595  CGM.getTarget().getDWARFAddressSpace(AddressSpace);
4596  if (!DWARFAddressSpace)
4597  return;
4598 
4599  Expr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_constu);
4600  Expr.push_back(*DWARFAddressSpace);
4601  Expr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_swap);
4602  Expr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_xderef);
4603 }
4604 
4605 void CGDebugInfo::EmitLexicalBlockStart(CGBuilderTy &Builder,
4606  SourceLocation Loc) {
4607  // Set our current location.
4608  setLocation(Loc);
4609 
4610  // Emit a line table change for the current location inside the new scope.
4611  Builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(llvm::DILocation::get(
4612  CGM.getLLVMContext(), getLineNumber(Loc), getColumnNumber(Loc),
4613  LexicalBlockStack.back(), CurInlinedAt));
4614 
4615  if (DebugKind <= llvm::codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly)
4616  return;
4617 
4618  // Create a new lexical block and push it on the stack.
4619  CreateLexicalBlock(Loc);
4620 }
4621 
4622 void CGDebugInfo::EmitLexicalBlockEnd(CGBuilderTy &Builder,
4623  SourceLocation Loc) {
4624  assert(!LexicalBlockStack.empty() && "Region stack mismatch, stack empty!");
4625 
4626  // Provide an entry in the line table for the end of the block.
4627  EmitLocation(Builder, Loc);
4628 
4629  if (DebugKind <= llvm::codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly)
4630  return;
4631 
4632  LexicalBlockStack.pop_back();
4633 }
4634 
4635 void CGDebugInfo::EmitFunctionEnd(CGBuilderTy &Builder, llvm::Function *Fn) {
4636  assert(!LexicalBlockStack.empty() && "Region stack mismatch, stack empty!");
4637  unsigned RCount = FnBeginRegionCount.back();
4638  assert(RCount <= LexicalBlockStack.size() && "Region stack mismatch");
4639 
4640  // Pop all regions for this function.
4641  while (LexicalBlockStack.size() != RCount) {
4642  // Provide an entry in the line table for the end of the block.
4643  EmitLocation(Builder, CurLoc);
4644  LexicalBlockStack.pop_back();
4645  }
4646  FnBeginRegionCount.pop_back();
4647 
4648  if (Fn && Fn->getSubprogram())
4649  DBuilder.finalizeSubprogram(Fn->getSubprogram());
4650 }
4651 
4652 CGDebugInfo::BlockByRefType
4653 CGDebugInfo::EmitTypeForVarWithBlocksAttr(const VarDecl *VD,
4654  uint64_t *XOffset) {
4655  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 5> EltTys;
4656  QualType FType;
4657  uint64_t FieldSize, FieldOffset;
4658  uint32_t FieldAlign;
4659 
4660  llvm::DIFile *Unit = getOrCreateFile(VD->getLocation());
4661  QualType Type = VD->getType();
4662 
4663  FieldOffset = 0;
4664  FType = CGM.getContext().getPointerType(CGM.getContext().VoidTy);
4665  EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__isa", &FieldOffset));
4666  EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__forwarding", &FieldOffset));
4667  FType = CGM.getContext().IntTy;
4668  EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__flags", &FieldOffset));
4669  EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__size", &FieldOffset));
4670 
4671  bool HasCopyAndDispose = CGM.getContext().BlockRequiresCopying(Type, VD);
4672  if (HasCopyAndDispose) {
4673  FType = CGM.getContext().getPointerType(CGM.getContext().VoidTy);
4674  EltTys.push_back(
4675  CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__copy_helper", &FieldOffset));
4676  EltTys.push_back(
4677  CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__destroy_helper", &FieldOffset));
4678  }
4679  bool HasByrefExtendedLayout;
4680  Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime Lifetime;
4681  if (CGM.getContext().getByrefLifetime(Type, Lifetime,
4682  HasByrefExtendedLayout) &&
4683  HasByrefExtendedLayout) {
4684  FType = CGM.getContext().getPointerType(CGM.getContext().VoidTy);
4685  EltTys.push_back(
4686  CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__byref_variable_layout", &FieldOffset));
4687  }
4688 
4689  CharUnits Align = CGM.getContext().getDeclAlign(VD);
4690  if (Align > CGM.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(
4691  CGM.getTarget().getPointerAlign(LangAS::Default))) {
4692  CharUnits FieldOffsetInBytes =
4693  CGM.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(FieldOffset);
4694  CharUnits AlignedOffsetInBytes = FieldOffsetInBytes.alignTo(Align);
4695  CharUnits NumPaddingBytes = AlignedOffsetInBytes - FieldOffsetInBytes;
4696 
4697  if (NumPaddingBytes.isPositive()) {
4698  llvm::APInt pad(32, NumPaddingBytes.getQuantity());
4699  FType = CGM.getContext().getConstantArrayType(
4700  CGM.getContext().CharTy, pad, nullptr, ArraySizeModifier::Normal, 0);
4701  EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "", &FieldOffset));
4702  }
4703  }
4704 
4705  FType = Type;
4706  llvm::DIType *WrappedTy = getOrCreateType(FType, Unit);
4707  FieldSize = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(FType);
4708  FieldAlign = CGM.getContext().toBits(Align);
4709 
4710  *XOffset = FieldOffset;
4711  llvm::DIType *FieldTy = DBuilder.createMemberType(
4712  Unit, VD->getName(), Unit, 0, FieldSize, FieldAlign, FieldOffset,
4713  llvm::DINode::FlagZero, WrappedTy);
4714  EltTys.push_back(FieldTy);
4715  FieldOffset += FieldSize;
4716 
4717  llvm::DINodeArray Elements = DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(EltTys);
4718  return {DBuilder.createStructType(Unit, "", Unit, 0, FieldOffset, 0,
4719  llvm::DINode::FlagZero, nullptr, Elements),
4720  WrappedTy};
4721 }
4722 
4723 llvm::DILocalVariable *CGDebugInfo::EmitDeclare(const VarDecl *VD,
4724  llvm::Value *Storage,
4725  std::optional<unsigned> ArgNo,
4726  CGBuilderTy &Builder,
4727  const bool UsePointerValue) {
4728  assert(CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo());
4729  assert(!LexicalBlockStack.empty() && "Region stack mismatch, stack empty!");
4730  if (VD->hasAttr<NoDebugAttr>() || noSystemDebugInfo(VD, CGM))
4731  return nullptr;
4732 
4733  bool Unwritten =
4734  VD->isImplicit() || (isa<Decl>(VD->getDeclContext()) &&
4735  cast<Decl>(VD->getDeclContext())->isImplicit());
4736  llvm::DIFile *Unit = nullptr;
4737  if (!Unwritten)
4738  Unit = getOrCreateFile(VD->getLocation());
4739  llvm::DIType *Ty;
4740  uint64_t XOffset = 0;
4741  if (VD->hasAttr<BlocksAttr>())
4742  Ty = EmitTypeForVarWithBlocksAttr(VD, &XOffset).WrappedType;
4743  else
4744  Ty = getOrCreateType(VD->getType(), Unit);
4745 
4746  // If there is no debug info for this type then do not emit debug info
4747  // for this variable.
4748  if (!Ty)
4749  return nullptr;
4750 
4751  // Get location information.
4752  unsigned Line = 0;
4753  unsigned Column = 0;
4754  if (!Unwritten) {
4755  Line = getLineNumber(VD->getLocation());
4756  Column = getColumnNumber(VD->getLocation());
4757  }
4758  SmallVector<uint64_t, 13> Expr;
4759  llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
4760  if (VD->isImplicit())
4761  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagArtificial;
4762 
4763  auto Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(VD, CGM.getContext());
4764 
4765  unsigned AddressSpace = CGM.getTypes().getTargetAddressSpace(VD->getType());
4766  AppendAddressSpaceXDeref(AddressSpace, Expr);
4767 
4768  // If this is implicit parameter of CXXThis or ObjCSelf kind, then give it an
4769  // object pointer flag.
4770  if (const auto *IPD = dyn_cast<ImplicitParamDecl>(VD)) {
4771  if (IPD->getParameterKind() == ImplicitParamKind::CXXThis ||
4772  IPD->getParameterKind() == ImplicitParamKind::ObjCSelf)
4773  Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagObjectPointer;
4774  }
4775 
4776  // Note: Older versions of clang used to emit byval references with an extra
4777  // DW_OP_deref, because they referenced the IR arg directly instead of
4778  // referencing an alloca. Newer versions of LLVM don't treat allocas
4779  // differently from other function arguments when used in a dbg.declare.
4780  auto *Scope = cast<llvm::DIScope>(LexicalBlockStack.back());
4781  StringRef Name = VD->getName();
4782  if (!Name.empty()) {
4783  // __block vars are stored on the heap if they are captured by a block that
4784  // can escape the local scope.
4785  if (VD->isEscapingByref()) {
4786  // Here, we need an offset *into* the alloca.
4787  CharUnits offset = CharUnits::fromQuantity(32);
4788  Expr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_plus_uconst);
4789  // offset of __forwarding field
4790  offset = CGM.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(
4791  CGM.getTarget().getPointerWidth(LangAS::Default));
4792  Expr.push_back(offset.getQuantity());
4793  Expr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_deref);
4794  Expr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_plus_uconst);
4795  // offset of x field
4796  offset = CGM.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(XOffset);
4797  Expr.push_back(offset.getQuantity());
4798  }
4799  } else if (const auto *RT = dyn_cast<RecordType>(VD->getType())) {
4800  // If VD is an anonymous union then Storage represents value for
4801  // all union fields.
4802  const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
4803  if (RD->isUnion() && RD->isAnonymousStructOrUnion()) {
4804  // GDB has trouble finding local variables in anonymous unions, so we emit
4805  // artificial local variables for each of the members.
4806  //
4807  // FIXME: Remove this code as soon as GDB supports this.
4808  // The debug info verifier in LLVM operates based on the assumption that a
4809  // variable has the same size as its storage and we had to disable the
4810  // check for artificial variables.
4811  for (const auto *Field : RD->fields()) {
4812  llvm::DIType *FieldTy = getOrCreateType(Field->getType(), Unit);
4813  StringRef FieldName = Field->getName();
4814 
4815  // Ignore unnamed fields. Do not ignore unnamed records.
4816  if (FieldName.empty() && !isa<RecordType>(Field->getType()))
4817  continue;
4818 
4819  // Use VarDecl's Tag, Scope and Line number.
4820  auto FieldAlign = getDeclAlignIfRequired(Field, CGM.getContext());
4821  auto *D = DBuilder.createAutoVariable(
4822  Scope, FieldName, Unit, Line, FieldTy, CGM.getLangOpts().Optimize,
4823  Flags | llvm::DINode::FlagArtificial, FieldAlign);
4824 
4825  // Insert an llvm.dbg.declare into the current block.
4826  DBuilder.insertDeclare(Storage, D, DBuilder.createExpression(Expr),
4827  llvm::DILocation::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), Line,
4828  Column, Scope,
4829  CurInlinedAt),
4830  Builder.GetInsertBlock());
4831  }
4832  }
4833  }
4834 
4835  // Clang stores the sret pointer provided by the caller in a static alloca.
4836  // Use DW_OP_deref to tell the debugger to load the pointer and treat it as
4837  // the address of the variable.
4838  if (UsePointerValue) {
4839  assert(!llvm::is_contained(Expr, llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_deref) &&
4840  "Debug info already contains DW_OP_deref.");
4841  Expr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_deref);
4842  }
4843 
4844  // Create the descriptor for the variable.
4845  llvm::DILocalVariable *D = nullptr;
4846  if (ArgNo) {
4847  llvm::DINodeArray Annotations = CollectBTFDeclTagAnnotations(VD);
4848  D = DBuilder.createParameterVariable(Scope, Name, *ArgNo, Unit, Line, Ty,
4849  CGM.getLangOpts().Optimize, Flags,
4850  Annotations);
4851  } else {
4852  // For normal local variable, we will try to find out whether 'VD' is the
4853  // copy parameter of coroutine.
4854  // If yes, we are going to use DIVariable of the origin parameter instead
4855  // of creating the new one.
4856  // If no, it might be a normal alloc, we just create a new one for it.
4857 
4858  // Check whether the VD is move parameters.
4859  auto RemapCoroArgToLocalVar = [&]() -> llvm::DILocalVariable * {
4860  // The scope of parameter and move-parameter should be distinct
4861  // DISubprogram.
4862  if (!isa<llvm::DISubprogram>(Scope) || !Scope->isDistinct())
4863  return nullptr;
4864 
4865  auto Iter = llvm::find_if(CoroutineParameterMappings, [&](auto &Pair) {
4866  Stmt *StmtPtr = const_cast<Stmt *>(Pair.second);
4867  if (DeclStmt *DeclStmtPtr = dyn_cast<DeclStmt>(StmtPtr)) {
4868  DeclGroupRef DeclGroup = DeclStmtPtr->getDeclGroup();
4869  Decl *Decl = DeclGroup.getSingleDecl();
4870  if (VD == dyn_cast_or_null<VarDecl>(Decl))
4871  return true;
4872  }
4873  return false;
4874  });
4875 
4876  if (Iter != CoroutineParameterMappings.end()) {
4877  ParmVarDecl *PD = const_cast<ParmVarDecl *>(Iter->first);
4878  auto Iter2 = llvm::find_if(ParamDbgMappings, [&](auto &DbgPair) {
4879  return DbgPair.first == PD && DbgPair.second->getScope() == Scope;
4880  });
4881  if (Iter2 != ParamDbgMappings.end())
4882  return const_cast<llvm::DILocalVariable *>(Iter2->second);
4883  }
4884  return nullptr;
4885  };
4886 
4887  // If we couldn't find a move param DIVariable, create a new one.
4888  D = RemapCoroArgToLocalVar();
4889  // Or we will create a new DIVariable for this Decl if D dose not exists.
4890  if (!D)
4891  D = DBuilder.createAutoVariable(Scope, Name, Unit, Line, Ty,
4892  CGM.getLangOpts().Optimize, Flags, Align);
4893  }
4894  // Insert an llvm.dbg.declare into the current block.
4895  DBuilder.insertDeclare(Storage, D, DBuilder.createExpression(Expr),
4896  llvm::DILocation::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), Line,
4897  Column, Scope, CurInlinedAt),
4898  Builder.GetInsertBlock());
4899 
4900  return D;
4901 }
4902 
4903 llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateBindingDeclType(const BindingDecl *BD) {
4904  llvm::DIFile *Unit = getOrCreateFile(BD->getLocation());
4905 
4906  // If the declaration is bound to a bitfield struct field, its type may have a
4907  // size that is different from its deduced declaration type's.
4908  if (const MemberExpr *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(BD->getBinding())) {
4909  if (const FieldDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(ME->getMemberDecl())) {
4910  if (FD->isBitField()) {
4911  ASTContext &Context = CGM.getContext();
4912  const CGRecordLayout &RL =
4913  CGM.getTypes().getCGRecordLayout(FD->getParent());
4914  const CGBitFieldInfo &Info = RL.getBitFieldInfo(FD);
4915 
4916  // Find an integer type with the same bitwidth as the bitfield size. If
4917  // no suitable type is present in the target, give up on producing debug
4918  // information as it would be wrong. It is certainly possible to produce
4919  // correct debug info, but the logic isn't currently implemented.
4920  uint64_t BitfieldSizeInBits = Info.Size;
4921  QualType IntTy =
4922  Context.getIntTypeForBitwidth(BitfieldSizeInBits, Info.IsSigned);
4923  if (IntTy.isNull())
4924  return nullptr;
4925  Qualifiers Quals = BD->getType().getQualifiers();
4926  QualType FinalTy = Context.getQualifiedType(IntTy, Quals);
4927  llvm::DIType *Ty = getOrCreateType(FinalTy, Unit);
4928  assert(Ty);
4929  return Ty;
4930  }
4931  }
4932  }
4933 
4934  return getOrCreateType(BD->getType(), Unit);
4935 }
4936 
4937 llvm::DILocalVariable *CGDebugInfo::EmitDeclare(const BindingDecl *BD,
4938  llvm::Value *Storage,
4939  std::optional<unsigned> ArgNo,
4940  CGBuilderTy &Builder,
4941  const bool UsePointerValue) {
4942  assert(CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo());
4943  assert(!LexicalBlockStack.empty() && "Region stack mismatch, stack empty!");
4944  if (BD->hasAttr<NoDebugAttr>() || noSystemDebugInfo(BD, CGM))
4945  return nullptr;
4946 
4947  // Skip the tuple like case, we don't handle that here
4948  if (isa<DeclRefExpr>(BD->getBinding()))
4949  return nullptr;
4950 
4951  llvm::DIType *Ty = CreateBindingDeclType(BD);
4952 
4953  // If there is no debug info for this type then do not emit debug info
4954  // for this variable.
4955  if (!Ty)
4956  return nullptr;
4957 
4958  auto Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(BD, CGM.getContext());
4959  unsigned AddressSpace = CGM.getTypes().getTargetAddressSpace(BD->getType());
4960 
4961  SmallVector<uint64_t, 3> Expr;
4962  AppendAddressSpaceXDeref(AddressSpace, Expr);
4963 
4964  // Clang stores the sret pointer provided by the caller in a static alloca.
4965  // Use DW_OP_deref to tell the debugger to load the pointer and treat it as
4966  // the address of the variable.
4967  if (UsePointerValue) {
4968  assert(!llvm::is_contained(Expr, llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_deref) &&
4969  "Debug info already contains DW_OP_deref.");
4970  Expr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_deref);
4971  }
4972 
4973  unsigned Line = getLineNumber(BD->getLocation());
4974  unsigned Column = getColumnNumber(BD->getLocation());
4975  StringRef Name = BD->getName();
4976  auto *Scope = cast<llvm::DIScope>(LexicalBlockStack.back());
4977  llvm::DIFile *Unit = getOrCreateFile(BD->getLocation());
4978  // Create the descriptor for the variable.
4979  llvm::DILocalVariable *D = DBuilder.createAutoVariable(
4980  Scope, Name, Unit, Line, Ty, CGM.getLangOpts().Optimize,
4981  llvm::DINode::FlagZero, Align);
4982 
4983  if (const MemberExpr *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(BD->getBinding())) {
4984  if (const FieldDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(ME->getMemberDecl())) {
4985  const unsigned fieldIndex = FD->getFieldIndex();
4986  const clang::CXXRecordDecl *parent =
4987  (const CXXRecordDecl *)FD->getParent();
4988  const ASTRecordLayout &layout =
4989  CGM.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(parent);
4990  const uint64_t fieldOffset = layout.getFieldOffset(fieldIndex);
4991 
4992  if (fieldOffset != 0) {
4993  // Currently if the field offset is not a multiple of byte, the produced
4994  // location would not be accurate. Therefore give up.
4995  if (fieldOffset % CGM.getContext().getCharWidth() != 0)
4996  return nullptr;
4997 
4998  Expr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_plus_uconst);
4999  Expr.push_back(
5000  CGM.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(fieldOffset).getQuantity());
5001  }
5002  }
5003  } else if (const ArraySubscriptExpr *ASE =
5004  dyn_cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(BD->getBinding())) {
5005  if (const IntegerLiteral *IL = dyn_cast<IntegerLiteral>(ASE->getIdx())) {
5006  const uint64_t value = IL->getValue().getZExtValue();
5007  const uint64_t typeSize = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(BD->getType());
5008 
5009  if (value != 0) {
5010  Expr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_plus_uconst);
5011  Expr.push_back(CGM.getContext()
5012  .toCharUnitsFromBits(value * typeSize)
5013  .getQuantity());
5014  }
5015  }
5016  }
5017 
5018  // Insert an llvm.dbg.declare into the current block.
5019  DBuilder.insertDeclare(Storage, D, DBuilder.createExpression(Expr),
5020  llvm::DILocation::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), Line,
5021  Column, Scope, CurInlinedAt),
5022  Builder.GetInsertBlock());
5023 
5024  return D;
5025 }
5026 
5027 llvm::DILocalVariable *
5028 CGDebugInfo::EmitDeclareOfAutoVariable(const VarDecl *VD, llvm::Value *Storage,
5029  CGBuilderTy &Builder,
5030  const bool UsePointerValue) {
5031  assert(CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo());
5032 
5033  if (auto *DD = dyn_cast<DecompositionDecl>(VD)) {
5034  for (auto *B : DD->bindings()) {
5035  EmitDeclare(B, Storage, std::nullopt, Builder,
5036  VD->getType()->isReferenceType());
5037  }
5038  // Don't emit an llvm.dbg.declare for the composite storage as it doesn't
5039  // correspond to a user variable.
5040  return nullptr;
5041  }
5042 
5043  return EmitDeclare(VD, Storage, std::nullopt, Builder, UsePointerValue);
5044 }

5046 void CGDebugInfo::EmitLabel(const LabelDecl *D, CGBuilderTy &Builder) {
5047  assert(CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo());
5048  assert(!LexicalBlockStack.empty() && "Region stack mismatch, stack empty!");
5049 
5050  if (D->hasAttr<NoDebugAttr>() || noSystemDebugInfo(D, CGM))
5051  return;
5052 
5053  auto *Scope = cast<llvm::DIScope>(LexicalBlockStack.back());
5054  llvm::DIFile *Unit = getOrCreateFile(D->getLocation());
5055 
5056  // Get location information.
5057  unsigned Line = getLineNumber(D->getLocation());
5058  unsigned Column = getColumnNumber(D->getLocation());
5059 
5060  StringRef Name = D->getName();
5061 
5062  // Create the descriptor for the label.
5063  auto *L =
5064  DBuilder.createLabel(Scope, Name, Unit, Line, CGM.getLangOpts().Optimize);
5065 
5066  // Insert an llvm.dbg.label into the current block.
5067  DBuilder.insertLabel(L,
5068  llvm::DILocation::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), Line, Column,
5069  Scope, CurInlinedAt),
5070  Builder.GetInsertBlock());
5071 }

5074  llvm::DIType *Ty) {

5080 
5081 void CGDebugInfo::EmitDeclareOfBlockDeclRefVariable(
5082  const VarDecl *VD, llvm::Value *Storage, CGBuilderTy &Builder,
5083  const CGBlockInfo &blockInfo, llvm::Instruction *InsertPoint) {
5084  assert(CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo());
5085  assert(!LexicalBlockStack.empty() && "Region stack mismatch, stack empty!");
5086 
5087  if (Builder.GetInsertBlock() == nullptr)
5088  return;
5089  if (VD->hasAttr<NoDebugAttr>() || noSystemDebugInfo(VD, CGM))
5090  return;
5091 
5092  bool isByRef = VD->hasAttr<BlocksAttr>();
5093 
5094  uint64_t XOffset = 0;
5095  llvm::DIFile *Unit = getOrCreateFile(VD->getLocation());
5096  llvm::DIType *Ty;
5097  if (isByRef)
5098  Ty = EmitTypeForVarWithBlocksAttr(VD, &XOffset).WrappedType;
5099  else
5100  Ty = getOrCreateType(VD->getType(), Unit);
5101 
5102  // Self is passed along as an implicit non-arg variable in a
5103  // block. Mark it as the object pointer.
5104  if (const auto *IPD = dyn_cast<ImplicitParamDecl>(VD))
5105  if (IPD->getParameterKind() == ImplicitParamKind::ObjCSelf)
5106  Ty = CreateSelfType(VD->getType(), Ty);
5107 
5108  // Get location information.
5109  const unsigned Line =
5110  getLineNumber(VD->getLocation().isValid() ? VD->getLocation() : CurLoc);
5111  unsigned Column = getColumnNumber(VD->getLocation());
5112 
5113  const llvm::DataLayout &target = CGM.getDataLayout();
5114 
5115  CharUnits offset = CharUnits::fromQuantity(
5116  target.getStructLayout(blockInfo.StructureType)
5117  ->getElementOffset(blockInfo.getCapture(VD).getIndex()));
5118 
5119  SmallVector<uint64_t, 9> addr;
5120  addr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_deref);
5121  addr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_plus_uconst);
5122  addr.push_back(offset.getQuantity());
5123  if (isByRef) {
5124  addr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_deref);
5125  addr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_plus_uconst);
5126  // offset of __forwarding field
5127  offset =
5128  CGM.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(target.getPointerSizeInBits(0));
5129  addr.push_back(offset.getQuantity());
5130  addr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_deref);
5131  addr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_plus_uconst);
5132  // offset of x field
5133  offset = CGM.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(XOffset);
5134  addr.push_back(offset.getQuantity());
5135  }
5136 
5137  // Create the descriptor for the variable.
5138  auto Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(VD, CGM.getContext());
5139  auto *D = DBuilder.createAutoVariable(
5140  cast<llvm::DILocalScope>(LexicalBlockStack.back()), VD->getName(), Unit,
5141  Line, Ty, false, llvm::DINode::FlagZero, Align);
5142 
5143  // Insert an llvm.dbg.declare into the current block.
5144  auto DL = llvm::DILocation::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), Line, Column,
5145  LexicalBlockStack.back(), CurInlinedAt);
5146  auto *Expr = DBuilder.createExpression(addr);
5147  if (InsertPoint)
5148  DBuilder.insertDeclare(Storage, D, Expr, DL, InsertPoint);
5149  else
5150  DBuilder.insertDeclare(Storage, D, Expr, DL, Builder.GetInsertBlock());
5151 }

5153 llvm::DILocalVariable *
5154 CGDebugInfo::EmitDeclareOfArgVariable(const VarDecl *VD, llvm::Value *AI,
5155  unsigned ArgNo, CGBuilderTy &Builder,
5156  bool UsePointerValue) {
5157  assert(CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo());
5158  return EmitDeclare(VD, AI, ArgNo, Builder, UsePointerValue);
5159 }

5161 namespace {
5162 struct BlockLayoutChunk {
5163  uint64_t OffsetInBits;
5164  const BlockDecl::Capture *Capture;
5165 };
5166 bool operator<(const BlockLayoutChunk &l, const BlockLayoutChunk &r) {
5167  return l.OffsetInBits < r.OffsetInBits;
5168 }
5169 } // namespace
5170 
5171 void CGDebugInfo::collectDefaultFieldsForBlockLiteralDeclare(
5172  const CGBlockInfo &Block, const ASTContext &Context, SourceLocation Loc,
5173  const llvm::StructLayout &BlockLayout, llvm::DIFile *Unit,
5174  SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Metadata *> &Fields) {
5175  // Blocks in OpenCL have unique constraints which make the standard fields
5176  // redundant while requiring size and align fields for enqueue_kernel. See
5177  // initializeForBlockHeader in CGBlocks.cpp
5178  if (CGM.getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
5179  Fields.push_back(createFieldType("__size", Context.IntTy, Loc, AS_public,
5180  BlockLayout.getElementOffsetInBits(0),
5181  Unit, Unit));
5182  Fields.push_back(createFieldType("__align", Context.IntTy, Loc, AS_public,
5183  BlockLayout.getElementOffsetInBits(1),
5184  Unit, Unit));
5185  } else {
5186  Fields.push_back(createFieldType("__isa", Context.VoidPtrTy, Loc, AS_public,
5187  BlockLayout.getElementOffsetInBits(0),
5188  Unit, Unit));
5189  Fields.push_back(createFieldType("__flags", Context.IntTy, Loc, AS_public,
5190  BlockLayout.getElementOffsetInBits(1),
5191  Unit, Unit));
5192  Fields.push_back(
5193  createFieldType("__reserved", Context.IntTy, Loc, AS_public,
5194  BlockLayout.getElementOffsetInBits(2), Unit, Unit));
5195  auto *FnTy = Block.getBlockExpr()->getFunctionType();
5196  auto FnPtrType = CGM.getContext().getPointerType(FnTy->desugar());
5197  Fields.push_back(createFieldType("__FuncPtr", FnPtrType, Loc, AS_public,
5198  BlockLayout.getElementOffsetInBits(3),
5199  Unit, Unit));
5200  Fields.push_back(createFieldType(
5201  "__descriptor",
5202  Context.getPointerType(Block.NeedsCopyDispose
5203  ? Context.getBlockDescriptorExtendedType()
5204  : Context.getBlockDescriptorType()),
5205  Loc, AS_public, BlockLayout.getElementOffsetInBits(4), Unit, Unit));
5206  }
5207 }
5208 
5209 void CGDebugInfo::EmitDeclareOfBlockLiteralArgVariable(const CGBlockInfo &block,
5210  StringRef Name,
5211  unsigned ArgNo,
5212  llvm::AllocaInst *Alloca,
5213  CGBuilderTy &Builder) {
5214  assert(CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo());
5215  ASTContext &C = CGM.getContext();
5216  const BlockDecl *blockDecl = block.getBlockDecl();
5217 
5218  // Collect some general information about the block's location.
5219  SourceLocation loc = blockDecl->getCaretLocation();
5220  llvm::DIFile *tunit = getOrCreateFile(loc);
5221  unsigned line = getLineNumber(loc);
5222  unsigned column = getColumnNumber(loc);
5223 
5224  // Build the debug-info type for the block literal.
5225  getDeclContextDescriptor(blockDecl);
5226 
5227  const llvm::StructLayout *blockLayout =
5228  CGM.getDataLayout().getStructLayout(block.StructureType);
5229 
5230  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 16> fields;
5231  collectDefaultFieldsForBlockLiteralDeclare(block, C, loc, *blockLayout, tunit,
5232  fields);
5233 
5234  // We want to sort the captures by offset, not because DWARF
5235  // requires this, but because we're paranoid about debuggers.
5236  SmallVector<BlockLayoutChunk, 8> chunks;
5237 
5238  // 'this' capture.
5239  if (blockDecl->capturesCXXThis()) {
5240  BlockLayoutChunk chunk;
5241  chunk.OffsetInBits =
5242  blockLayout->getElementOffsetInBits(block.CXXThisIndex);
5243  chunk.Capture = nullptr;
5244  chunks.push_back(chunk);
5245  }
5246 
5247  // Variable captures.
5248  for (const auto &capture : blockDecl->captures()) {
5249  const VarDecl *variable = capture.getVariable();
5250  const CGBlockInfo::Capture &captureInfo = block.getCapture(variable);
5251 
5252  // Ignore constant captures.
5253  if (captureInfo.isConstant())
5254  continue;
5255 
5256  BlockLayoutChunk chunk;
5257  chunk.OffsetInBits =
5258  blockLayout->getElementOffsetInBits(captureInfo.getIndex());
5259  chunk.Capture = &capture;
5260  chunks.push_back(chunk);
5261  }
5262 
5263  // Sort by offset.
5264  llvm::array_pod_sort(chunks.begin(), chunks.end());
5265 
5266  for (const BlockLayoutChunk &Chunk : chunks) {
5267  uint64_t offsetInBits = Chunk.OffsetInBits;
5268  const BlockDecl::Capture *capture = Chunk.Capture;
5269 
5270  // If we have a null capture, this must be the C++ 'this' capture.
5271  if (!capture) {
5272  QualType type;
5273  if (auto *Method =
5274  cast_or_null<CXXMethodDecl>(blockDecl->getNonClosureContext()))
5275  type = Method->getThisType();
5276  else if (auto *RDecl = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(blockDecl->getParent()))
5277  type = QualType(RDecl->getTypeForDecl(), 0);
5278  else
5279  llvm_unreachable("unexpected block declcontext");
5280 
5281  fields.push_back(createFieldType("this", type, loc, AS_public,
5282  offsetInBits, tunit, tunit));
5283  continue;
5284  }
5285 
5286  const VarDecl *variable = capture->getVariable();
5287  StringRef name = variable->getName();
5288 
5289  llvm::DIType *fieldType;
5290  if (capture->isByRef()) {
5291  TypeInfo PtrInfo = C.getTypeInfo(C.VoidPtrTy);
5292  auto Align = PtrInfo.isAlignRequired() ? PtrInfo.Align : 0;
5293  // FIXME: This recomputes the layout of the BlockByRefWrapper.
5294  uint64_t xoffset;
5295  fieldType =
5296  EmitTypeForVarWithBlocksAttr(variable, &xoffset).BlockByRefWrapper;
5297  fieldType = DBuilder.createPointerType(fieldType, PtrInfo.Width);
5298  fieldType = DBuilder.createMemberType(tunit, name, tunit, line,
5299  PtrInfo.Width, Align, offsetInBits,
5300  llvm::DINode::FlagZero, fieldType);
5301  } else {
5302  auto Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(variable, CGM.getContext());
5303  fieldType = createFieldType(name, variable->getType(), loc, AS_public,
5304  offsetInBits, Align, tunit, tunit);
5305  }
5306  fields.push_back(fieldType);
5307  }
5308 
5309  SmallString<36> typeName;
5310  llvm::raw_svector_ostream(typeName)
5311  << "__block_literal_" << CGM.getUniqueBlockCount();
5312 
5313  llvm::DINodeArray fieldsArray = DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(fields);
5314 
5315  llvm::DIType *type =
5316  DBuilder.createStructType(tunit, typeName.str(), tunit, line,
5317  CGM.getContext().toBits(block.BlockSize), 0,
5318  llvm::DINode::FlagZero, nullptr, fieldsArray);
5319  type = DBuilder.createPointerType(type, CGM.PointerWidthInBits);
5320 
5321  // Get overall information about the block.
5322  llvm::DINode::DIFlags flags = llvm::DINode::FlagArtificial;
5323  auto *scope = cast<llvm::DILocalScope>(LexicalBlockStack.back());
5324 
5325  // Create the descriptor for the parameter.
5326  auto *debugVar = DBuilder.createParameterVariable(
5327  scope, Name, ArgNo, tunit, line, type, CGM.getLangOpts().Optimize, flags);
5328 
5329  // Insert an llvm.dbg.declare into the current block.
5330  DBuilder.insertDeclare(Alloca, debugVar, DBuilder.createExpression(),
5331  llvm::DILocation::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), line,
5332  column, scope, CurInlinedAt),
5333  Builder.GetInsertBlock());
5334 }
5335 
5336 llvm::DIDerivedType *
5337 CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateStaticDataMemberDeclarationOrNull(const VarDecl *D) {
5338  if (!D || !D->isStaticDataMember())
5339  return nullptr;
5340 
5341  auto MI = StaticDataMemberCache.find(D->getCanonicalDecl());
5342  if (MI != StaticDataMemberCache.end()) {
5343  assert(MI->second && "Static data member declaration should still exist");
5344  return MI->second;
5345  }
5346 
5347  // If the member wasn't found in the cache, lazily construct and add it to the
5348  // type (used when a limited form of the type is emitted).
5349  auto DC = D->getDeclContext();
5350  auto *Ctxt = cast<llvm::DICompositeType>(getDeclContextDescriptor(D));
5351  return CreateRecordStaticField(D, Ctxt, cast<RecordDecl>(DC));
5352 }

5354 llvm::DIGlobalVariableExpression *CGDebugInfo::CollectAnonRecordDecls(
5355  const RecordDecl *RD, llvm::DIFile *Unit, unsigned LineNo,
5356  StringRef LinkageName, llvm::GlobalVariable *Var, llvm::DIScope *DContext) {
5357  llvm::DIGlobalVariableExpression *GVE = nullptr;
5358 
5359  for (const auto *Field : RD->fields()) {
5360  llvm::DIType *FieldTy = getOrCreateType(Field->getType(), Unit);
5361  StringRef FieldName = Field->getName();
5362 
5363  // Ignore unnamed fields, but recurse into anonymous records.
5364  if (FieldName.empty()) {
5365  if (const auto *RT = dyn_cast<RecordType>(Field->getType()))
5366  GVE = CollectAnonRecordDecls(RT->getDecl(), Unit, LineNo, LinkageName,
5367  Var, DContext);
5368  continue;
5369  }
5370  // Use VarDecl's Tag, Scope and Line number.
5371  GVE = DBuilder.createGlobalVariableExpression(
5372  DContext, FieldName, LinkageName, Unit, LineNo, FieldTy,
5373  Var->hasLocalLinkage());
5374  Var->addDebugInfo(GVE);
5375  }
5376  return GVE;
5377 }
5378 
5379 static bool ReferencesAnonymousEntity(ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args);
5380 static bool ReferencesAnonymousEntity(RecordType *RT) {
5381  // Unnamed classes/lambdas can't be reconstituted due to a lack of column
5382  // info we produce in the DWARF, so we can't get Clang's full name back.
5383  // But so long as it's not one of those, it doesn't matter if some sub-type
5384  // of the record (a template parameter) can't be reconstituted - because the
5385  // un-reconstitutable type itself will carry its own name.
5386  const auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl());
5387  if (!RD)
5388  return false;
5389  if (!RD->getIdentifier())
5390  return true;
5391  auto *TSpecial = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RD);
5392  if (!TSpecial)
5393  return false;
5394  return ReferencesAnonymousEntity(TSpecial->getTemplateArgs().asArray());
5395 }
5396 static bool ReferencesAnonymousEntity(ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args) {
5397  return llvm::any_of(Args, [&](const TemplateArgument &TA) {
5398  switch (TA.getKind()) {
5399  case TemplateArgument::Pack:
5400  return ReferencesAnonymousEntity(TA.getPackAsArray());
5401  case TemplateArgument::Type: {
5402  struct ReferencesAnonymous
5403  : public RecursiveASTVisitor<ReferencesAnonymous> {
5404  bool RefAnon = false;
5405  bool VisitRecordType(RecordType *RT) {
5406  if (ReferencesAnonymousEntity(RT)) {
5407  RefAnon = true;
5408  return false;
5409  }
5410  return true;
5411  }
5412  };
5413  ReferencesAnonymous RT;
5414  RT.TraverseType(TA.getAsType());
5415  if (RT.RefAnon)
5416  return true;
5417  break;
5418  }
5419  default:
5420  break;
5421  }
5422  return false;
5423  });
5424 }
5425 namespace {
5426 struct ReconstitutableType : public RecursiveASTVisitor<ReconstitutableType> {
5427  bool Reconstitutable = true;
5428  bool VisitVectorType(VectorType *FT) {
5429  Reconstitutable = false;
5430  return false;
5431  }
5432  bool VisitAtomicType(AtomicType *FT) {
5433  Reconstitutable = false;
5434  return false;
5435  }
5436  bool VisitType(Type *T) {
5437  // _BitInt(N) isn't reconstitutable because the bit width isn't encoded in
5438  // the DWARF, only the byte width.
5439  if (T->isBitIntType()) {
5440  Reconstitutable = false;
5441  return false;
5442  }
5443  return true;
5444  }
5445  bool TraverseEnumType(EnumType *ET) {
5446  // Unnamed enums can't be reconstituted due to a lack of column info we
5447  // produce in the DWARF, so we can't get Clang's full name back.
5448  if (const auto *ED = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(ET->getDecl())) {
5449  if (!ED->getIdentifier()) {
5450  Reconstitutable = false;
5451  return false;
5452  }
5453  if (!ED->isExternallyVisible()) {
5454  Reconstitutable = false;
5455  return false;
5456  }
5457  }
5458  return true;
5459  }
5460  bool VisitFunctionProtoType(FunctionProtoType *FT) {
5461  // noexcept is not encoded in DWARF, so the reversi
5462  Reconstitutable &= !isNoexceptExceptionSpec(FT->getExceptionSpecType());
5463  Reconstitutable &= !FT->getNoReturnAttr();
5464  return Reconstitutable;
5465  }
5466  bool VisitRecordType(RecordType *RT) {
5467  if (ReferencesAnonymousEntity(RT)) {
5468  Reconstitutable = false;
5469  return false;
5470  }
5471  return true;
5472  }
5473 };
5474 } // anonymous namespace
5475 
5476 // Test whether a type name could be rebuilt from emitted debug info.
5477 static bool IsReconstitutableType(QualType QT) {
5478  ReconstitutableType T;
5479  T.TraverseType(QT);
5480  return T.Reconstitutable;
5481 }
5482 
5483 bool CGDebugInfo::HasReconstitutableArgs(
5484  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args) const {
5485  return llvm::all_of(Args, [&](const TemplateArgument &TA) {
5486  switch (TA.getKind()) {
5487  case TemplateArgument::Template:
5488  // Easy to reconstitute - the value of the parameter in the debug
5489  // info is the string name of the template. The template name
5490  // itself won't benefit from any name rebuilding, but that's a
5491  // representational limitation - maybe DWARF could be
5492  // changed/improved to use some more structural representation.
5493  return true;
5494  case TemplateArgument::Declaration:
5495  // Reference and pointer non-type template parameters point to
5496  // variables, functions, etc and their value is, at best (for
5497  // variables) represented as an address - not a reference to the
5498  // DWARF describing the variable/function/etc. This makes it hard,
5499  // possibly impossible to rebuild the original name - looking up
5500  // the address in the executable file's symbol table would be
5501  // needed.
5502  return false;
5503  case TemplateArgument::NullPtr:
5504  // These could be rebuilt, but figured they're close enough to the
5505  // declaration case, and not worth rebuilding.
5506  return false;
5507  case TemplateArgument::Pack:
5508  // A pack is invalid if any of the elements of the pack are
5509  // invalid.
5510  return HasReconstitutableArgs(TA.getPackAsArray());
5511  case TemplateArgument::Integral:
5512  // Larger integers get encoded as DWARF blocks which are a bit
5513  // harder to parse back into a large integer, etc - so punting on
5514  // this for now. Re-parsing the integers back into APInt is
5515  // probably feasible some day.
5516  return TA.getAsIntegral().getBitWidth() <= 64 &&
5517  IsReconstitutableType(TA.getIntegralType());
5518  case TemplateArgument::StructuralValue:
5519  return false;
5520  case TemplateArgument::Type:
5521  return IsReconstitutableType(TA.getAsType());
5522  case TemplateArgument::Expression:
5523  return IsReconstitutableType(TA.getAsExpr()->getType());
5524  default:
5525  llvm_unreachable("Other, unresolved, template arguments should "
5526  "not be seen here");
5527  }
5528  });
5529 }
5530 
5531 std::string CGDebugInfo::GetName(const Decl *D, bool Qualified) const {
5532  std::string Name;
5533  llvm::raw_string_ostream OS(Name);
5534  const NamedDecl *ND = dyn_cast<NamedDecl>(D);
5535  if (!ND)
5536  return Name;
5537  llvm::codegenoptions::DebugTemplateNamesKind TemplateNamesKind =
5538  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().getDebugSimpleTemplateNames();
5539 
5540  if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo())
5541  TemplateNamesKind = llvm::codegenoptions::DebugTemplateNamesKind::Full;
5542 
5543  std::optional<TemplateArgs> Args;
5544 
5545  bool IsOperatorOverload = false; // isa<CXXConversionDecl>(ND);
5546  if (auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(ND)) {
5547  Args = GetTemplateArgs(RD);
5548  } else if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(ND)) {
5549  Args = GetTemplateArgs(FD);
5550  auto NameKind = ND->getDeclName().getNameKind();
5551  IsOperatorOverload |=
5552  NameKind == DeclarationName::CXXOperatorName ||
5553  NameKind == DeclarationName::CXXConversionFunctionName;
5554  } else if (auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(ND)) {
5555  Args = GetTemplateArgs(VD);
5556  }
5557 
5558  // A conversion operator presents complications/ambiguity if there's a
5559  // conversion to class template that is itself a template, eg:
5560  // template<typename T>
5561  // operator ns::t1<T, int>();
5562  // This should be named, eg: "operator ns::t1<float, int><float>"
5563  // (ignoring clang bug that means this is currently "operator t1<float>")
5564  // but if the arguments were stripped, the consumer couldn't differentiate
5565  // whether the template argument list for the conversion type was the
5566  // function's argument list (& no reconstitution was needed) or not.
5567  // This could be handled if reconstitutable names had a separate attribute
5568  // annotating them as such - this would remove the ambiguity.
5569  //
5570  // Alternatively the template argument list could be parsed enough to check
5571  // whether there's one list or two, then compare that with the DWARF
5572  // description of the return type and the template argument lists to determine
5573  // how many lists there should be and if one is missing it could be assumed(?)
5574  // to be the function's template argument list & then be rebuilt.
5575  //
5576  // Other operator overloads that aren't conversion operators could be
5577  // reconstituted but would require a bit more nuance about detecting the
5578  // difference between these different operators during that rebuilding.
5579  bool Reconstitutable =
5580  Args && HasReconstitutableArgs(Args->Args) && !IsOperatorOverload;
5581 
5582  PrintingPolicy PP = getPrintingPolicy();
5583 
5584  if (TemplateNamesKind == llvm::codegenoptions::DebugTemplateNamesKind::Full ||
5585  !Reconstitutable) {
5586  ND->getNameForDiagnostic(OS, PP, Qualified);
5587  } else {
5588  bool Mangled = TemplateNamesKind ==
5589  llvm::codegenoptions::DebugTemplateNamesKind::Mangled;
5590  // check if it's a template
5591  if (Mangled)
5592  OS << "_STN|";
5593 
5594  OS << ND->getDeclName();
5595  std::string EncodedOriginalName;
5596  llvm::raw_string_ostream EncodedOriginalNameOS(EncodedOriginalName);
5597  EncodedOriginalNameOS << ND->getDeclName();
5598 
5599  if (Mangled) {
5600  OS << "|";
5601  printTemplateArgumentList(OS, Args->Args, PP);
5602  printTemplateArgumentList(EncodedOriginalNameOS, Args->Args, PP);
5603 #ifndef NDEBUG
5604  std::string CanonicalOriginalName;
5605  llvm::raw_string_ostream OriginalOS(CanonicalOriginalName);
5606  ND->getNameForDiagnostic(OriginalOS, PP, Qualified);
5607  assert(EncodedOriginalNameOS.str() == OriginalOS.str());
5608 #endif
5609  }
5610  }
5611  return Name;
5612 }
5613 
5614 void CGDebugInfo::EmitGlobalVariable(llvm::GlobalVariable *Var,
5615  const VarDecl *D) {
5616  assert(CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo());
5617  if (D->hasAttr<NoDebugAttr>() || noSystemDebugInfo(D, CGM))
5618  return;
5619 
5620  llvm::TimeTraceScope TimeScope("DebugGlobalVariable", [&]() {
5621  return GetName(D, true);
5622  });
5623 
5624  // If we already created a DIGlobalVariable for this declaration, just attach
5625  // it to the llvm::GlobalVariable.
5626  auto Cached = DeclCache.find(D->getCanonicalDecl());
5627  if (Cached != DeclCache.end())
5628  return Var->addDebugInfo(
5629  cast<llvm::DIGlobalVariableExpression>(Cached->second));
5630 
5631  // Create global variable debug descriptor.
5632  llvm::DIFile *Unit = nullptr;
5633  llvm::DIScope *DContext = nullptr;
5634  unsigned LineNo;
5635  StringRef DeclName, LinkageName;
5636  QualType T;
5637  llvm::MDTuple *TemplateParameters = nullptr;
5638  collectVarDeclProps(D, Unit, LineNo, T, DeclName, LinkageName,
5639  TemplateParameters, DContext);
5640 
5641  // Attempt to store one global variable for the declaration - even if we
5642  // emit a lot of fields.
5643  llvm::DIGlobalVariableExpression *GVE = nullptr;
5644 
5645  // If this is an anonymous union then we'll want to emit a global
5646  // variable for each member of the anonymous union so that it's possible
5647  // to find the name of any field in the union.
5648  if (T->isUnionType() && DeclName.empty()) {
5649  const RecordDecl *RD = T->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
5650  assert(RD->isAnonymousStructOrUnion() &&
5651  "unnamed non-anonymous struct or union?");
5652  GVE = CollectAnonRecordDecls(RD, Unit, LineNo, LinkageName, Var, DContext);
5653  } else {
5654  auto Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(D, CGM.getContext());
5655 
5656  SmallVector<uint64_t, 4> Expr;
5657  unsigned AddressSpace = CGM.getTypes().getTargetAddressSpace(D->getType());
5658  if (CGM.getLangOpts().CUDA && CGM.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice) {
5659  if (D->hasAttr<CUDASharedAttr>())
5660  AddressSpace =
5661  CGM.getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::cuda_shared);
5662  else if (D->hasAttr<CUDAConstantAttr>())
5663  AddressSpace =
5664  CGM.getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::cuda_constant);
5665  }
5666  AppendAddressSpaceXDeref(AddressSpace, Expr);
5667 
5668  llvm::DINodeArray Annotations = CollectBTFDeclTagAnnotations(D);
5669  GVE = DBuilder.createGlobalVariableExpression(
5670  DContext, DeclName, LinkageName, Unit, LineNo, getOrCreateType(T, Unit),
5671  Var->hasLocalLinkage(), true,
5672  Expr.empty() ? nullptr : DBuilder.createExpression(Expr),
5673  getOrCreateStaticDataMemberDeclarationOrNull(D), TemplateParameters,
5674  Align, Annotations);
5675  Var->addDebugInfo(GVE);
5676  }
5677  DeclCache[D->getCanonicalDecl()].reset(GVE);
5678 }
5679 
5680 void CGDebugInfo::EmitGlobalVariable(const ValueDecl *VD, const APValue &Init) {
5681  assert(CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo());
5682  if (VD->hasAttr<NoDebugAttr>() || noSystemDebugInfo(VD, CGM))
5683  return;
5684  llvm::TimeTraceScope TimeScope("DebugConstGlobalVariable", [&]() {
5685  return GetName(VD, true);
5686  });
5687 
5688  auto Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(VD, CGM.getContext());
5689  // Create the descriptor for the variable.
5690  llvm::DIFile *Unit = getOrCreateFile(VD->getLocation());
5691  StringRef Name = VD->getName();
5692  llvm::DIType *Ty = getOrCreateType(VD->getType(), Unit);
5693 
5694  if (const auto *ECD = dyn_cast<EnumConstantDecl>(VD)) {
5695  const auto *ED = cast<EnumDecl>(ECD->getDeclContext());
5696  assert(isa<EnumType>(ED->getTypeForDecl()) && "Enum without EnumType?");
5697 
5698  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCodeView) {
5699  // If CodeView, emit enums as global variables, unless they are defined
5700  // inside a class. We do this because MSVC doesn't emit S_CONSTANTs for
5701  // enums in classes, and because it is difficult to attach this scope
5702  // information to the global variable.
5703  if (isa<RecordDecl>(ED->getDeclContext()))
5704  return;
5705  } else {
5706  // If not CodeView, emit DW_TAG_enumeration_type if necessary. For
5707  // example: for "enum { ZERO };", a DW_TAG_enumeration_type is created the
5708  // first time `ZERO` is referenced in a function.
5709  llvm::DIType *EDTy =
5710  getOrCreateType(QualType(ED->getTypeForDecl(), 0), Unit);
5711  assert (EDTy->getTag() == llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_enumeration_type);
5712  (void)EDTy;
5713  return;
5714  }
5715  }
5716 
5717  // Do not emit separate definitions for function local consts.
5718  if (isa<FunctionDecl>(VD->getDeclContext()))
5719  return;
5720 
5721  VD = cast<ValueDecl>(VD->getCanonicalDecl());
5722  auto *VarD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(VD);
5723  if (VarD && VarD->isStaticDataMember()) {
5724  auto *RD = cast<RecordDecl>(VarD->getDeclContext());
5725  getDeclContextDescriptor(VarD);
5726  // Ensure that the type is retained even though it's otherwise unreferenced.
5727  //
5728  // FIXME: This is probably unnecessary, since Ty should reference RD
5729  // through its scope.
5730  RetainedTypes.push_back(
5731  CGM.getContext().getRecordType(RD).getAsOpaquePtr());
5732 
5733  return;
5734  }
5735  llvm::DIScope *DContext = getDeclContextDescriptor(VD);
5736 
5737  auto &GV = DeclCache[VD];
5738  if (GV)
5739  return;
5740 
5741  llvm::DIExpression *InitExpr = createConstantValueExpression(VD, Init);
5742  llvm::MDTuple *TemplateParameters = nullptr;
5743 
5744  if (isa<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(VD))
5745  if (VarD) {
5746  llvm::DINodeArray parameterNodes = CollectVarTemplateParams(VarD, &*Unit);
5747  TemplateParameters = parameterNodes.get();
5748  }
5749 
5750  GV.reset(DBuilder.createGlobalVariableExpression(
5751  DContext, Name, StringRef(), Unit, getLineNumber(VD->getLocation()), Ty,
5752  true, true, InitExpr, getOrCreateStaticDataMemberDeclarationOrNull(VarD),
5753  TemplateParameters, Align));
5754 }
5755 
5756 void CGDebugInfo::EmitExternalVariable(llvm::GlobalVariable *Var,
5757  const VarDecl *D) {
5758  assert(CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo());
5759  if (D->hasAttr<NoDebugAttr>() || noSystemDebugInfo(D, CGM))
5760  return;
5761 
5762  auto Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(D, CGM.getContext());
5763  llvm::DIFile *Unit = getOrCreateFile(D->getLocation());
5764  StringRef Name = D->getName();
5765  llvm::DIType *Ty = getOrCreateType(D->getType(), Unit);
5766 
5767  llvm::DIScope *DContext = getDeclContextDescriptor(D);
5768  llvm::DIGlobalVariableExpression *GVE =
5769  DBuilder.createGlobalVariableExpression(
5770  DContext, Name, StringRef(), Unit, getLineNumber(D->getLocation()),
5771  Ty, false, false, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, Align);
5772  Var->addDebugInfo(GVE);
5773 }

5775 void CGDebugInfo::EmitGlobalAlias(const llvm::GlobalValue *GV,
5776  const GlobalDecl GD) {
5777 
5778  assert(GV);
5779 
5780  if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo())
5781  return;
5782 
5783  const auto *D = cast<ValueDecl>(GD.getDecl());
5784  if (D->hasAttr<NoDebugAttr>() || noSystemDebugInfo(D, CGM))
5785  return;
5786 
5787  auto AliaseeDecl = CGM.getMangledNameDecl(GV->getName());
5788  llvm::DINode *DI;
5789 
5790  if (!AliaseeDecl)
5791  // FIXME: Aliasee not declared yet - possibly declared later
5792  // For example,
5793  //
5794  // 1 extern int newname __attribute__((alias("oldname")));
5795  // 2 int oldname = 1;
5796  //
5797  // No debug info would be generated for 'newname' in this case.
5798  //
5799  // Fix compiler to generate "newname" as imported_declaration
5800  // pointing to the DIE of "oldname".
5801  return;
5802  if (!(DI = getDeclarationOrDefinition(
5803  AliaseeDecl.getCanonicalDecl().getDecl())))
5804  return;
5805 
5806  llvm::DIScope *DContext = getDeclContextDescriptor(D);
5807  auto Loc = D->getLocation();
5808 
5809  llvm::DIImportedEntity *ImportDI = DBuilder.createImportedDeclaration(
5810  DContext, DI, getOrCreateFile(Loc), getLineNumber(Loc), D->getName());
5811 
5812  // Record this DIE in the cache for nested declaration reference.
5813  ImportedDeclCache[GD.getCanonicalDecl().getDecl()].reset(ImportDI);
5814 }

5816 void CGDebugInfo::AddStringLiteralDebugInfo(llvm::GlobalVariable *GV,
5817  const StringLiteral *S) {
5818  SourceLocation Loc = S->getStrTokenLoc(0);
5819  PresumedLoc PLoc = CGM.getContext().getSourceManager().getPresumedLoc(Loc);
5820  if (!PLoc.isValid())
5821  return;
5822 
5823  llvm::DIFile *File = getOrCreateFile(Loc);
5824  llvm::DIGlobalVariableExpression *Debug =
5825  DBuilder.createGlobalVariableExpression(
5826  nullptr, StringRef(), StringRef(), getOrCreateFile(Loc),
5827  getLineNumber(Loc), getOrCreateType(S->getType(), File), true);
5828  GV->addDebugInfo(Debug);
5829 }

5834  llvm::DIScope *Mod = getParentModuleOrNull(D);

5838 void CGDebugInfo::EmitUsingDirective(const UsingDirectiveDecl &UD) {
5839  if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo())
5840  return;
5841  if (noSystemDebugInfo(&UD, CGM))
5842  return;
5843  const NamespaceDecl *NSDecl = UD.getNominatedNamespace();
5844  if (!NSDecl->isAnonymousNamespace() ||
5845  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DebugExplicitImport) {
5846  auto Loc = UD.getLocation();
5847  if (!Loc.isValid())
5848  Loc = CurLoc;
5849  DBuilder.createImportedModule(
5850  getCurrentContextDescriptor(cast<Decl>(UD.getDeclContext())),
5851  getOrCreateNamespace(NSDecl), getOrCreateFile(Loc), getLineNumber(Loc));
5852  }
5853 }

5855 void CGDebugInfo::EmitUsingShadowDecl(const UsingShadowDecl &USD) {
5856  if (llvm::DINode *Target =
5857  getDeclarationOrDefinition(USD.getUnderlyingDecl())) {
5858  auto Loc = USD.getLocation();
5859  DBuilder.createImportedDeclaration(
5860  getCurrentContextDescriptor(cast<Decl>(USD.getDeclContext())), Target,
5861  getOrCreateFile(Loc), getLineNumber(Loc));
5862  }
5863 }
5864 
5865 void CGDebugInfo::EmitUsingDecl(const UsingDecl &UD) {
5866  if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo())
5867  return;
5868  if (noSystemDebugInfo(&UD, CGM))
5869  return;
5870  assert(UD.shadow_size() &&
5871  "We shouldn't be codegening an invalid UsingDecl containing no decls");
5872 
5873  for (const auto *USD : UD.shadows()) {
5874  // FIXME: Skip functions with undeduced auto return type for now since we
5875  // don't currently have the plumbing for separate declarations & definitions
5876  // of free functions and mismatched types (auto in the declaration, concrete
5877  // return type in the definition)
5878  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(USD->getUnderlyingDecl()))
5879  if (const auto *AT = FD->getType()
5880  ->castAs<FunctionProtoType>()
5881  ->getContainedAutoType())
5882  if (AT->getDeducedType().isNull())
5883  continue;
5884 
5885  EmitUsingShadowDecl(*USD);
5886  // Emitting one decl is sufficient - debuggers can detect that this is an
5887  // overloaded name & provide lookup for all the overloads.
5888  break;
5889  }
5890 }
5891 
5892 void CGDebugInfo::EmitUsingEnumDecl(const UsingEnumDecl &UD) {
5893  if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo())
5894  return;
5895  if (noSystemDebugInfo(&UD, CGM))
5896  return;
5897  assert(UD.shadow_size() &&
5898  "We shouldn't be codegening an invalid UsingEnumDecl"
5899  " containing no decls");
5900 
5901  for (const auto *USD : UD.shadows())
5902  EmitUsingShadowDecl(*USD);
5903 }

5905 void CGDebugInfo::EmitImportDecl(const ImportDecl &ID) {
5906  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().getDebuggerTuning() != llvm::DebuggerKind::LLDB)
5907  return;
5908  if (Module *M = ID.getImportedModule()) {
5909  auto Info = ASTSourceDescriptor(*M);
5910  auto Loc = ID.getLocation();
5911  DBuilder.createImportedDeclaration(
5912  getCurrentContextDescriptor(cast<Decl>(ID.getDeclContext())),
5913  getOrCreateModuleRef(Info, DebugTypeExtRefs), getOrCreateFile(Loc),
5914  getLineNumber(Loc));
5915  }
5916 }

5918 llvm::DIImportedEntity *
5919 CGDebugInfo::EmitNamespaceAlias(const NamespaceAliasDecl &NA) {
5920  if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo())
5921  return nullptr;
5922  if (noSystemDebugInfo(&NA, CGM))
5923  return nullptr;
5924  auto &VH = NamespaceAliasCache[&NA];
5925  if (VH)
5926  return cast<llvm::DIImportedEntity>(VH);
5927  llvm::DIImportedEntity *R;
5928  auto Loc = NA.getLocation();
5929  if (const auto *Underlying =
5930  dyn_cast<NamespaceAliasDecl>(NA.getAliasedNamespace()))
5931  // This could cache & dedup here rather than relying on metadata deduping.
5932  R = DBuilder.createImportedDeclaration(
5933  getCurrentContextDescriptor(cast<Decl>(NA.getDeclContext())),
5934  EmitNamespaceAlias(*Underlying), getOrCreateFile(Loc),
5935  getLineNumber(Loc), NA.getName());
5936  else
5937  R = DBuilder.createImportedDeclaration(
5938  getCurrentContextDescriptor(cast<Decl>(NA.getDeclContext())),
5939  getOrCreateNamespace(cast<NamespaceDecl>(NA.getAliasedNamespace())),
5940  getOrCreateFile(Loc), getLineNumber(Loc), NA.getName());
5941  VH.reset(R);
5942  return R;
5943 }
5944 
5945 llvm::DINamespace *
5946 CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateNamespace(const NamespaceDecl *NSDecl) {
5947  // Don't canonicalize the NamespaceDecl here: The DINamespace will be uniqued
5948  // if necessary, and this way multiple declarations of the same namespace in
5949  // different parent modules stay distinct.
5950  auto I = NamespaceCache.find(NSDecl);
5951  if (I != NamespaceCache.end())
5952  return cast<llvm::DINamespace>(I->second);
5953 
5954  llvm::DIScope *Context = getDeclContextDescriptor(NSDecl);
5955  // Don't trust the context if it is a DIModule (see comment above).
5956  llvm::DINamespace *NS =
5957  DBuilder.createNameSpace(Context, NSDecl->getName(), NSDecl->isInline());
5958  NamespaceCache[NSDecl].reset(NS);
5959  return NS;
5960 }

5962 void CGDebugInfo::setDwoId(uint64_t Signature) {
5963  assert(TheCU && "no main compile unit");
5964  TheCU->setDWOId(Signature);
5965 }
5966 
5967 void CGDebugInfo::finalize() {
5968  // Creating types might create further types - invalidating the current
5969  // element and the size(), so don't cache/reference them.
5970  for (size_t i = 0; i != ObjCInterfaceCache.size(); ++i) {
5971  ObjCInterfaceCacheEntry E = ObjCInterfaceCache[i];
5972  llvm::DIType *Ty = E.Type->getDecl()->getDefinition()
5973  ? CreateTypeDefinition(E.Type, E.Unit)
5974  : E.Decl;
5975  DBuilder.replaceTemporary(llvm::TempDIType(E.Decl), Ty);
5976  }
5977 
5978  // Add methods to interface.
5979  for (const auto &P : ObjCMethodCache) {
5980  if (P.second.empty())
5981  continue;
5982 
5983  QualType QTy(P.first->getTypeForDecl(), 0);
5984  auto It = TypeCache.find(QTy.getAsOpaquePtr());
5985  assert(It != TypeCache.end());
5986 
5987  llvm::DICompositeType *InterfaceDecl =
5988  cast<llvm::DICompositeType>(It->second);
5989 
5990  auto CurElts = InterfaceDecl->getElements();
5991  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 16> EltTys(CurElts.begin(), CurElts.end());
5992 
5993  // For DWARF v4 or earlier, only add objc_direct methods.
5994  for (auto &SubprogramDirect : P.second)
5995  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DwarfVersion >= 5 || SubprogramDirect.getInt())
5996  EltTys.push_back(SubprogramDirect.getPointer());
5997 
5998  llvm::DINodeArray Elements = DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(EltTys);
5999  DBuilder.replaceArrays(InterfaceDecl, Elements);
6000  }
6001 
6002  for (const auto &P : ReplaceMap) {
6003  assert(P.second);
6004  auto *Ty = cast<llvm::DIType>(P.second);
6005  assert(Ty->isForwardDecl());
6006 
6007  auto It = TypeCache.find(P.first);
6008  assert(It != TypeCache.end());
6009  assert(It->second);
6010 
6011  DBuilder.replaceTemporary(llvm::TempDIType(Ty),
6012  cast<llvm::DIType>(It->second));
6013  }
6014 
6015  for (const auto &P : FwdDeclReplaceMap) {
6016  assert(P.second);
6017  llvm::TempMDNode FwdDecl(cast<llvm::MDNode>(P.second));
6018  llvm::Metadata *Repl;
6019 
6020  auto It = DeclCache.find(P.first);
6021  // If there has been no definition for the declaration, call RAUW
6022  // with ourselves, that will destroy the temporary MDNode and
6023  // replace it with a standard one, avoiding leaking memory.
6024  if (It == DeclCache.end())
6025  Repl = P.second;
6026  else
6027  Repl = It->second;
6028 
6029  if (auto *GVE = dyn_cast_or_null<llvm::DIGlobalVariableExpression>(Repl))
6030  Repl = GVE->getVariable();
6031  DBuilder.replaceTemporary(std::move(FwdDecl), cast<llvm::MDNode>(Repl));
6032  }
6033 
6034  // We keep our own list of retained types, because we need to look
6035  // up the final type in the type cache.
6036  for (auto &RT : RetainedTypes)
6037  if (auto MD = TypeCache[RT])
6038  DBuilder.retainType(cast<llvm::DIType>(MD));
6039 
6040  DBuilder.finalize();
6041 }
6042 
6043 // Don't ignore in case of explicit cast where it is referenced indirectly.
6044 void CGDebugInfo::EmitExplicitCastType(QualType Ty) {
6045  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo())
6046  if (auto *DieTy = getOrCreateType(Ty, TheCU->getFile()))
6047  DBuilder.retainType(DieTy);
6048 }
6049 
6050 void CGDebugInfo::EmitAndRetainType(QualType Ty) {
6051  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasMaybeUnusedDebugInfo())
6052  if (auto *DieTy = getOrCreateType(Ty, TheCU->getFile()))
6053  DBuilder.retainType(DieTy);
6054 }

6056 llvm::DebugLoc CGDebugInfo::SourceLocToDebugLoc(SourceLocation Loc) {
6057  if (LexicalBlockStack.empty())
6058  return llvm::DebugLoc();
6059 
6060  llvm::MDNode *Scope = LexicalBlockStack.back();
6061  return llvm::DILocation::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), getLineNumber(Loc),
6062  getColumnNumber(Loc), Scope);
6063 }
6064 
6065 llvm::DINode::DIFlags CGDebugInfo::getCallSiteRelatedAttrs() const {
6066  // Call site-related attributes are only useful in optimized programs, and
6067  // when there's a possibility of debugging backtraces.
6068  if (!CGM.getLangOpts().Optimize ||
6069  DebugKind == llvm::codegenoptions::NoDebugInfo ||
6070  DebugKind == llvm::codegenoptions::LocTrackingOnly)
6071  return llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
6072 
6073  // Call site-related attributes are available in DWARF v5. Some debuggers,
6074  // while not fully DWARF v5-compliant, may accept these attributes as if they
6075  // were part of DWARF v4.
6076  bool SupportsDWARFv4Ext =
6077  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DwarfVersion == 4 &&
6078  (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().getDebuggerTuning() == llvm::DebuggerKind::LLDB ||
6079  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().getDebuggerTuning() == llvm::DebuggerKind::GDB);
6080 
6081  if (!SupportsDWARFv4Ext && CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DwarfVersion < 5)
6082  return llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
6083 
6084  return llvm::DINode::FlagAllCallsDescribed;
6085 }
6086 
6087 llvm::DIExpression *
6088 CGDebugInfo::createConstantValueExpression(const clang::ValueDecl *VD,
6089  const APValue &Val) {
6090  // FIXME: Add a representation for integer constants wider than 64 bits.
6091  if (CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(VD->getType()) > 64)
6092  return nullptr;
6093 
6094  if (Val.isFloat())
6095  return DBuilder.createConstantValueExpression(
6096  Val.getFloat().bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue());
6097 
6098  if (!Val.isInt())
6099  return nullptr;
6100 
6101  llvm::APSInt const &ValInt = Val.getInt();
6102  std::optional<uint64_t> ValIntOpt;
6103  if (ValInt.isUnsigned())
6104  ValIntOpt = ValInt.tryZExtValue();
6105  else if (auto tmp = ValInt.trySExtValue())
6106  // Transform a signed optional to unsigned optional. When cpp 23 comes,
6107  // use std::optional::transform
6108  ValIntOpt = static_cast<uint64_t>(*tmp);
6109 
6110  if (ValIntOpt)
6111  return DBuilder.createConstantValueExpression(ValIntOpt.value());
6112 
6113  return nullptr;
6114 }
6115 
6116 bool clang::CodeGen::noSystemDebugInfo(const Decl *D,
6117  const CodeGenModule &CGM) {
6118  // Declaration is in system file
6119  if (CGM.getContext().getSourceManager().isInSystemHeader(D->getLocation())) {
6120  // Make an exception for typedefs in system header files. Generate debug
6121  // information for these decls because these are rare (thus they will not
6122  // greatly increase debug size) and a user could rely on these typedefs
6123  // during debugging. For example uid_t in in "sys/types.h" can be used in
6124  // the gdb command:
6125  //
6126  // print ruid == (uid_t)-1
6127  //
6128  // This occurs in GDB test gdb.reverse/getresuid-reverse.c
6129  if (isa<TypedefDecl>(D))
6130  return false;
6131 
6132  // -fno-system-debug was used. Do not generate debug info.
6133  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().NoSystemDebug)
6134  return true;
6135  }
6136  return false;
6137 }
